53/// Determine whether the given binary operation may overflow.
54/// Sets \p Result to the value of the operation for BO_Add, BO_Sub, BO_Mul,
55/// and signed BO_{Div,Rem}. For these opcodes, and for unsigned BO_{Div,Rem},
56/// the returned overflow check is precise. The returned value is 'true' for
57/// all other opcodes, to be conservative.
58bool mayHaveIntegerOverflow(llvm::ConstantInt *LHS, llvm::ConstantInt *RHS,
59 BinaryOperator::Opcode Opcode, bool Signed,
60 llvm::APInt &Result) {
61 // Assume overflow is possible, unless we can prove otherwise.
62 bool Overflow = true;
63 const auto &LHSAP = LHS->getValue();
64 const auto &RHSAP = RHS->getValue();
65 if (Opcode == BO_Add) {
66 if (Signed)
67 Result = LHSAP.sadd_ov(RHSAP, Overflow);
68 else
69 Result = LHSAP.uadd_ov(RHSAP, Overflow);
70 } else if (Opcode == BO_Sub) {
71 if (Signed)
72 Result = LHSAP.ssub_ov(RHSAP, Overflow);
73 else
74 Result = LHSAP.usub_ov(RHSAP, Overflow);
75 } else if (Opcode == BO_Mul) {
76 if (Signed)
77 Result = LHSAP.smul_ov(RHSAP, Overflow);
78 else
79 Result = LHSAP.umul_ov(RHSAP, Overflow);
80 } else if (Opcode == BO_Div || Opcode == BO_Rem) {
81 if (Signed && !RHS->isZero())
82 Result = LHSAP.sdiv_ov(RHSAP, Overflow);
83 else
84 return false;
85 }
86 return Overflow;
87}
88
89struct BinOpInfo {
90 Value *LHS;
91 Value *RHS;
92 QualType Ty; // Computation Type.
93 BinaryOperator::Opcode Opcode; // Opcode of BinOp to perform
94 FPOptions FPFeatures;
95 const Expr *E; // Entire expr, for error unsupported. May not be binop.
96 // For CHERI we may have to use NULL as the resulting base in a bitiwise-and
97 // instead of the LHS (see https://github.com/CTSRD-CHERI/clang/issues/189)
98 Value *ResultProvenanceOverride = nullptr;
99
100 /// Check if the binop can result in integer overflow.
101 bool mayHaveIntegerOverflow() const {
102 // Without constant input, we can't rule out overflow.
103 auto *LHSCI = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(LHS);
104 auto *RHSCI = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(RHS);
105 if (!LHSCI || !RHSCI)
106 return true;
107
108 llvm::APInt Result;
109 return ::mayHaveIntegerOverflow(
110 LHSCI, RHSCI, Opcode, Ty->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation(), Result);
111 }
112
113 /// Check if the binop computes a division or a remainder.
114 bool isDivremOp() const {
115 return Opcode == BO_Div || Opcode == BO_Rem || Opcode == BO_DivAssign ||
116 Opcode == BO_RemAssign;
117 }
118
119 /// Check if the binop can result in an integer division by zero.
120 bool mayHaveIntegerDivisionByZero() const {
121 if (isDivremOp())
122 if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(RHS))
123 return CI->isZero();
124 return true;
125 }
126
127 /// Check if the binop can result in a float division by zero.
128 bool mayHaveFloatDivisionByZero() const {
129 if (isDivremOp())
130 if (auto *CFP = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantFP>(RHS))
131 return CFP->isZero();
132 return true;
133 }
134
135 /// Check if either operand is a fixed point type or integer type, with at
136 /// least one being a fixed point type. In any case, this
137 /// operation did not follow usual arithmetic conversion and both operands may
138 /// not be the same.
139 bool isFixedPointBinOp() const {
140 // We cannot simply check the result type since comparison operations return
141 // an int.
142 if (const auto *BinOp = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(E)) {
143 QualType LHSType = BinOp->getLHS()->getType();
144 QualType RHSType = BinOp->getRHS()->getType();
145 return LHSType->isFixedPointType() || RHSType->isFixedPointType();
146 }
147 return false;
148 }
149};
150
151static bool MustVisitNullValue(const Expr *E) {
152 // If a null pointer expression's type is the C++0x nullptr_t, then
153 // it's not necessarily a simple constant and it must be evaluated
154 // for its potential side effects.
155 return E->getType()->isNullPtrType();
156}
157
158/// If \p E is a widened promoted integer, get its base (unpromoted) type.
159static llvm::Optional<QualType> getUnwidenedIntegerType(const ASTContext &Ctx,
160 const Expr *E) {
161 const Expr *Base = E->IgnoreImpCasts();
162 if (E == Base)
163 return llvm::None;
164
165 QualType BaseTy = Base->getType();
166 if (!BaseTy->isPromotableIntegerType() ||
167 Ctx.getTypeSize(BaseTy) >= Ctx.getTypeSize(E->getType()))
168 return llvm::None;
169
170 return BaseTy;
171}
172
173/// Check if \p E is a widened promoted integer.
174static bool IsWidenedIntegerOp(const ASTContext &Ctx, const Expr *E) {
175 return getUnwidenedIntegerType(Ctx, E).hasValue();
176}
177
178/// Check if we can skip the overflow check for \p Op.
179static bool CanElideOverflowCheck(const ASTContext &Ctx, const BinOpInfo &Op) {
180 assert((isa<UnaryOperator>(Op.E) || isa<BinaryOperator>(Op.E)) &&
181 "Expected a unary or binary operator");
182
183 // If the binop has constant inputs and we can prove there is no overflow,
184 // we can elide the overflow check.
185 if (!Op.mayHaveIntegerOverflow())
186 return true;
187
188 // If a unary op has a widened operand, the op cannot overflow.
189 if (const auto *UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(Op.E))
190 return !UO->canOverflow();
191
192 // We usually don't need overflow checks for binops with widened operands.
193 // Multiplication with promoted unsigned operands is a special case.
194 const auto *BO = cast<BinaryOperator>(Op.E);
195 auto OptionalLHSTy = getUnwidenedIntegerType(Ctx, BO->getLHS());
196 if (!OptionalLHSTy)
197 return false;
198
199 auto OptionalRHSTy = getUnwidenedIntegerType(Ctx, BO->getRHS());
200 if (!OptionalRHSTy)
201 return false;
202
203 QualType LHSTy = *OptionalLHSTy;
204 QualType RHSTy = *OptionalRHSTy;
205
206 // This is the simple case: binops without unsigned multiplication, and with
207 // widened operands. No overflow check is needed here.
208 if ((Op.Opcode != BO_Mul && Op.Opcode != BO_MulAssign) ||
209 !LHSTy->isUnsignedIntegerType() || !RHSTy->isUnsignedIntegerType())
210 return true;
211
212 // For unsigned multiplication the overflow check can be elided if either one
213 // of the unpromoted types are less than half the size of the promoted type.
214 unsigned PromotedSize = Ctx.getTypeSize(Op.E->getType());
215 return (2 * Ctx.getTypeSize(LHSTy)) < PromotedSize ||
216 (2 * Ctx.getTypeSize(RHSTy)) < PromotedSize;
217}
218
219/// Update the FastMathFlags of LLVM IR from the FPOptions in LangOptions.
220static void updateFastMathFlags(llvm::FastMathFlags &FMF,
221 FPOptions FPFeatures) {
222 FMF.setAllowContract(FPFeatures.allowFPContractAcrossStatement());
223}
224
225/// Propagate fast-math flags from \p Op to the instruction in \p V.
226static Value *propagateFMFlags(Value *V, const BinOpInfo &Op) {
227 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<llvm::Instruction>(V)) {
228 llvm::FastMathFlags FMF = I->getFastMathFlags();
229 updateFastMathFlags(FMF, Op.FPFeatures);
230 I->setFastMathFlags(FMF);
231 }
232 return V;
233}

271 void EmitLValueAlignmentAssumption(const Expr *E, Value *V) {
272 const AlignValueAttr *AVAttr = nullptr;
273 if (const auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
274 const ValueDecl *VD = DRE->getDecl();
275
276 if (VD->getType()->isReferenceType()) {
277 if (const auto *TTy =
278 dyn_cast<TypedefType>(VD->getType().getNonReferenceType()))
279 AVAttr = TTy->getDecl()->getAttr<AlignValueAttr>();
280 } else {
281 // Assumptions for function parameters are emitted at the start of the
282 // function, so there is no need to repeat that here,
283 // unless the alignment-assumption sanitizer is enabled,
284 // then we prefer the assumption over alignment attribute
285 // on IR function param.
286 if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(VD) && !CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Alignment))
287 return;
288
289 AVAttr = VD->getAttr<AlignValueAttr>();
290 }
291 }
292
293 if (!AVAttr)
294 if (const auto *TTy =
295 dyn_cast<TypedefType>(E->getType()))
296 AVAttr = TTy->getDecl()->getAttr<AlignValueAttr>();
297
298 if (!AVAttr)
299 return;
300
301 Value *AlignmentValue = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(AVAttr->getAlignment());
302 llvm::ConstantInt *AlignmentCI = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(AlignmentValue);
303 CGF.EmitAlignmentAssumption(V, E, AVAttr->getLocation(),
304 AlignmentCI->getZExtValue());
305 }

307 /// EmitLoadOfLValue - Given an expression with complex type that represents a
308 /// value l-value, this method emits the address of the l-value, then loads
309 /// and returns the result.
310 Value *EmitLoadOfLValue(const Expr *E) {
311 Value *V = EmitLoadOfLValue(EmitCheckedLValue(E, CodeGenFunction::TCK_Load),
312 E->getExprLoc());
313
314 EmitLValueAlignmentAssumption(E, V);
315 return V;
316 }

349 /// Emit a conversion from the specified type to the specified destination
350 /// type, both of which are LLVM scalar types.
351 struct ScalarConversionOpts {
352 bool TreatBooleanAsSigned;
353 bool EmitImplicitIntegerTruncationChecks;
354 bool EmitImplicitIntegerSignChangeChecks;
355
356 ScalarConversionOpts()
357 : TreatBooleanAsSigned(false),
358 EmitImplicitIntegerTruncationChecks(false),
359 EmitImplicitIntegerSignChangeChecks(false) {}
360
361 ScalarConversionOpts(clang::SanitizerSet SanOpts)
362 : TreatBooleanAsSigned(false),
363 EmitImplicitIntegerTruncationChecks(
364 SanOpts.hasOneOf(SanitizerKind::ImplicitIntegerTruncation)),
365 EmitImplicitIntegerSignChangeChecks(
366 SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ImplicitIntegerSignChange)) {}
367 };
368 Value *
369 EmitScalarConversion(Value *Src, QualType SrcTy, QualType DstTy,
370 SourceLocation Loc,
371 ScalarConversionOpts Opts = ScalarConversionOpts());
372
373 /// Convert between either a fixed point and other fixed point or fixed point
374 /// and an integer.
375 Value *EmitFixedPointConversion(Value *Src, QualType SrcTy, QualType DstTy,
376 SourceLocation Loc);
377 Value *EmitFixedPointConversion(Value *Src, FixedPointSemantics &SrcFixedSema,
378 FixedPointSemantics &DstFixedSema,
379 SourceLocation Loc,
380 bool DstIsInteger = false);

382 /// Emit a conversion from the specified complex type to the specified
383 /// destination type, where the destination type is an LLVM scalar type.
384 Value *EmitComplexToScalarConversion(CodeGenFunction::ComplexPairTy Src,
385 QualType SrcTy, QualType DstTy,
386 SourceLocation Loc);
387
388 /// EmitNullValue - Emit a value that corresponds to null for the given type.
389 Value *EmitNullValue(QualType Ty);
390
391 /// EmitFloatToBoolConversion - Perform an FP to boolean conversion.
392 Value *EmitFloatToBoolConversion(Value *V) {
393 // Compare against 0.0 for fp scalars.
394 llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(V->getType());
395 return Builder.CreateFCmpUNE(V, Zero, "tobool");
396 }
397
398 /// EmitPointerToBoolConversion - Perform a pointer to boolean conversion.
399 Value *EmitPointerToBoolConversion(Value *V, QualType QT) {
400 Value *Zero = CGF.CGM.getNullPointer(cast<llvm::PointerType>(V->getType()), QT);
401
402 return Builder.CreateICmpNE(V, Zero, "tobool");
403 }
404
405 Value *EmitIntToBoolConversion(Value *V) {
406 // Because of the type rules of C, we often end up computing a
407 // logical value, then zero extending it to int, then wanting it
408 // as a logical value again. Optimize this common case.
409 if (llvm::ZExtInst *ZI = dyn_cast<llvm::ZExtInst>(V)) {
410 if (ZI->getOperand(0)->getType() == Builder.getInt1Ty()) {
411 Value *Result = ZI->getOperand(0);
412 // If there aren't any more uses, zap the instruction to save space.
413 // Note that there can be more uses, for example if this
414 // is the result of an assignment.
415 if (ZI->use_empty())
416 ZI->eraseFromParent();
417 return Result;
418 }
419 }
420
421 return Builder.CreateIsNotNull(V, "tobool");
422 }

461 // Leaves.
462 Value *VisitIntegerLiteral(const IntegerLiteral *E) {
463 if (E->getType()->isIntCapType()) {
464 // FIXME: diagnose > 64 bit constants
465 auto Value = E->getValue();
466 assert(Value.getBitWidth() == CGF.getTarget().getPointerRangeForCHERICapability());
467 // assert(E->getValue().getBitWidth() <= 64);
468 return CGF.setCapabilityIntegerValue(
469 llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(CGF.Int8CheriCapTy),
470 Builder.getInt(Value));
471 }
472 return Builder.getInt(E->getValue());
473 }

554 Value *VisitObjCAvailabilityCheckExpr(ObjCAvailabilityCheckExpr *E) {
555 VersionTuple Version = E->getVersion();
556
557 // If we're checking for a platform older than our minimum deployment
558 // target, we can fold the check away.
559 if (Version <= CGF.CGM.getTarget().getPlatformMinVersion())
560 return llvm::ConstantInt::get(Builder.getInt1Ty(), 1);
561
562 Optional<unsigned> Min = Version.getMinor(), SMin = Version.getSubminor();
563 llvm::Value *Args[] = {
564 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.CGM.Int32Ty, Version.getMajor()),
565 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.CGM.Int32Ty, Min ? *Min : 0),
566 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.CGM.Int32Ty, SMin ? *SMin : 0),
567 };
568
569 return CGF.EmitBuiltinAvailable(Args);
570 }

743 // Binary Operators.
744 Value *EmitMul(const BinOpInfo &Ops) {
745 if (Ops.Ty->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType()) {
746 switch (CGF.getLangOpts().getSignedOverflowBehavior()) {
747 case LangOptions::SOB_Defined:
748 return Builder.CreateMul(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "mul");
749 case LangOptions::SOB_Undefined:
750 if (!CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow))
751 return Builder.CreateNSWMul(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "mul");
752 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
753 case LangOptions::SOB_Trapping:
754 if (CanElideOverflowCheck(CGF.getContext(), Ops))
755 return Builder.CreateNSWMul(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "mul");
756 return EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(Ops);
757 }
758 }
759
760 if (Ops.Ty->isUnsignedIntegerType() &&
761 CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow) &&
762 !CanElideOverflowCheck(CGF.getContext(), Ops))
763 return EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(Ops);
764
765 if (Ops.LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
766 Value *V = Builder.CreateFMul(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "mul");
767 return propagateFMFlags(V, Ops);
768 }
769 return Builder.CreateMul(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "mul");
770 }

777 llvm::Value *Zero,bool isDiv);
778 Value *GetBinOpVal(const BinOpInfo &Op, Value *V, QualType T) {
779 // If this isn't a capability type, do nothing. If it's not a pointer
780 // type, also do nothing - add operations are handled differently so need
781 // the second case.
782 if (!T->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.getContext()) ||
783 !V->getType()->isPointerTy())
784 return V;
785 return CGF.getCapabilityIntegerValue(V);
786 }
787 Value *GetBinOpVal(const BinOpInfo &Op, Value *V) {
788 return GetBinOpVal(Op, V, Op.E->getType());
789 }
790 Value *GetBinOpResult(const BinOpInfo &Op, Value *LHS, Value *V, QualType T) {
791 bool IsCapabilityResult = T->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.getContext());
792 // TODO: or just check LHS LLVM type?
793 if (!IsCapabilityResult)
794 return V;
795 // Bitwise-and require special handling (due to checking vs clearing low
796 // pointer bits: see https://github.com/CTSRD-CHERI/clang/issues/189
797 // Note: without data-dependent provenance patterns such as
798 // `if (uintptr_t(x) & 1 == 1)` break. This is commonly used is used to
799 // test for data stored in low pointer bits (for mutexes, etc...)
800 if (Op.Opcode == BinaryOperator::Opcode::BO_And ||
801 Op.Opcode == BinaryOperator::Opcode::BO_AndAssign) {
802 // If we are using data-dependent provenance we may need to return either
803 // a NULL-derived or LHS derived capability for bitwise-and
804 // TODO: is this also a problem for xor (should be less common so can
805 // probably ignore?)
806 if (IsCapabilityResult &&
807 CGF.getLangOpts().CheriDataDependentProvenance) {
808 // For now we derive from NULL if the value we are anding with is less
809 // than one page since such values should *almost* never be valid anyway
810 uint64_t NullDeriveLimit = 4096;
811 auto *ShouldDeriveFromNull = CGF.Builder.CreateICmpULE(
812 Op.RHS, llvm::ConstantInt::get(Op.RHS->getType(), NullDeriveLimit),
813 "bitand.should-nullderive");
814 auto CapNull = llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(
815 cast<llvm::PointerType>(LHS->getType()));
816 LHS = Builder.CreateSelect(ShouldDeriveFromNull, CapNull, LHS,
817 "bitand.provenance");
818 }
819 }
820 return CGF.setCapabilityIntegerValue(LHS, V);
821 }
822 Value *GetBinOpResult(const BinOpInfo &Op, Value *LHS, Value *V) {
823 return GetBinOpResult(Op, LHS, V, Op.E->getType());
824 }

964/// EmitConversionToBool - Convert the specified expression value to a
965/// boolean (i1) truth value. This is equivalent to "Val != 0".
966Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitConversionToBool(Value *Src, QualType SrcType) {
967 assert(SrcType.isCanonical() && "EmitScalarConversion strips typedefs");
968
969 if (SrcType->isRealFloatingType())
970 return EmitFloatToBoolConversion(Src);
971
972 if (const MemberPointerType *MPT = dyn_cast<MemberPointerType>(SrcType))
973 return CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberPointerIsNotNull(CGF, Src, MPT);
974
975 assert((SrcType->isIntegerType() || isa<llvm::PointerType>(Src->getType())) &&
976 "Unknown scalar type to convert");
977
978 if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(Src->getType()))
979 return EmitIntToBoolConversion(Src);
980
981 assert(isa<llvm::PointerType>(Src->getType()));
982 return EmitPointerToBoolConversion(Src, SrcType);
983}
984
985void ScalarExprEmitter::EmitFloatConversionCheck(
986 Value *OrigSrc, QualType OrigSrcType, Value *Src, QualType SrcType,
987 QualType DstType, llvm::Type *DstTy, SourceLocation Loc) {
988 CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
989 using llvm::APFloat;
990 using llvm::APSInt;
991
992 llvm::Type *SrcTy = Src->getType();
993
994 llvm::Value *Check = nullptr;
995 if (llvm::IntegerType *IntTy = dyn_cast<llvm::IntegerType>(SrcTy)) {
996 // Integer to floating-point. This can fail for unsigned short -> __half
997 // or unsigned __int128 -> float.
998 assert(DstType->isFloatingType());
999 bool SrcIsUnsigned = OrigSrcType->isUnsignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1000
1001 APFloat LargestFloat =
1002 APFloat::getLargest(CGF.getContext().getFloatTypeSemantics(DstType));
1003 APSInt LargestInt(IntTy->getBitWidth(), SrcIsUnsigned);
1004
1005 bool IsExact;
1006 if (LargestFloat.convertToInteger(LargestInt, APFloat::rmTowardZero,
1007 &IsExact) != APFloat::opOK)
1008 // The range of representable values of this floating point type includes
1009 // all values of this integer type. Don't need an overflow check.
1010 return;
1011
1012 llvm::Value *Max = llvm::ConstantInt::get(VMContext, LargestInt);
1013 if (SrcIsUnsigned)
1014 Check = Builder.CreateICmpULE(Src, Max);
1015 else {
1016 llvm::Value *Min = llvm::ConstantInt::get(VMContext, -LargestInt);
1017 llvm::Value *GE = Builder.CreateICmpSGE(Src, Min);
1018 llvm::Value *LE = Builder.CreateICmpSLE(Src, Max);
1019 Check = Builder.CreateAnd(GE, LE);
1020 }
1021 } else {
1022 const llvm::fltSemantics &SrcSema =
1023 CGF.getContext().getFloatTypeSemantics(OrigSrcType);
1024 if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(DstTy)) {
1025 // Floating-point to integer. This has undefined behavior if the source is
1026 // +-Inf, NaN, or doesn't fit into the destination type (after truncation
1027 // to an integer).
1028 unsigned Width = CGF.getContext().getIntWidth(DstType);
1029 bool Unsigned = DstType->isUnsignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1030
1031 APSInt Min = APSInt::getMinValue(Width, Unsigned);
1032 APFloat MinSrc(SrcSema, APFloat::uninitialized);
1033 if (MinSrc.convertFromAPInt(Min, !Unsigned, APFloat::rmTowardZero) &
1034 APFloat::opOverflow)
1035 // Don't need an overflow check for lower bound. Just check for
1036 // -Inf/NaN.
1037 MinSrc = APFloat::getInf(SrcSema, true);
1038 else
1039 // Find the largest value which is too small to represent (before
1040 // truncation toward zero).
1041 MinSrc.subtract(APFloat(SrcSema, 1), APFloat::rmTowardNegative);
1042
1043 APSInt Max = APSInt::getMaxValue(Width, Unsigned);
1044 APFloat MaxSrc(SrcSema, APFloat::uninitialized);
1045 if (MaxSrc.convertFromAPInt(Max, !Unsigned, APFloat::rmTowardZero) &
1046 APFloat::opOverflow)
1047 // Don't need an overflow check for upper bound. Just check for
1048 // +Inf/NaN.
1049 MaxSrc = APFloat::getInf(SrcSema, false);
1050 else
1051 // Find the smallest value which is too large to represent (before
1052 // truncation toward zero).
1053 MaxSrc.add(APFloat(SrcSema, 1), APFloat::rmTowardPositive);
1054
1055 // If we're converting from __half, convert the range to float to match
1056 // the type of src.
1057 if (OrigSrcType->isHalfType()) {
1058 const llvm::fltSemantics &Sema =
1059 CGF.getContext().getFloatTypeSemantics(SrcType);
1060 bool IsInexact;
1061 MinSrc.convert(Sema, APFloat::rmTowardZero, &IsInexact);
1062 MaxSrc.convert(Sema, APFloat::rmTowardZero, &IsInexact);
1063 }
1064
1065 llvm::Value *GE =
1066 Builder.CreateFCmpOGT(Src, llvm::ConstantFP::get(VMContext, MinSrc));
1067 llvm::Value *LE =
1068 Builder.CreateFCmpOLT(Src, llvm::ConstantFP::get(VMContext, MaxSrc));
1069 Check = Builder.CreateAnd(GE, LE);
1070 } else {
1071 // FIXME: Maybe split this sanitizer out from float-cast-overflow.
1072 //
1073 // Floating-point to floating-point. This has undefined behavior if the
1074 // source is not in the range of representable values of the destination
1075 // type. The C and C++ standards are spectacularly unclear here. We
1076 // diagnose finite out-of-range conversions, but allow infinities and NaNs
1077 // to convert to the corresponding value in the smaller type.
1078 //
1079 // C11 Annex F gives all such conversions defined behavior for IEC 60559
1080 // conforming implementations. Unfortunately, LLVM's fptrunc instruction
1081 // does not.
1082
1083 // Converting from a lower rank to a higher rank can never have
1084 // undefined behavior, since higher-rank types must have a superset
1085 // of values of lower-rank types.
1086 if (CGF.getContext().getFloatingTypeOrder(OrigSrcType, DstType) != 1)
1087 return;
1088
1089 assert(!OrigSrcType->isHalfType() &&
1090 "should not check conversion from __half, it has the lowest rank");
1091
1092 const llvm::fltSemantics &DstSema =
1093 CGF.getContext().getFloatTypeSemantics(DstType);
1094 APFloat MinBad = APFloat::getLargest(DstSema, false);
1095 APFloat MaxBad = APFloat::getInf(DstSema, false);
1096
1097 bool IsInexact;
1098 MinBad.convert(SrcSema, APFloat::rmTowardZero, &IsInexact);
1099 MaxBad.convert(SrcSema, APFloat::rmTowardZero, &IsInexact);
1100
1101 Value *AbsSrc = CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(
1102 CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::fabs, Src->getType()), Src);
1103 llvm::Value *GE =
1104 Builder.CreateFCmpOGT(AbsSrc, llvm::ConstantFP::get(VMContext, MinBad));
1105 llvm::Value *LE =
1106 Builder.CreateFCmpOLT(AbsSrc, llvm::ConstantFP::get(VMContext, MaxBad));
1107 Check = Builder.CreateNot(Builder.CreateAnd(GE, LE));
1108 }
1109 }
1110
1111 llvm::Constant *StaticArgs[] = {CGF.EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc),
1112 CGF.EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(OrigSrcType),
1113 CGF.EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(DstType)};
1114 CGF.EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Check, SanitizerKind::FloatCastOverflow),
1115 SanitizerHandler::FloatCastOverflow, StaticArgs, OrigSrc);
1116}
1117
1118// Should be called within CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope RAII scope.
1119// Returns 'i1 false' when the truncation Src -> Dst was lossy.
1120static std::pair<ScalarExprEmitter::ImplicitConversionCheckKind,
1121 std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>>
1122EmitIntegerTruncationCheckHelper(Value *Src, QualType SrcType, Value *Dst,
1123 QualType DstType, CGBuilderTy &Builder) {
1124 llvm::Type *SrcTy = Src->getType();
1125 llvm::Type *DstTy = Dst->getType();
1126 (void)DstTy; // Only used in assert()
1127
1128 // This should be truncation of integral types.
1129 assert(Src != Dst);
1130 assert(SrcTy->getScalarSizeInBits() > Dst->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits());
1131 assert(isa<llvm::IntegerType>(SrcTy) && isa<llvm::IntegerType>(DstTy) &&
1132 "non-integer llvm type");
1133
1134 bool SrcSigned = SrcType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1135 bool DstSigned = DstType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1136
1137 // If both (src and dst) types are unsigned, then it's an unsigned truncation.
1138 // Else, it is a signed truncation.
1139 ScalarExprEmitter::ImplicitConversionCheckKind Kind;
1140 SanitizerMask Mask;
1141 if (!SrcSigned && !DstSigned) {
1142 Kind = ScalarExprEmitter::ICCK_UnsignedIntegerTruncation;
1143 Mask = SanitizerKind::ImplicitUnsignedIntegerTruncation;
1144 } else {
1145 Kind = ScalarExprEmitter::ICCK_SignedIntegerTruncation;
1146 Mask = SanitizerKind::ImplicitSignedIntegerTruncation;
1147 }
1148
1149 llvm::Value *Check = nullptr;
1150 // 1. Extend the truncated value back to the same width as the Src.
1151 Check = Builder.CreateIntCast(Dst, SrcTy, DstSigned, "anyext");
1152 // 2. Equality-compare with the original source value
1153 Check = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(Check, Src, "truncheck");
1154 // If the comparison result is 'i1 false', then the truncation was lossy.
1155 return std::make_pair(Kind, std::make_pair(Check, Mask));
1156}
1157
1158void ScalarExprEmitter::EmitIntegerTruncationCheck(Value *Src, QualType SrcType,
1159 Value *Dst, QualType DstType,
1160 SourceLocation Loc) {
1161 if (!CGF.SanOpts.hasOneOf(SanitizerKind::ImplicitIntegerTruncation))
1162 return;
1163
1164 // We only care about int->int conversions here.
1165 // We ignore conversions to/from pointer and/or bool.
1166 if (!(SrcType->isIntegerType() && DstType->isIntegerType()))
1167 return;
1168
1169 unsigned SrcBits = Src->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
1170 unsigned DstBits = Dst->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
1171 // This must be truncation. Else we do not care.
1172 if (SrcBits <= DstBits)
1173 return;
1174
1175 assert(!DstType->isBooleanType() && "we should not get here with booleans.");
1176
1177 // If the integer sign change sanitizer is enabled,
1178 // and we are truncating from larger unsigned type to smaller signed type,
1179 // let that next sanitizer deal with it.
1180 bool SrcSigned = SrcType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1181 bool DstSigned = DstType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1182 if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ImplicitIntegerSignChange) &&
1183 (!SrcSigned && DstSigned))
1184 return;
1185
1186 CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
1187
1188 std::pair<ScalarExprEmitter::ImplicitConversionCheckKind,
1189 std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>>
1190 Check =
1191 EmitIntegerTruncationCheckHelper(Src, SrcType, Dst, DstType, Builder);
1192 // If the comparison result is 'i1 false', then the truncation was lossy.
1193
1194 // Do we care about this type of truncation?
1195 if (!CGF.SanOpts.has(Check.second.second))
1196 return;
1197
1198 llvm::Constant *StaticArgs[] = {
1199 CGF.EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc), CGF.EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(SrcType),
1200 CGF.EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(DstType),
1201 llvm::ConstantInt::get(Builder.getInt8Ty(), Check.first)};
1202 CGF.EmitCheck(Check.second, SanitizerHandler::ImplicitConversion, StaticArgs,
1203 {Src, Dst});
1204}
1205
1206// Should be called within CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope RAII scope.
1207// Returns 'i1 false' when the conversion Src -> Dst changed the sign.
1208static std::pair<ScalarExprEmitter::ImplicitConversionCheckKind,
1209 std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>>
1210EmitIntegerSignChangeCheckHelper(Value *Src, QualType SrcType, Value *Dst,
1211 QualType DstType, CGBuilderTy &Builder) {
1212 llvm::Type *SrcTy = Src->getType();
1213 llvm::Type *DstTy = Dst->getType();
1214
1215 assert(isa<llvm::IntegerType>(SrcTy) && isa<llvm::IntegerType>(DstTy) &&
1216 "non-integer llvm type");
1217
1218 bool SrcSigned = SrcType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1219 bool DstSigned = DstType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1220 (void)SrcSigned; // Only used in assert()
1221 (void)DstSigned; // Only used in assert()
1222 unsigned SrcBits = SrcTy->getScalarSizeInBits();
1223 unsigned DstBits = DstTy->getScalarSizeInBits();
1224 (void)SrcBits; // Only used in assert()
1225 (void)DstBits; // Only used in assert()
1226
1227 assert(((SrcBits != DstBits) || (SrcSigned != DstSigned)) &&
1228 "either the widths should be different, or the signednesses.");
1229
1230 // NOTE: zero value is considered to be non-negative.
1231 auto EmitIsNegativeTest = [&Builder](Value *V, QualType VType,
1232 const char *Name) -> Value * {
1233 // Is this value a signed type?
1234 bool VSigned = VType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1235 llvm::Type *VTy = V->getType();
1236 if (!VSigned) {
1237 // If the value is unsigned, then it is never negative.
1238 // FIXME: can we encounter non-scalar VTy here?
1239 return llvm::ConstantInt::getFalse(VTy->getContext());
1240 }
1241 // Get the zero of the same type with which we will be comparing.
1242 llvm::Constant *Zero = llvm::ConstantInt::get(VTy, 0);
1243 // %V.isnegative = icmp slt %V, 0
1244 // I.e is %V *strictly* less than zero, does it have negative value?
1245 return Builder.CreateICmp(llvm::ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT, V, Zero,
1246 llvm::Twine(Name) + "." + V->getName() +
1247 ".negativitycheck");
1248 };
1249
1250 // 1. Was the old Value negative?
1251 llvm::Value *SrcIsNegative = EmitIsNegativeTest(Src, SrcType, "src");
1252 // 2. Is the new Value negative?
1253 llvm::Value *DstIsNegative = EmitIsNegativeTest(Dst, DstType, "dst");
1254 // 3. Now, was the 'negativity status' preserved during the conversion?
1255 // NOTE: conversion from negative to zero is considered to change the sign.
1256 // (We want to get 'false' when the conversion changed the sign)
1257 // So we should just equality-compare the negativity statuses.
1258 llvm::Value *Check = nullptr;
1259 Check = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(SrcIsNegative, DstIsNegative, "signchangecheck");
1260 // If the comparison result is 'false', then the conversion changed the sign.
1261 return std::make_pair(
1262 ScalarExprEmitter::ICCK_IntegerSignChange,
1263 std::make_pair(Check, SanitizerKind::ImplicitIntegerSignChange));
1264}
1265
1266void ScalarExprEmitter::EmitIntegerSignChangeCheck(Value *Src, QualType SrcType,
1267 Value *Dst, QualType DstType,
1268 SourceLocation Loc) {
1269 if (!CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ImplicitIntegerSignChange))
1270 return;
1271
1272 llvm::Type *SrcTy = Src->getType();
1273 llvm::Type *DstTy = Dst->getType();
1274
1275 // We only care about int->int conversions here.
1276 // We ignore conversions to/from pointer and/or bool.
1277 if (!(SrcType->isIntegerType() && DstType->isIntegerType()))
1278 return;
1279
1280 bool SrcSigned = SrcType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1281 bool DstSigned = DstType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1282 unsigned SrcBits = SrcTy->getScalarSizeInBits();
1283 unsigned DstBits = DstTy->getScalarSizeInBits();
1284
1285 // Now, we do not need to emit the check in *all* of the cases.
1286 // We can avoid emitting it in some obvious cases where it would have been
1287 // dropped by the opt passes (instcombine) always anyways.
1288 // If it's a cast between effectively the same type, no check.
1289 // NOTE: this is *not* equivalent to checking the canonical types.
1290 if (SrcSigned == DstSigned && SrcBits == DstBits)
1291 return;
1292 // At least one of the values needs to have signed type.
1293 // If both are unsigned, then obviously, neither of them can be negative.
1294 if (!SrcSigned && !DstSigned)
1295 return;
1296 // If the conversion is to *larger* *signed* type, then no check is needed.
1297 // Because either sign-extension happens (so the sign will remain),
1298 // or zero-extension will happen (the sign bit will be zero.)
1299 if ((DstBits > SrcBits) && DstSigned)
1300 return;
1301 if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ImplicitSignedIntegerTruncation) &&
1302 (SrcBits > DstBits) && SrcSigned) {
1303 // If the signed integer truncation sanitizer is enabled,
1304 // and this is a truncation from signed type, then no check is needed.
1305 // Because here sign change check is interchangeable with truncation check.
1306 return;
1307 }
1308 // That's it. We can't rule out any more cases with the data we have.
1309
1310 CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
1311
1312 std::pair<ScalarExprEmitter::ImplicitConversionCheckKind,
1313 std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>>
1314 Check;
1315
1316 // Each of these checks needs to return 'false' when an issue was detected.
1317 ImplicitConversionCheckKind CheckKind;
1318 llvm::SmallVector<std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>, 2> Checks;
1319 // So we can 'and' all the checks together, and still get 'false',
1320 // if at least one of the checks detected an issue.
1321
1322 Check = EmitIntegerSignChangeCheckHelper(Src, SrcType, Dst, DstType, Builder);
1323 CheckKind = Check.first;
1324 Checks.emplace_back(Check.second);
1325
1326 if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ImplicitSignedIntegerTruncation) &&
1327 (SrcBits > DstBits) && !SrcSigned && DstSigned) {
1328 // If the signed integer truncation sanitizer was enabled,
1329 // and we are truncating from larger unsigned type to smaller signed type,
1330 // let's handle the case we skipped in that check.
1331 Check =
1332 EmitIntegerTruncationCheckHelper(Src, SrcType, Dst, DstType, Builder);
1333 CheckKind = ICCK_SignedIntegerTruncationOrSignChange;
1334 Checks.emplace_back(Check.second);
1335 // If the comparison result is 'i1 false', then the truncation was lossy.
1336 }
1337
1338 llvm::Constant *StaticArgs[] = {
1339 CGF.EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc), CGF.EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(SrcType),
1340 CGF.EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(DstType),
1341 llvm::ConstantInt::get(Builder.getInt8Ty(), CheckKind)};
1342 // EmitCheck() will 'and' all the checks together.
1343 CGF.EmitCheck(Checks, SanitizerHandler::ImplicitConversion, StaticArgs,
1344 {Src, Dst});
1345}
1346
1347/// Emit a conversion from the specified type to the specified destination type,
1348/// both of which are LLVM scalar types.
1349Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitScalarConversion(Value *Src, QualType SrcType,
1350 QualType DstType,
1351 SourceLocation Loc,
1352 ScalarConversionOpts Opts) {
1353 // All conversions involving fixed point types should be handled by the
1354 // EmitFixedPoint family functions. This is done to prevent bloating up this
1355 // function more, and although fixed point numbers are represented by
1356 // integers, we do not want to follow any logic that assumes they should be
1357 // treated as integers.
1358 // TODO(leonardchan): When necessary, add another if statement checking for
1359 // conversions to fixed point types from other types.
1360 if (SrcType->isFixedPointType()) {
1361 if (DstType->isBooleanType())
1362 // It is important that we check this before checking if the dest type is
1363 // an integer because booleans are technically integer types.
1364 // We do not need to check the padding bit on unsigned types if unsigned
1365 // padding is enabled because overflow into this bit is undefined
1366 // behavior.
1367 return Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Src, "tobool");
1368 if (DstType->isFixedPointType() || DstType->isIntegerType())
1369 return EmitFixedPointConversion(Src, SrcType, DstType, Loc);
1370
1371 llvm_unreachable(
1372 "Unhandled scalar conversion from a fixed point type to another type.");
1373 } else if (DstType->isFixedPointType()) {
1374 if (SrcType->isIntegerType())
1375 // This also includes converting booleans and enums to fixed point types.
1376 return EmitFixedPointConversion(Src, SrcType, DstType, Loc);
1377
1378 llvm_unreachable(
1379 "Unhandled scalar conversion to a fixed point type from another type.");
1380 }
1381
1382 QualType NoncanonicalSrcType = SrcType;
1383 QualType NoncanonicalDstType = DstType;
1384
1385 SrcType = CGF.getContext().getCanonicalType(SrcType);
1386 DstType = CGF.getContext().getCanonicalType(DstType);
1387 if (SrcType == DstType) return Src;
1388
1389 if (DstType->isVoidType()) return nullptr;
1390
1391 llvm::Value *OrigSrc = Src;
1392 QualType OrigSrcType = SrcType;
1393 llvm::Type *SrcTy = Src->getType();
1394
1395 // Handle conversions to bool first, they are special: comparisons against 0.
1396 if (DstType->isBooleanType())
1397 return EmitConversionToBool(Src, SrcType);
1398
1399 llvm::Type *DstTy = ConvertType(DstType);
1400
1401 // Cast from half through float if half isn't a native type.
1402 if (SrcType->isHalfType() && !CGF.getContext().getLangOpts().NativeHalfType) {
1403 // Cast to FP using the intrinsic if the half type itself isn't supported.
1404 if (DstTy->isFloatingPointTy()) {
1405 if (CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo().useFP16ConversionIntrinsics())
1406 return Builder.CreateCall(
1407 CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::convert_from_fp16, DstTy),
1408 Src);
1409 } else {
1410 // Cast to other types through float, using either the intrinsic or FPExt,
1411 // depending on whether the half type itself is supported
1412 // (as opposed to operations on half, available with NativeHalfType).
1413 if (CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo().useFP16ConversionIntrinsics()) {
1414 Src = Builder.CreateCall(
1415 CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::convert_from_fp16,
1416 CGF.CGM.FloatTy),
1417 Src);
1418 } else {
1419 Src = Builder.CreateFPExt(Src, CGF.CGM.FloatTy, "conv");
1420 }
1421 SrcType = CGF.getContext().FloatTy;
1422 SrcTy = CGF.FloatTy;
1423 }
1424 }
1425
1426 // Ignore conversions like int -> uint.
1427 if (SrcTy == DstTy) {
1428 if (Opts.EmitImplicitIntegerSignChangeChecks)
1429 EmitIntegerSignChangeCheck(Src, NoncanonicalSrcType, Src,
1430 NoncanonicalDstType, Loc);
1431
1432 return Src;
1433 }
1434
1435 // Handle pointer conversions next: pointers can only be converted to/from
1436 // other pointers and integers. Check for pointer types in terms of LLVM, as
1437 // some native types (like Obj-C id) may map to a pointer type.
1438 if (auto DstPT = dyn_cast<llvm::PointerType>(DstTy)) {
1439 // The source value may be an integer, or a pointer.
1440 if (isa<llvm::PointerType>(SrcTy))
1441 return Builder.CreateBitCast(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1442
1443 // Allow conversions from floating point types -> (u)intcap
1444 if (SrcType->isFloatingType()) {
1445 assert((DstType->isIntCapType()) &&
1446 "Float->cap conversions should only be possible with (u)intcap");
1447 unsigned BitWidth =
1448 CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo().getPointerRangeForCHERICapability();
1449 bool Signed = DstType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1450 QualType ConvertedType =
1451 CGF.getContext().getIntTypeForBitwidth(BitWidth, Signed);
1452 Src = EmitScalarConversion(Src, SrcType, ConvertedType, Loc, Opts);
1453 SrcType = ConvertedType;
1454 }
1455 assert(SrcType->isIntegerType() && "Not ptr->ptr or int->ptr conversion?");
1456
1457 if (DstType->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.getContext())) {
1458 Value *Null = llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(DstPT);
1459 if (SrcType->isBooleanType() && !Opts.TreatBooleanAsSigned)
1460 Src = Builder.CreateZExtOrTrunc(Src, CGF.IntPtrTy);
1461 else
1462 Src = Builder.CreateSExtOrTrunc(Src, CGF.IntPtrTy);
1463 return CGF.setCapabilityIntegerValue(Null, Src);
1464 }
1465 // First, convert to the correct width so that we control the kind of
1466 // extension.
1467 llvm::Type *MiddleTy = CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().getIntPtrType(DstPT);
1468 bool InputSigned = SrcType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1469 assert(!SrcType->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.getContext()));
1470 llvm::Value* IntResult =
1471 Builder.CreateIntCast(Src, MiddleTy, InputSigned, "conv");
1472 // Then, cast to pointer.
1473 return Builder.CreateIntToPtr(IntResult, DstTy, "conv");
1474 }
1475
1476 if (isa<llvm::PointerType>(SrcTy)) {
1477 if (!SrcType->isPointerType()) {
1478 // If this is not a pointer type in C, but is in LLVM IR, then it must be
1479 // a [u]intcap_t or enum type whose underlying integer type is [u]intcap_t
1480 assert(SrcType->isIntCapType());
1481 Src = CGF.getCapabilityIntegerValue(Src);
1482 // Conversions from (u)intcap -> float should not be a bitcast:
1483 if (DstType->isFloatingType()) {
1484 if (SrcType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType()) {
1485 return Builder.CreateSIToFP(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1486 } else {
1487 assert(SrcType->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::UIntCap) ||
1488 SrcType->isUnsignedIntegerOrEnumerationType());
1489 return Builder.CreateUIToFP(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1490 }
1491 }
1492 return Builder.CreateIntCast(Src, DstTy,
1493 SrcType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType(), "conv");
1494 }
1495 // Must be an ptr to int cast.
1496 assert(isa<llvm::IntegerType>(DstTy) && "not ptr->int?");
1497 return Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1498 }
1499
1500 // A scalar can be splatted to an extended vector of the same element type
1501 if (DstType->isExtVectorType() && !SrcType->isVectorType()) {
1502 // Sema should add casts to make sure that the source expression's type is
1503 // the same as the vector's element type (sans qualifiers)
1504 assert(DstType->castAs<ExtVectorType>()->getElementType().getTypePtr() ==
1505 SrcType.getTypePtr() &&
1506 "Splatted expr doesn't match with vector element type?");
1507
1508 // Splat the element across to all elements
1509 unsigned NumElements = DstTy->getVectorNumElements();
1510 return Builder.CreateVectorSplat(NumElements, Src, "splat");
1511 }
1512
1513 if (isa<llvm::VectorType>(SrcTy) || isa<llvm::VectorType>(DstTy)) {
1514 // Allow bitcast from vector to integer/fp of the same size.
1515 unsigned SrcSize = SrcTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
1516 unsigned DstSize = DstTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
1517 if (SrcSize == DstSize)
1518 return Builder.CreateBitCast(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1519
1520 // Conversions between vectors of different sizes are not allowed except
1521 // when vectors of half are involved. Operations on storage-only half
1522 // vectors require promoting half vector operands to float vectors and
1523 // truncating the result, which is either an int or float vector, to a
1524 // short or half vector.
1525
1526 // Source and destination are both expected to be vectors.
1527 llvm::Type *SrcElementTy = SrcTy->getVectorElementType();
1528 llvm::Type *DstElementTy = DstTy->getVectorElementType();
1529 (void)DstElementTy;
1530
1531 assert(((SrcElementTy->isIntegerTy() &&
1532 DstElementTy->isIntegerTy()) ||
1533 (SrcElementTy->isFloatingPointTy() &&
1534 DstElementTy->isFloatingPointTy())) &&
1535 "unexpected conversion between a floating-point vector and an "
1536 "integer vector");
1537
1538 // Truncate an i32 vector to an i16 vector.
1539 if (SrcElementTy->isIntegerTy())
1540 return Builder.CreateIntCast(Src, DstTy, false, "conv");
1541
1542 // Truncate a float vector to a half vector.
1543 if (SrcSize > DstSize)
1544 return Builder.CreateFPTrunc(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1545
1546 // Promote a half vector to a float vector.
1547 return Builder.CreateFPExt(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1548 }
1549
1550 // Finally, we have the arithmetic types: real int/float.
1551 Value *Res = nullptr;
1552 llvm::Type *ResTy = DstTy;
1553
1554 // An overflowing conversion has undefined behavior if either the source type
1555 // or the destination type is a floating-point type.
1556 if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::FloatCastOverflow) &&
1557 (OrigSrcType->isFloatingType() || DstType->isFloatingType()))
1558 EmitFloatConversionCheck(OrigSrc, OrigSrcType, Src, SrcType, DstType, DstTy,
1559 Loc);
1560
1561 // Cast to half through float if half isn't a native type.
1562 if (DstType->isHalfType() && !CGF.getContext().getLangOpts().NativeHalfType) {
1563 // Make sure we cast in a single step if from another FP type.
1564 if (SrcTy->isFloatingPointTy()) {
1565 // Use the intrinsic if the half type itself isn't supported
1566 // (as opposed to operations on half, available with NativeHalfType).
1567 if (CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo().useFP16ConversionIntrinsics())
1568 return Builder.CreateCall(
1569 CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::convert_to_fp16, SrcTy), Src);
1570 // If the half type is supported, just use an fptrunc.
1571 return Builder.CreateFPTrunc(Src, DstTy);
1572 }
1573 DstTy = CGF.FloatTy;
1574 }
1575
1576 if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(SrcTy)) {
1577 bool InputSigned = SrcType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1578 if (SrcType->isBooleanType() && Opts.TreatBooleanAsSigned) {
1579 InputSigned = true;
1580 }
1581 if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(DstTy))
1582 Res = Builder.CreateIntCast(Src, DstTy, InputSigned, "conv");
1583 else if (InputSigned)
1584 Res = Builder.CreateSIToFP(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1585 else
1586 Res = Builder.CreateUIToFP(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1587 } else if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(DstTy)) {
1588 assert(SrcTy->isFloatingPointTy() && "Unknown real conversion");
1589 if (DstType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType())
1590 Res = Builder.CreateFPToSI(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1591 else
1592 Res = Builder.CreateFPToUI(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1593 } else {
1594 assert(SrcTy->isFloatingPointTy() && DstTy->isFloatingPointTy() &&
1595 "Unknown real conversion");
1596 if (DstTy->getTypeID() < SrcTy->getTypeID())
1597 Res = Builder.CreateFPTrunc(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1598 else
1599 Res = Builder.CreateFPExt(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1600 }
1601
1602 if (DstTy != ResTy) {
1603 if (CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo().useFP16ConversionIntrinsics()) {
1604 assert(ResTy->isIntegerTy(16) && "Only half FP requires extra conversion");
1605 Res = Builder.CreateCall(
1606 CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::convert_to_fp16, CGF.CGM.FloatTy),
1607 Res);
1608 } else {
1609 Res = Builder.CreateFPTrunc(Res, ResTy, "conv");
1610 }
1611 }
1612
1613 if (Opts.EmitImplicitIntegerTruncationChecks)
1614 EmitIntegerTruncationCheck(Src, NoncanonicalSrcType, Res,
1615 NoncanonicalDstType, Loc);
1616
1617 if (Opts.EmitImplicitIntegerSignChangeChecks)
1618 EmitIntegerSignChangeCheck(Src, NoncanonicalSrcType, Res,
1619 NoncanonicalDstType, Loc);
1620
1621 return Res;
1622}
1623
1624Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitFixedPointConversion(Value *Src, QualType SrcTy,
1625 QualType DstTy,
1626 SourceLocation Loc) {
1627 FixedPointSemantics SrcFPSema =
1628 CGF.getContext().getFixedPointSemantics(SrcTy);
1629 FixedPointSemantics DstFPSema =
1630 CGF.getContext().getFixedPointSemantics(DstTy);
1631 return EmitFixedPointConversion(Src, SrcFPSema, DstFPSema, Loc,
1632 DstTy->isIntegerType());
1633}
1634
1635Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitFixedPointConversion(
1636 Value *Src, FixedPointSemantics &SrcFPSema, FixedPointSemantics &DstFPSema,
1637 SourceLocation Loc, bool DstIsInteger) {
1638 using llvm::APInt;
1639 using llvm::ConstantInt;
1640 using llvm::Value;
1641
1642 unsigned SrcWidth = SrcFPSema.getWidth();
1643 unsigned DstWidth = DstFPSema.getWidth();
1644 unsigned SrcScale = SrcFPSema.getScale();
1645 unsigned DstScale = DstFPSema.getScale();
1646 bool SrcIsSigned = SrcFPSema.isSigned();
1647 bool DstIsSigned = DstFPSema.isSigned();
1648
1649 llvm::Type *DstIntTy = Builder.getIntNTy(DstWidth);
1650
1651 Value *Result = Src;
1652 unsigned ResultWidth = SrcWidth;
1653
1654 // Downscale.
1655 if (DstScale < SrcScale) {
1656 // When converting to integers, we round towards zero. For negative numbers,
1657 // right shifting rounds towards negative infinity. In this case, we can
1658 // just round up before shifting.
1659 if (DstIsInteger && SrcIsSigned) {
1660 Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Result->getType());
1661 Value *IsNegative = Builder.CreateICmpSLT(Result, Zero);
1662 Value *LowBits = ConstantInt::get(
1663 CGF.getLLVMContext(), APInt::getLowBitsSet(ResultWidth, SrcScale));
1664 Value *Rounded = Builder.CreateAdd(Result, LowBits);
1665 Result = Builder.CreateSelect(IsNegative, Rounded, Result);
1666 }
1667
1668 Result = SrcIsSigned
1669 ? Builder.CreateAShr(Result, SrcScale - DstScale, "downscale")
1670 : Builder.CreateLShr(Result, SrcScale - DstScale, "downscale");
1671 }
1672
1673 if (!DstFPSema.isSaturated()) {
1674 // Resize.
1675 Result = Builder.CreateIntCast(Result, DstIntTy, SrcIsSigned, "resize");
1676
1677 // Upscale.
1678 if (DstScale > SrcScale)
1679 Result = Builder.CreateShl(Result, DstScale - SrcScale, "upscale");
1680 } else {
1681 // Adjust the number of fractional bits.
1682 if (DstScale > SrcScale) {
1683 // Compare to DstWidth to prevent resizing twice.
1684 ResultWidth = std::max(SrcWidth + DstScale - SrcScale, DstWidth);
1685 llvm::Type *UpscaledTy = Builder.getIntNTy(ResultWidth);
1686 Result = Builder.CreateIntCast(Result, UpscaledTy, SrcIsSigned, "resize");
1687 Result = Builder.CreateShl(Result, DstScale - SrcScale, "upscale");
1688 }
1689
1690 // Handle saturation.
1691 bool LessIntBits = DstFPSema.getIntegralBits() < SrcFPSema.getIntegralBits();
1692 if (LessIntBits) {
1693 Value *Max = ConstantInt::get(
1694 CGF.getLLVMContext(),
1695 APFixedPoint::getMax(DstFPSema).getValue().extOrTrunc(ResultWidth));
1696 Value *TooHigh = SrcIsSigned ? Builder.CreateICmpSGT(Result, Max)
1697 : Builder.CreateICmpUGT(Result, Max);
1698 Result = Builder.CreateSelect(TooHigh, Max, Result, "satmax");
1699 }
1700 // Cannot overflow min to dest type if src is unsigned since all fixed
1701 // point types can cover the unsigned min of 0.
1702 if (SrcIsSigned && (LessIntBits || !DstIsSigned)) {
1703 Value *Min = ConstantInt::get(
1704 CGF.getLLVMContext(),
1705 APFixedPoint::getMin(DstFPSema).getValue().extOrTrunc(ResultWidth));
1706 Value *TooLow = Builder.CreateICmpSLT(Result, Min);
1707 Result = Builder.CreateSelect(TooLow, Min, Result, "satmin");
1708 }
1709
1710 // Resize the integer part to get the final destination size.
1711 if (ResultWidth != DstWidth)
1712 Result = Builder.CreateIntCast(Result, DstIntTy, SrcIsSigned, "resize");
1713 }
1714 return Result;
1715}
1716
1717/// Emit a conversion from the specified complex type to the specified
1718/// destination type, where the destination type is an LLVM scalar type.
1719Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitComplexToScalarConversion(
1720 CodeGenFunction::ComplexPairTy Src, QualType SrcTy, QualType DstTy,
1721 SourceLocation Loc) {
1722 // Get the source element type.
1723 SrcTy = SrcTy->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
1724
1725 // Handle conversions to bool first, they are special: comparisons against 0.
1726 if (DstTy->isBooleanType()) {
1727 // Complex != 0 -> (Real != 0) | (Imag != 0)
1728 Src.first = EmitScalarConversion(Src.first, SrcTy, DstTy, Loc);
1729 Src.second = EmitScalarConversion(Src.second, SrcTy, DstTy, Loc);
1730 return Builder.CreateOr(Src.first, Src.second, "tobool");
1731 }
1732
1733 // C99 6.3.1.7p2: "When a value of complex type is converted to a real type,
1734 // the imaginary part of the complex value is discarded and the value of the
1735 // real part is converted according to the conversion rules for the
1736 // corresponding real type.
1737 return EmitScalarConversion(Src.first, SrcTy, DstTy, Loc);
1738}
1739
1740Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitNullValue(QualType Ty) {
1741 return CGF.EmitFromMemory(CGF.CGM.EmitNullConstant(Ty), Ty);
1742}

1744/// Emit a sanitization check for the given "binary" operation (which
1745/// might actually be a unary increment which has been lowered to a binary
1746/// operation). The check passes if all values in \p Checks (which are \c i1),
1747/// are \c true.
1748void ScalarExprEmitter::EmitBinOpCheck(
1749 ArrayRef<std::pair<Value *, SanitizerMask>> Checks, const BinOpInfo &Info) {
1750 assert(CGF.IsSanitizerScope);
1751 SanitizerHandler Check;
1752 SmallVector<llvm::Constant *, 4> StaticData;
1753 SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 2> DynamicData;
1754
1755 BinaryOperatorKind Opcode = Info.Opcode;
1756 if (BinaryOperator::isCompoundAssignmentOp(Opcode))
1757 Opcode = BinaryOperator::getOpForCompoundAssignment(Opcode);
1758
1759 StaticData.push_back(CGF.EmitCheckSourceLocation(Info.E->getExprLoc()));
1760 const UnaryOperator *UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(Info.E);
1761 if (UO && UO->getOpcode() == UO_Minus) {
1762 Check = SanitizerHandler::NegateOverflow;
1763 StaticData.push_back(CGF.EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(UO->getType()));
1764 DynamicData.push_back(Info.RHS);
1765 } else {
1766 if (BinaryOperator::isShiftOp(Opcode)) {
1767 // Shift LHS negative or too large, or RHS out of bounds.
1768 Check = SanitizerHandler::ShiftOutOfBounds;
1769 const BinaryOperator *BO = cast<BinaryOperator>(Info.E);
1770 StaticData.push_back(
1771 CGF.EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(BO->getLHS()->getType()));
1772 StaticData.push_back(
1773 CGF.EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(BO->getRHS()->getType()));
1774 } else if (Opcode == BO_Div || Opcode == BO_Rem) {
1775 // Divide or modulo by zero, or signed overflow (eg INT_MAX / -1).
1776 Check = SanitizerHandler::DivremOverflow;
1777 StaticData.push_back(CGF.EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(Info.Ty));
1778 } else {
1779 // Arithmetic overflow (+, -, *).
1780 switch (Opcode) {
1781 case BO_Add: Check = SanitizerHandler::AddOverflow; break;
1782 case BO_Sub: Check = SanitizerHandler::SubOverflow; break;
1783 case BO_Mul: Check = SanitizerHandler::MulOverflow; break;
1784 default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected opcode for bin op check");
1785 }
1786 StaticData.push_back(CGF.EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(Info.Ty));
1787 }
1788 DynamicData.push_back(Info.LHS);
1789 DynamicData.push_back(Info.RHS);
1790 }
1791
1792 CGF.EmitCheck(Checks, Check, StaticData, DynamicData);
1793}

1798
1799Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitExpr(Expr *E) {
1800 CGF.ErrorUnsupported(E, "scalar expression");
1801 if (E->getType()->isVoidType())
1802 return nullptr;
1803 return llvm::UndefValue::get(CGF.ConvertType(E->getType()));
1804}
1805
1806Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitShuffleVectorExpr(ShuffleVectorExpr *E) {
1807 // Vector Mask Case
1808 if (E->getNumSubExprs() == 2) {
1809 Value *LHS = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getExpr(0));
1810 Value *RHS = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getExpr(1));
1811 Value *Mask;
1812
1813 llvm::VectorType *LTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(LHS->getType());
1814 unsigned LHSElts = LTy->getNumElements();
1815
1816 Mask = RHS;
1817
1818 llvm::VectorType *MTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(Mask->getType());
1819
1820 // Mask off the high bits of each shuffle index.
1821 Value *MaskBits =
1822 llvm::ConstantInt::get(MTy, llvm::NextPowerOf2(LHSElts - 1) - 1);
1823 Mask = Builder.CreateAnd(Mask, MaskBits, "mask");
1824
1825 // newv = undef
1826 // mask = mask & maskbits
1827 // for each elt
1828 // n = extract mask i
1829 // x = extract val n
1830 // newv = insert newv, x, i
1831 llvm::VectorType *RTy = llvm::VectorType::get(LTy->getElementType(),
1832 MTy->getNumElements());
1833 Value* NewV = llvm::UndefValue::get(RTy);
1834 for (unsigned i = 0, e = MTy->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
1835 Value *IIndx = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.SizeTy, i);
1836 Value *Indx = Builder.CreateExtractElement(Mask, IIndx, "shuf_idx");
1837
1838 Value *VExt = Builder.CreateExtractElement(LHS, Indx, "shuf_elt");
1839 NewV = Builder.CreateInsertElement(NewV, VExt, IIndx, "shuf_ins");
1840 }
1841 return NewV;
1842 }
1843
1844 Value* V1 = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getExpr(0));
1845 Value* V2 = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getExpr(1));
1846
1847 SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 32> indices;
1848 for (unsigned i = 2; i < E->getNumSubExprs(); ++i) {
1849 llvm::APSInt Idx = E->getShuffleMaskIdx(CGF.getContext(), i-2);
1850 // Check for -1 and output it as undef in the IR.
1851 if (Idx.isSigned() && Idx.isAllOnesValue())
1852 indices.push_back(llvm::UndefValue::get(CGF.Int32Ty));
1853 else
1854 indices.push_back(Builder.getInt32(Idx.getZExtValue()));
1855 }
1856
1857 Value *SV = llvm::ConstantVector::get(indices);
1858 return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(V1, V2, SV, "shuffle");
1859}
1860
1861Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitConvertVectorExpr(ConvertVectorExpr *E) {
1862 QualType SrcType = E->getSrcExpr()->getType(),
1863 DstType = E->getType();
1864
1865 Value *Src = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getSrcExpr());
1866
1867 SrcType = CGF.getContext().getCanonicalType(SrcType);
1868 DstType = CGF.getContext().getCanonicalType(DstType);
1869 if (SrcType == DstType) return Src;
1870
1871 assert(SrcType->isVectorType() &&
1872 "ConvertVector source type must be a vector");
1873 assert(DstType->isVectorType() &&
1874 "ConvertVector destination type must be a vector");
1875
1876 llvm::Type *SrcTy = Src->getType();
1877 llvm::Type *DstTy = ConvertType(DstType);
1878
1879 // Ignore conversions like int -> uint.
1880 if (SrcTy == DstTy)
1881 return Src;
1882
1883 QualType SrcEltType = SrcType->getAs<VectorType>()->getElementType(),
1884 DstEltType = DstType->getAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
1885
1886 assert(SrcTy->isVectorTy() &&
1887 "ConvertVector source IR type must be a vector");
1888 assert(DstTy->isVectorTy() &&
1889 "ConvertVector destination IR type must be a vector");
1890
1891 llvm::Type *SrcEltTy = SrcTy->getVectorElementType(),
1892 *DstEltTy = DstTy->getVectorElementType();
1893
1894 if (DstEltType->isBooleanType()) {
1895 assert((SrcEltTy->isFloatingPointTy() ||
1896 isa<llvm::IntegerType>(SrcEltTy)) && "Unknown boolean conversion");
1897
1898 llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(SrcTy);
1899 if (SrcEltTy->isFloatingPointTy()) {
1900 return Builder.CreateFCmpUNE(Src, Zero, "tobool");
1901 } else {
1902 return Builder.CreateICmpNE(Src, Zero, "tobool");
1903 }
1904 }
1905
1906 // We have the arithmetic types: real int/float.
1907 Value *Res = nullptr;
1908
1909 if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(SrcEltTy)) {
1910 bool InputSigned = SrcEltType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1911 if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(DstEltTy))
1912 Res = Builder.CreateIntCast(Src, DstTy, InputSigned, "conv");
1913 else if (InputSigned)
1914 Res = Builder.CreateSIToFP(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1915 else
1916 Res = Builder.CreateUIToFP(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1917 } else if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(DstEltTy)) {
1918 assert(SrcEltTy->isFloatingPointTy() && "Unknown real conversion");
1919 if (DstEltType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType())
1920 Res = Builder.CreateFPToSI(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1921 else
1922 Res = Builder.CreateFPToUI(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1923 } else {
1924 assert(SrcEltTy->isFloatingPointTy() && DstEltTy->isFloatingPointTy() &&
1925 "Unknown real conversion");
1926 if (DstEltTy->getTypeID() < SrcEltTy->getTypeID())
1927 Res = Builder.CreateFPTrunc(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1928 else
1929 Res = Builder.CreateFPExt(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1930 }
1931
1932 return Res;
1933}
1934
1935Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitMemberExpr(MemberExpr *E) {
1936 if (CodeGenFunction::ConstantEmission Constant = CGF.tryEmitAsConstant(E)) {
1937 CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E->getBase());
1938 return CGF.emitScalarConstant(Constant, E);
1939 } else {
1940 Expr::EvalResult Result;
1941 if (E->EvaluateAsInt(Result, CGF.getContext(), Expr::SE_AllowSideEffects)) {
1942 llvm::APSInt Value = Result.Val.getInt();
1943 CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E->getBase());
1944 return Builder.getInt(Value);
1945 }
1946 }
1947
1948 return EmitLoadOfLValue(E);
1949}
1950
1951Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitArraySubscriptExpr(ArraySubscriptExpr *E) {
1952 TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
1953
1954 // Emit subscript expressions in rvalue context's. For most cases, this just
1955 // loads the lvalue formed by the subscript expr. However, we have to be
1956 // careful, because the base of a vector subscript is occasionally an rvalue,
1957 // so we can't get it as an lvalue.
1958 if (!E->getBase()->getType()->isVectorType()) {
1959 // Note: this eventually calls EmitArraySubscriptExpression which will set
1960 // CHERI sub-object bounds on the array.
1961 return EmitLoadOfLValue(E);
1962 }
1963
1964 // Handle the vector case. The base must be a vector, the index must be an
1965 // integer value.
1966 Value *Base = Visit(E->getBase());
1967 Value *Idx = Visit(E->getIdx());
1968 QualType IdxTy = E->getIdx()->getType();
1969
1970 if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds))
1971 CGF.EmitBoundsCheck(E, E->getBase(), Idx, IdxTy, /*Accessed*/true);
1972
1973 // Note: don't Add CHERI sub-object bounds for extractvector (it should be
1974 // ensured by the backend that this cannot be out of bounds)
1975#if 0
1976 if (CGF.getLangOpts().getCheriBounds() >= LangOptions::CBM_SubObjectsSafe) {
1977 auto BoundedResult = CGF.setCHERIBoundsOnArraySubscript(Base, E);
1978 assert(BoundedResult->getType() == Base->getType());
1979 Base = BoundedResult;
1980 }
1981#endif
1982 return Builder.CreateExtractElement(Base, Idx, "vecext");
1983}
1984
1985static llvm::Constant *getMaskElt(llvm::ShuffleVectorInst *SVI, unsigned Idx,
1986 unsigned Off, llvm::Type *I32Ty) {
1987 int MV = SVI->getMaskValue(Idx);
1988 if (MV == -1)
1989 return llvm::UndefValue::get(I32Ty);
1990 return llvm::ConstantInt::get(I32Ty, Off+MV);
1991}
1992
1993static llvm::Constant *getAsInt32(llvm::ConstantInt *C, llvm::Type *I32Ty) {
1994 if (C->getBitWidth() != 32) {
1995 assert(llvm::ConstantInt::isValueValidForType(I32Ty,
1996 C->getZExtValue()) &&
1997 "Index operand too large for shufflevector mask!");
1998 return llvm::ConstantInt::get(I32Ty, C->getZExtValue());
1999 }
2000 return C;
2001}
2002
2003Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitInitListExpr(InitListExpr *E) {
2004 bool Ignore = TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
2005 (void)Ignore;
2006 assert (Ignore == false && "init list ignored");
2007 unsigned NumInitElements = E->getNumInits();
2008
2009 if (E->hadArrayRangeDesignator())
2010 CGF.ErrorUnsupported(E, "GNU array range designator extension");
2011
2012 llvm::VectorType *VType =
2013 dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(ConvertType(E->getType()));
2014
2015 if (!VType) {
2016 if (NumInitElements == 0) {
2017 // C++11 value-initialization for the scalar.
2018 return EmitNullValue(E->getType());
2019 }
2020 // We have a scalar in braces. Just use the first element.
2021 return Visit(E->getInit(0));
2022 }
2023
2024 unsigned ResElts = VType->getNumElements();
2025
2026 // Loop over initializers collecting the Value for each, and remembering
2027 // whether the source was swizzle (ExtVectorElementExpr). This will allow
2028 // us to fold the shuffle for the swizzle into the shuffle for the vector
2029 // initializer, since LLVM optimizers generally do not want to touch
2030 // shuffles.
2031 unsigned CurIdx = 0;
2032 bool VIsUndefShuffle = false;
2033 llvm::Value *V = llvm::UndefValue::get(VType);
2034 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumInitElements; ++i) {
2035 Expr *IE = E->getInit(i);
2036 Value *Init = Visit(IE);
2037 SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 16> Args;
2038
2039 llvm::VectorType *VVT = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(Init->getType());
2040
2041 // Handle scalar elements. If the scalar initializer is actually one
2042 // element of a different vector of the same width, use shuffle instead of
2043 // extract+insert.
2044 if (!VVT) {
2045 if (isa<ExtVectorElementExpr>(IE)) {
2046 llvm::ExtractElementInst *EI = cast<llvm::ExtractElementInst>(Init);
2047
2048 if (EI->getVectorOperandType()->getNumElements() == ResElts) {
2049 llvm::ConstantInt *C = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(EI->getIndexOperand());
2050 Value *LHS = nullptr, *RHS = nullptr;
2051 if (CurIdx == 0) {
2052 // insert into undef -> shuffle (src, undef)
2053 // shufflemask must use an i32
2054 Args.push_back(getAsInt32(C, CGF.Int32Ty));
2055 Args.resize(ResElts, llvm::UndefValue::get(CGF.Int32Ty));
2056
2057 LHS = EI->getVectorOperand();
2058 RHS = V;
2059 VIsUndefShuffle = true;
2060 } else if (VIsUndefShuffle) {
2061 // insert into undefshuffle && size match -> shuffle (v, src)
2062 llvm::ShuffleVectorInst *SVV = cast<llvm::ShuffleVectorInst>(V);
2063 for (unsigned j = 0; j != CurIdx; ++j)
2064 Args.push_back(getMaskElt(SVV, j, 0, CGF.Int32Ty));
2065 Args.push_back(Builder.getInt32(ResElts + C->getZExtValue()));
2066 Args.resize(ResElts, llvm::UndefValue::get(CGF.Int32Ty));
2067
2068 LHS = cast<llvm::ShuffleVectorInst>(V)->getOperand(0);
2069 RHS = EI->getVectorOperand();
2070 VIsUndefShuffle = false;
2071 }
2072 if (!Args.empty()) {
2073 llvm::Constant *Mask = llvm::ConstantVector::get(Args);
2074 V = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(LHS, RHS, Mask);
2075 ++CurIdx;
2076 continue;
2077 }
2078 }
2079 }
2080 V = Builder.CreateInsertElement(V, Init, Builder.getInt32(CurIdx),
2081 "vecinit");
2082 VIsUndefShuffle = false;
2083 ++CurIdx;
2084 continue;
2085 }
2086
2087 unsigned InitElts = VVT->getNumElements();
2088
2089 // If the initializer is an ExtVecEltExpr (a swizzle), and the swizzle's
2090 // input is the same width as the vector being constructed, generate an
2091 // optimized shuffle of the swizzle input into the result.
2092 unsigned Offset = (CurIdx == 0) ? 0 : ResElts;
2093 if (isa<ExtVectorElementExpr>(IE)) {
2094 llvm::ShuffleVectorInst *SVI = cast<llvm::ShuffleVectorInst>(Init);
2095 Value *SVOp = SVI->getOperand(0);
2096 llvm::VectorType *OpTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(SVOp->getType());
2097
2098 if (OpTy->getNumElements() == ResElts) {
2099 for (unsigned j = 0; j != CurIdx; ++j) {
2100 // If the current vector initializer is a shuffle with undef, merge
2101 // this shuffle directly into it.
2102 if (VIsUndefShuffle) {
2103 Args.push_back(getMaskElt(cast<llvm::ShuffleVectorInst>(V), j, 0,
2104 CGF.Int32Ty));
2105 } else {
2106 Args.push_back(Builder.getInt32(j));
2107 }
2108 }
2109 for (unsigned j = 0, je = InitElts; j != je; ++j)
2110 Args.push_back(getMaskElt(SVI, j, Offset, CGF.Int32Ty));
2111 Args.resize(ResElts, llvm::UndefValue::get(CGF.Int32Ty));
2112
2113 if (VIsUndefShuffle)
2114 V = cast<llvm::ShuffleVectorInst>(V)->getOperand(0);
2115
2116 Init = SVOp;
2117 }
2118 }
2119
2120 // Extend init to result vector length, and then shuffle its contribution
2121 // to the vector initializer into V.
2122 if (Args.empty()) {
2123 for (unsigned j = 0; j != InitElts; ++j)
2124 Args.push_back(Builder.getInt32(j));
2125 Args.resize(ResElts, llvm::UndefValue::get(CGF.Int32Ty));
2126 llvm::Constant *Mask = llvm::ConstantVector::get(Args);
2127 Init = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Init, llvm::UndefValue::get(VVT),
2128 Mask, "vext");
2129
2130 Args.clear();
2131 for (unsigned j = 0; j != CurIdx; ++j)
2132 Args.push_back(Builder.getInt32(j));
2133 for (unsigned j = 0; j != InitElts; ++j)
2134 Args.push_back(Builder.getInt32(j+Offset));
2135 Args.resize(ResElts, llvm::UndefValue::get(CGF.Int32Ty));
2136 }
2137
2138 // If V is undef, make sure it ends up on the RHS of the shuffle to aid
2139 // merging subsequent shuffles into this one.
2140 if (CurIdx == 0)
2141 std::swap(V, Init);
2142 llvm::Constant *Mask = llvm::ConstantVector::get(Args);
2143 V = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(V, Init, Mask, "vecinit");
2144 VIsUndefShuffle = isa<llvm::UndefValue>(Init);
2145 CurIdx += InitElts;
2146 }
2147
2148 // FIXME: evaluate codegen vs. shuffling against constant null vector.
2149 // Emit remaining default initializers.
2150 llvm::Type *EltTy = VType->getElementType();
2151
2152 // Emit remaining default initializers
2153 for (/* Do not initialize i*/; CurIdx < ResElts; ++CurIdx) {
2154 Value *Idx = Builder.getInt32(CurIdx);
2155 llvm::Value *Init = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(EltTy);
2156 V = Builder.CreateInsertElement(V, Init, Idx, "vecinit");
2157 }
2158 return V;
2159}

2161bool CodeGenFunction::ShouldNullCheckClassCastValue(const CastExpr *CE) {
2162 const Expr *E = CE->getSubExpr();
2163
2164 if (CE->getCastKind() == CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase)
2165 return false;
2166
2167 if (isa<CXXThisExpr>(E->IgnoreParens())) {
2168 // We always assume that 'this' is never null.
2169 return false;
2170 }
2171
2172 if (const ImplicitCastExpr *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(CE)) {
2173 // And that glvalue casts are never null.
2174 if (ICE->getValueKind() != VK_RValue)
2175 return false;
2176 }
2177
2178 return true;
2179}

2181llvm::Value* CodeGenFunction::EmitPointerCast(llvm::Value *From,
2182 llvm::PointerType *ToType) {
2183 llvm::PointerType *FromTy = cast<llvm::PointerType>(From->getType());
2184 unsigned FromAddrSpace = FromTy->getAddressSpace();
2185 unsigned ToAddrSpace = ToType->getAddressSpace();
2186 if (FromAddrSpace == ToAddrSpace)
2187 return Builder.CreateBitCast(From, ToType);
2188 else
2189 return Builder.CreateAddrSpaceCast(From, ToType);
2190}
2191
2192llvm::Value* CodeGenFunction::EmitPointerCast(llvm::Value *From,
2193 QualType FromTy,
2194 QualType ToTy) {
2195 llvm::PointerType *toTy = cast<llvm::PointerType>(ConvertType(ToTy));
2196 unsigned ToAddrSpace = toTy->getAddressSpace();
2197 llvm::Value *result = EmitPointerCast(From, toTy);
2198 if (Target.getTriple().isMIPS()) {
2199 if (ToAddrSpace != (unsigned)CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getCHERICapabilityAS()) return result;
2200 unsigned flags = 0xffff;
2201 // Clear the store and store-capability flags
2202 if (ToTy->getPointeeType().getQualifiers().hasInput() &&
2203 !FromTy->getPointeeType().getQualifiers().hasInput())
2204 flags &= 0xFFD7;
2205 // Clear the load and load-capability flags
2206 if (ToTy->getPointeeType().getQualifiers().hasOutput() &&
2207 !FromTy->getPointeeType().getQualifiers().hasOutput())
2208 flags &= 0xFFEB;
2209
2210 if (flags != 0xffff) {
2211 llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_cap_perms_and, SizeTy);
2212 if (F->getFunctionType()->getParamType(0) != result->getType())
2213 result = Builder.CreateBitCast(result, F->getFunctionType()->getParamType(0));
2214 result = Builder.CreateCall(F, {result,
2215 llvm::ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, flags)});
2216 if (toTy != result->getType())
2217 result = Builder.CreateBitCast(result, toTy);
2218 }
2219 }
2220 return result;
2221}
