2230
2231static llvm::Value *createCToPtr(CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::Value *Cap,
2232 llvm::Type *LLVMTy, QualType Ty) {
2233 assert(llvm::isCheriPointer(Cap->getType(), &CGF.CGM.getDataLayout()));
2234 assert(LLVMTy->isIntegerTy());
2235 auto DDC =
2236 CGF.Builder.CreateIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_ddc_get, {}, {});
2237 auto CToPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateIntrinsic(
2238 llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_cap_to_pointer, CGF.PtrDiffTy, {DDC, Cap});
2239 // sign extend if the target is a signed integer type otherwise zext.
2240 // This should only happen when assigning the result to a larger type:
2241 // i.e. __int128 or int64_t for CHERI64
2242 return CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(CToPtr, LLVMTy, Ty->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType());
2243}
2244
2245// VisitCastExpr - Emit code for an explicit or implicit cast. Implicit casts
2246// have to handle a more broad range of conversions than explicit casts, as they
2247// handle things like function to ptr-to-function decay etc.
2248Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitCastExpr(CastExpr *CE) {
2249 Expr *E = CE->getSubExpr();
2250 QualType DestTy = CE->getType();
2251 CastKind Kind = CE->getCastKind();
2252
2253 // These cases are generally not written to ignore the result of
2254 // evaluating their sub-expressions, so we clear this now.
2255 bool Ignored = TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
2256
2257 // Since almost all cast kinds apply to scalars, this switch doesn't have
2258 // a default case, so the compiler will warn on a missing case. The cases
2259 // are in the same order as in the CastKind enum.
2260 switch (Kind) {
2261 case CK_Dependent: llvm_unreachable("dependent cast kind in IR gen!");
2262 case CK_BuiltinFnToFnPtr:
2263 llvm_unreachable("builtin functions are handled elsewhere");
2264
2265 case CK_LValueBitCast:
2266 case CK_ObjCObjectLValueCast: {
2267 Address Addr = EmitLValue(E).getAddress();
2268 Addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(DestTy));
2269 LValue LV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, DestTy);
2270 return EmitLoadOfLValue(LV, CE->getExprLoc());
2271 }
2272
2273 case CK_CPointerToObjCPointerCast:
2274 case CK_BlockPointerToObjCPointerCast:
2275 case CK_AnyPointerToBlockPointerCast:
2276 case CK_BitCast: {
2277 Value *Src = Visit(const_cast<Expr*>(E));
2278 llvm::Type *SrcTy = Src->getType();
2279 llvm::Type *DstTy = ConvertType(DestTy);
2280 if (SrcTy->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() && DstTy->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() &&
2281 SrcTy->getPointerAddressSpace() != DstTy->getPointerAddressSpace()) {
2282 llvm_unreachable("wrong cast for pointers in different address spaces"
2283 "(must be an address space cast)!");
2284 }
2285
2286 if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIUnrelatedCast)) {
2287 if (auto PT = DestTy->getAs<PointerType>())
2288 CGF.EmitVTablePtrCheckForCast(PT->getPointeeType(), Src,
2289 /*MayBeNull=*/true,
2290 CodeGenFunction::CFITCK_UnrelatedCast,
2291 CE->getBeginLoc());
2292 }
2293
2294 if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers) {
2295 const QualType SrcType = E->getType();
2296
2297 if (SrcType.mayBeNotDynamicClass() && DestTy.mayBeDynamicClass()) {
2298 // Casting to pointer that could carry dynamic information (provided by
2299 // invariant.group) requires launder.
2300 Src = Builder.CreateLaunderInvariantGroup(Src);
2301 } else if (SrcType.mayBeDynamicClass() && DestTy.mayBeNotDynamicClass()) {
2302 // Casting to pointer that does not carry dynamic information (provided
2303 // by invariant.group) requires stripping it. Note that we don't do it
2304 // if the source could not be dynamic type and destination could be
2305 // dynamic because dynamic information is already laundered. It is
2306 // because launder(strip(src)) == launder(src), so there is no need to
2307 // add extra strip before launder.
2308 Src = Builder.CreateStripInvariantGroup(Src);
2309 }
2310 }
2311
2312 // Update heapallocsite metadata when there is an explicit cast.
2313 if (llvm::CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<llvm::CallInst>(Src))
2314 if (CI->getMetadata("heapallocsite") && isa<ExplicitCastExpr>(CE))
2315 CGF.getDebugInfo()->
2316 addHeapAllocSiteMetadata(CI, CE->getType(), CE->getExprLoc());
2317
2318 // Handle CHERI pointers casts (e.g. __input+__output qualifiers, etc)
2319 if (E->getType()->isPointerType() && DestTy->isPointerType())
2320 return CGF.EmitPointerCast(Src, E->getType(), DestTy);
2321
2322 return Builder.CreateBitCast(Src, DstTy);
2323 }
2324 case CK_AddressSpaceConversion:
2325 // FIXME: these two should probably be moved
2326 case CK_CHERICapabilityToPointer:
2327 case CK_PointerToCHERICapability: {
2328 if (CGF.CGM.PointerCastStats) {
2329 if (Kind == CK_PointerToCHERICapability) {
2330 CGF.CGM.PointerCastStats->PointerToCap.push_back(
2331 {E->getSourceRange(), isa<ImplicitCastExpr>(CE)});
2332 } else {
2333 CGF.CGM.PointerCastStats->CapToPointer.push_back(
2334 {E->getSourceRange(), isa<ImplicitCastExpr>(CE)});
2335 }
2336 }
2337
2338 Expr::EvalResult Result;
2339 if (E->EvaluateAsRValue(Result, CGF.getContext()) &&
2340 Result.Val.isNullPointer()) {
2341 // If E has side effect, it is emitted even if its final result is a
2342 // null pointer. In that case, a DCE pass should be able to
2343 // eliminate the useless instructions emitted during translating E.
2344 if (Result.HasSideEffects)
2345 Visit(E);
2346 return CGF.CGM.getNullPointer(cast<llvm::PointerType>(
2347 ConvertType(DestTy)), DestTy);
2348 }
2349 // Since target may map different address spaces in AST to the same address
2350 // space, an address space conversion may end up as a bitcast.
2351 Value *Src = Visit(const_cast<Expr*>(E));
2352 llvm::Type *DestType = ConvertType(DestTy);
2353 if (Src->getType() == DestType)
2354 return Src;
2355 auto &TI = CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo();
2356 QualType SrcTy = E->getType();
2357 QualType SrcPointeeTy = SrcTy->getPointeeType();
2358 QualType DstPointeeTy = DestTy->getPointeeType();
2359 if (TI.SupportsCapabilities()) {
2360 if (SrcPointeeTy->isFunctionType() && DstPointeeTy->isFunctionType()) {
2361 // FIXME: Should we handle casts in the other direction by doing a
2362 // pcc-relative cfromptr?
2363 if (Kind == CK_PointerToCHERICapability)
2364 Src = CodeGenFunction::FunctionAddressToCapability(CGF, Src);
2365 }
2366 }
2367
2368 return CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().performAddrSpaceCast(
2369 CGF, Src, SrcPointeeTy.getAddressSpace(),
2370 DstPointeeTy.getAddressSpace(), DestType);
2371 }
2372 case CK_CHERICapabilityToOffset:
2373 case CK_CHERICapabilityToAddress: {
2374 llvm::Value *Src = nullptr;
2375 // Special handling of CHERI C++ capability references. By default, clang
2376 // emits a load of the referencee but that can lead to the Verifier being
2377 // unhappy if the referencee type is incomplete. What we really want is
2378 // just the pointer to the referencee, which is what we do here.
2379 if (const DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E))
2380 if (const VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(DRE->getDecl()))
2381 if (const ReferenceType *RT = dyn_cast<ReferenceType>(VD->getType())) {
2382 // RT is guaranteed to be a capability
2383 assert(RT->isCHERICapability());
2384 Src = EmitLValue(E).getPointer();
2385 }
2386
2387 if (!Src)
2388 Src = Visit(E); // The default case
2389 llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(DestTy);
2390 Src = Kind == CK_CHERICapabilityToOffset
2391 ? CGF.getPointerOffset(Src)
2392 : CGF.getPointerAddress(Src);
2393 bool DestSigned = DestTy->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
2394 // Insert int cast in case size of result type and capability offset field
2395 // are not the same. This will be a no-op if the sizes are the same.
2396 return Builder.CreateIntCast(Src, ResultType, DestSigned, "conv");
2397 }
2398
2399 case CK_AtomicToNonAtomic:
2400 case CK_NonAtomicToAtomic:
2401 case CK_NoOp:
2402 case CK_UserDefinedConversion:
2403 return Visit(const_cast<Expr*>(E));
2404
2405 case CK_BaseToDerived: {
2406 const CXXRecordDecl *DerivedClassDecl = DestTy->getPointeeCXXRecordDecl();
2407 assert(DerivedClassDecl && "BaseToDerived arg isn't a C++ object pointer!");
2408
2409 Address Base = CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(E);
2410 Address Derived =
2411 CGF.GetAddressOfDerivedClass(Base, DerivedClassDecl,
2412 CE->path_begin(), CE->path_end(),
2413 CGF.ShouldNullCheckClassCastValue(CE));
2414
2415 // C++11 [expr.static.cast]p11: Behavior is undefined if a downcast is
2416 // performed and the object is not of the derived type.
2417 if (CGF.sanitizePerformTypeCheck())
2418 CGF.EmitTypeCheck(CodeGenFunction::TCK_DowncastPointer, CE->getExprLoc(),
2419 Derived.getPointer(), DestTy->getPointeeType());
2420
2421 if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIDerivedCast))
2422 CGF.EmitVTablePtrCheckForCast(
2423 DestTy->getPointeeType(), Derived.getPointer(),
2424 /*MayBeNull=*/true, CodeGenFunction::CFITCK_DerivedCast,
2425 CE->getBeginLoc());
2426
2427 return Derived.getPointer();
2428 }
2429 case CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase:
2430 case CK_DerivedToBase: {
2431 // The EmitPointerWithAlignment path does this fine; just discard
2432 // the alignment.
2433 return CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(CE).getPointer();
2434 }
2435
2436 case CK_Dynamic: {
2437 Address V = CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(E);
2438 const CXXDynamicCastExpr *DCE = cast<CXXDynamicCastExpr>(CE);
2439 return CGF.EmitDynamicCast(V, DCE);
2440 }
2441
2442 case CK_ArrayToPointerDecay:
2443 return CGF.EmitArrayToPointerDecay(E).getPointer();
2444 case CK_FunctionToPointerDecay: {
2445 llvm::Value *Addr = EmitLValue(E).getPointer();
2446 llvm::Type *AddrTy = Addr->getType();
2447 auto &TI = CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo();
2448 if (TI.areAllPointersCapabilities()) {
2449 unsigned CapAS = CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getCHERICapabilityAS();
2450 if (AddrTy->getPointerAddressSpace() != CapAS) {
2451 Addr = CodeGenFunction::FunctionAddressToCapability(CGF, Addr);
2452 }
2453 }
2454 return Addr;
2455 }
2456
2457 case CK_NullToPointer:
2458 if (MustVisitNullValue(E))
2459 (void) Visit(E);
2460
2461 return CGF.CGM.getNullPointer(cast<llvm::PointerType>(ConvertType(DestTy)),
2462 DestTy);
2463
2464 case CK_NullToMemberPointer: {
2465 if (MustVisitNullValue(E))
2466 (void) Visit(E);
2467
2468 const MemberPointerType *MPT = CE->getType()->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
2469 return CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().EmitNullMemberPointer(MPT);
2470 }
2471
2472 case CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer:
2473 case CK_BaseToDerivedMemberPointer:
2474 case CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer: {
2475 Value *Src = Visit(E);
2476
2477 // Note that the AST doesn't distinguish between checked and
2478 // unchecked member pointer conversions, so we always have to
2479 // implement checked conversions here. This is inefficient when
2480 // actual control flow may be required in order to perform the
2481 // check, which it is for data member pointers (but not member
2482 // function pointers on Itanium and ARM).
2483 return CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberPointerConversion(CGF, CE, Src);
2484 }
2485
2486 case CK_ARCProduceObject:
2487 return CGF.EmitARCRetainScalarExpr(E);
2488 case CK_ARCConsumeObject:
2489 return CGF.EmitObjCConsumeObject(E->getType(), Visit(E));
2490 case CK_ARCReclaimReturnedObject:
2491 return CGF.EmitARCReclaimReturnedObject(E, /*allowUnsafe*/ Ignored);
2492 case CK_ARCExtendBlockObject:
2493 return CGF.EmitARCExtendBlockObject(E);
2494
2495 case CK_CopyAndAutoreleaseBlockObject:
2496 return CGF.EmitBlockCopyAndAutorelease(Visit(E), E->getType());
2497
2498 case CK_FloatingRealToComplex:
2499 case CK_FloatingComplexCast:
2500 case CK_IntegralRealToComplex:
2501 case CK_IntegralComplexCast:
2502 case CK_IntegralComplexToFloatingComplex:
2503 case CK_FloatingComplexToIntegralComplex:
2504 case CK_ConstructorConversion:
2505 case CK_ToUnion:
2506 llvm_unreachable("scalar cast to non-scalar value");
2507
2508 case CK_LValueToRValue:
2509 assert(CGF.getContext().hasSameUnqualifiedType(E->getType(), DestTy));
2510 assert(E->isGLValue() && "lvalue-to-rvalue applied to r-value!");
2511 return Visit(const_cast<Expr*>(E));
2512
2513 case CK_IntegralToPointer: {
2514 Value *Src = Visit(const_cast<Expr*>(E));
2515 if (CGF.CGM.PointerCastStats)
2516 CGF.CGM.PointerCastStats->IntToPointer.push_back(
2517 {E->getSourceRange(), isa<ImplicitCastExpr>(CE)});
2518
2519 llvm::Type *DestLLVMTy = ConvertType(DestTy);
2520 auto &C = CGF.getContext();
2521 auto &TI = C.getTargetInfo();
2522 bool IsPureCap = TI.areAllPointersCapabilities();
2523
2524 // First, convert to the correct width so that we control the kind of
2525 // extension.
2526 llvm::Type *MiddleTy = CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().getIntPtrType(DestLLVMTy);
2527
2528 // For __[u]intcap_t, the underlying LLVM type is actually a pointer.
2529 bool SrcIsCheriCap = E->getType()->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.getContext());
2530 if (SrcIsCheriCap) {
2531 // If we're casting to a capability pointer, then it's just a bitcast:
2532 if (DestTy->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.getContext()))
2533 return Builder.CreateBitCast(Src, DestLLVMTy);
2534 // Otherwise, it's some kind of non-capability pointer, so we need to
2535 // create an integer value first
2536 if (IsPureCap) {
2537 Src = CGF.getCapabilityIntegerValue(Src);
2538 } else {
2539 warnAboutImplicitCToPtr(CGF.CGM, CE);
2540 Src = createCToPtr(CGF, Src, MiddleTy, DestTy);
2541 }
2542 }
2543
2544 bool InputSigned = E->getType()->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
2545 llvm::Value* IntResult =
2546 Builder.CreateIntCast(Src, MiddleTy, InputSigned, "conv");
2547
2548
2549 llvm::Value* IntToPtr = nullptr;
2550
2551 if (IsPureCap && DestTy->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.getContext())) {
2552 IntToPtr = CGF.setCapabilityIntegerValue(
2553 llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(cast<llvm::PointerType>(DestLLVMTy)),
2554 IntResult);
2555 } else {
2556 // assert(!SrcIsCheriCap);
2557 // TODO: generate CFromPtr/CFromInt depending on value (for constants use
2558 // CFromInt/otherwise CFromPtr)
2559 // FIMXE: This should warn!
2560
2561 IntToPtr = Builder.CreateIntToPtr(IntResult, DestLLVMTy);
2562 }
2563 if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers) {
2564 // Going from integer to pointer that could be dynamic requires reloading
2565 // dynamic information from invariant.group.
2566 if (DestTy.mayBeDynamicClass())
2567 IntToPtr = Builder.CreateLaunderInvariantGroup(IntToPtr);
2568 }
2569 return IntToPtr;
2570 }
2571 case CK_PointerToIntegral: {
2572 assert(!DestTy->isBooleanType() && "bool should use PointerToBool");
2573 auto *PtrExpr = Visit(E);
2574 llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(DestTy);
2575
2576 if (CGF.CGM.PointerCastStats) {
2577 CGF.CGM.PointerCastStats->PointerToInt.push_back(
2578 {E->getSourceRange(), isa<ImplicitCastExpr>(CE)});
2579 }
2580
2581 if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers) {
2582 const QualType SrcType = E->getType();
2583
2584 // Casting to integer requires stripping dynamic information as it does
2585 // not carries it.
2586 if (SrcType.mayBeDynamicClass())
2587 PtrExpr = Builder.CreateStripInvariantGroup(PtrExpr);
2588 }
2589
2590 auto &C = CGF.getContext();
2591 auto &TI = C.getTargetInfo();
2592 bool IsPureCap = TI.areAllPointersCapabilities();
2593 // For casts from pointers to intcap_t, we need to turn the pointer into a
2594 // capability.
2595 if (DestTy->isCHERICapabilityType(C)) {
2596 assert(DestTy->isIntCapType());
2597 if (E->getType()->isCHERICapabilityType(C))
2598 return Builder.CreateBitCast(PtrExpr, ResultType);
2599
2600 assert(!IsPureCap);
2601 PtrExpr = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(PtrExpr, CGF.PtrDiffTy);
2602 // FIXME: should casts to intcap_t yield a tagged or untagged value?
2603 // I believe we should make a cast to __intcap_t yield the integer value
2604 // and require a (__cheri_tocap ) cast if you really want the cfromddc behaviour
2605 return CGF.setCapabilityIntegerValue(
2606 llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(cast<llvm::PointerType>(ResultType)), PtrExpr);
2607#if 0 // This would yield a cfromddc:
2608 return Builder.CreateIntToPtr(PtrExpr, ResultType);
2609#endif
2610 }
2611 if (IsPureCap) {
2612 PtrExpr = CGF.getPointerAddress(PtrExpr);
2613 return Builder.CreateTruncOrBitCast(PtrExpr, ResultType);
2614 }
2615 // ptrtoint will result in CToPtr in the hybrid ABI -> warn about it
2616 if (E->getType()->isCHERICapabilityType(C)) {
2617 warnAboutImplicitCToPtr(CGF.CGM, CE);
2618 return createCToPtr(CGF, PtrExpr, ResultType, DestTy);
2619 }
2620 return Builder.CreatePtrToInt(PtrExpr, ResultType);
2621 }
2622 case CK_ToVoid: {
2623 CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E);
2624 return nullptr;
2625 }
2626 case CK_VectorSplat: {
2627 llvm::Type *DstTy = ConvertType(DestTy);
2628 Value *Elt = Visit(const_cast<Expr*>(E));
2629 // Splat the element across to all elements
2630 unsigned NumElements = DstTy->getVectorNumElements();
2631 return Builder.CreateVectorSplat(NumElements, Elt, "splat");
2632 }
2633
2634 case CK_FixedPointCast:
2635 return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2636 CE->getExprLoc());
2637
2638 case CK_FixedPointToBoolean:
2639 assert(E->getType()->isFixedPointType() &&
2640 "Expected src type to be fixed point type");
2641 assert(DestTy->isBooleanType() && "Expected dest type to be boolean type");
2642 return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2643 CE->getExprLoc());
2644
2645 case CK_FixedPointToIntegral:
2646 assert(E->getType()->isFixedPointType() &&
2647 "Expected src type to be fixed point type");
2648 assert(DestTy->isIntegerType() && "Expected dest type to be an integer");
2649 return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2650 CE->getExprLoc());
2651
2652 case CK_IntegralToFixedPoint:
2653 assert(E->getType()->isIntegerType() &&
2654 "Expected src type to be an integer");
2655 assert(DestTy->isFixedPointType() &&
2656 "Expected dest type to be fixed point type");
2657 return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2658 CE->getExprLoc());
2659
2660 case CK_IntegralCast: {
2661 ScalarConversionOpts Opts;
2662 if (auto *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(CE)) {
2663 if (!ICE->isPartOfExplicitCast())
2664 Opts = ScalarConversionOpts(CGF.SanOpts);
2665 }
2666 return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2667 CE->getExprLoc(), Opts);
2668 }
2669 case CK_IntegralToFloating:
2670 case CK_FloatingToIntegral:
2671 case CK_FloatingCast:
2672 return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2673 CE->getExprLoc());
2674 case CK_BooleanToSignedIntegral: {
2675 ScalarConversionOpts Opts;
2676 Opts.TreatBooleanAsSigned = true;
2677 return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2678 CE->getExprLoc(), Opts);
2679 }
2680 case CK_IntegralToBoolean:
2681 return EmitIntToBoolConversion(Visit(E));
2682 case CK_PointerToBoolean:
2683 return EmitPointerToBoolConversion(Visit(E), E->getType());
2684 case CK_FloatingToBoolean:
2685 return EmitFloatToBoolConversion(Visit(E));
2686 case CK_MemberPointerToBoolean: {
2687 llvm::Value *MemPtr = Visit(E);
2688 const MemberPointerType *MPT = E->getType()->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
2689 return CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberPointerIsNotNull(CGF, MemPtr, MPT);
2690 }
2691
2692 case CK_FloatingComplexToReal:
2693 case CK_IntegralComplexToReal:
2694 return CGF.EmitComplexExpr(E, false, true).first;
2695
2696 case CK_FloatingComplexToBoolean:
2697 case CK_IntegralComplexToBoolean: {
2698 CodeGenFunction::ComplexPairTy V = CGF.EmitComplexExpr(E);
2699
2700 // TODO: kill this function off, inline appropriate case here
2701 return EmitComplexToScalarConversion(V, E->getType(), DestTy,
2702 CE->getExprLoc());
2703 }
2704
2705 case CK_ZeroToOCLOpaqueType: {
2706 assert((DestTy->isEventT() || DestTy->isQueueT() ||
2707 DestTy->isOCLIntelSubgroupAVCType()) &&
2708 "CK_ZeroToOCLEvent cast on non-event type");
2709 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ConvertType(DestTy));
2710 }
2711
2712 case CK_IntToOCLSampler:
2713 return CGF.CGM.createOpenCLIntToSamplerConversion(E, CGF);
2714
2715 } // end of switch
2716
2717 llvm_unreachable("unknown scalar cast");
2718}
2719
2720Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitStmtExpr(const StmtExpr *E) {
2721 CodeGenFunction::StmtExprEvaluation eval(CGF);
2722 Address RetAlloca = CGF.EmitCompoundStmt(*E->getSubStmt(),
2723 !E->getType()->isVoidType());
2724 if (!RetAlloca.isValid())
2725 return nullptr;
2726 return CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(CGF.MakeAddrLValue(RetAlloca, E->getType()),
2727 E->getExprLoc());
2728}
2729
2730Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitExprWithCleanups(ExprWithCleanups *E) {
2731 CGF.enterFullExpression(E);
2732 CodeGenFunction::RunCleanupsScope Scope(CGF);
2733 Value *V = Visit(E->getSubExpr());
2734 // Defend against dominance problems caused by jumps out of expression
2735 // evaluation through the shared cleanup block.
2736 Scope.ForceCleanup({&V});
2737 return V;
2738}

2740//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2741// Unary Operators
2742//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2743
2744static BinOpInfo createBinOpInfoFromIncDec(const UnaryOperator *E,
2745 llvm::Value *InVal, bool IsInc) {
2746 BinOpInfo BinOp;
2747 BinOp.LHS = InVal;
2748 BinOp.RHS = llvm::ConstantInt::get(InVal->getType(), 1, false);
2749 BinOp.Ty = E->getType();
2750 BinOp.Opcode = IsInc ? BO_Add : BO_Sub;
2751 // FIXME: once UnaryOperator carries FPFeatures, copy it here.
2752 BinOp.E = E;
2753 return BinOp;
2754}
2755
2756llvm::Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitIncDecConsiderOverflowBehavior(
2757 const UnaryOperator *E, llvm::Value *InVal, bool IsInc) {
2758 llvm::Value *Amount =
2759 llvm::ConstantInt::get(InVal->getType(), IsInc ? 1 : -1, true);
2760 StringRef Name = IsInc ? "inc" : "dec";
2761 switch (CGF.getLangOpts().getSignedOverflowBehavior()) {
2762 case LangOptions::SOB_Defined:
2763 return Builder.CreateAdd(InVal, Amount, Name);
2764 case LangOptions::SOB_Undefined:
2765 if (!CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow))
2766 return Builder.CreateNSWAdd(InVal, Amount, Name);
2767 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2768 case LangOptions::SOB_Trapping:
2769 if (!E->canOverflow())
2770 return Builder.CreateNSWAdd(InVal, Amount, Name);
2771 return EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(createBinOpInfoFromIncDec(E, InVal, IsInc));
2772 }
2773 llvm_unreachable("Unknown SignedOverflowBehaviorTy");
2774}
2775
2776llvm::Value *
2777ScalarExprEmitter::EmitScalarPrePostIncDec(const UnaryOperator *E, LValue LV,
2778 bool isInc, bool isPre) {
2779
2780 QualType type = E->getSubExpr()->getType();
2781 llvm::PHINode *atomicPHI = nullptr;
2782 llvm::Value *value;
2783 llvm::Value *input;
2784
2785 int amount = (isInc ? 1 : -1);
2786 bool isSubtraction = !isInc;
2787
2788 if (const AtomicType *atomicTy = type->getAs<AtomicType>()) {
2789 type = atomicTy->getValueType();
2790 if (isInc && type->isBooleanType()) {
2791 llvm::Value *True = CGF.EmitToMemory(Builder.getTrue(), type);
2792 if (isPre) {
2793 Builder.CreateStore(True, LV.getAddress(), LV.isVolatileQualified())
2794 ->setAtomic(llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent);
2795 return Builder.getTrue();
2796 }
2797 // For atomic bool increment, we just store true and return it for
2798 // preincrement, do an atomic swap with true for postincrement
2799 return Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(
2800 llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Xchg, LV.getPointer(), True,
2801 llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent);
2802 }
2803 // Special case for atomic increment / decrement on integers, emit
2804 // atomicrmw instructions. We skip this if we want to be doing overflow
2805 // checking, and fall into the slow path with the atomic cmpxchg loop.
2806 if (!type->isBooleanType() && type->isIntegerType() &&
2807 !(type->isUnsignedIntegerType() &&
2808 CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow)) &&
2809 CGF.getLangOpts().getSignedOverflowBehavior() !=
2810 LangOptions::SOB_Trapping) {
2811 llvm::AtomicRMWInst::BinOp aop = isInc ? llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Add :
2812 llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Sub;
2813 llvm::Instruction::BinaryOps op = isInc ? llvm::Instruction::Add :
2814 llvm::Instruction::Sub;
2815 llvm::Value *amt = CGF.EmitToMemory(
2816 llvm::ConstantInt::get(ConvertType(type), 1, true), type);
2817 llvm::Value *old = Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(aop,
2818 LV.getPointer(), amt, llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent);
2819 return isPre ? Builder.CreateBinOp(op, old, amt) : old;
2820 }
2821 value = EmitLoadOfLValue(LV, E->getExprLoc());
2822 input = value;
2823 // For every other atomic operation, we need to emit a load-op-cmpxchg loop
2824 llvm::BasicBlock *startBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
2825 llvm::BasicBlock *opBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_op", CGF.CurFn);
2826 value = CGF.EmitToMemory(value, type);
2827 Builder.CreateBr(opBB);
2828 Builder.SetInsertPoint(opBB);
2829 atomicPHI = Builder.CreatePHI(value->getType(), 2);
2830 atomicPHI->addIncoming(value, startBB);
2831 value = atomicPHI;
2832 } else {
2833 value = EmitLoadOfLValue(LV, E->getExprLoc());
2834 input = value;
2835 }
2836
2837 // Special case of integer increment that we have to check first: bool++.
2838 // Due to promotion rules, we get:
2839 // bool++ -> bool = bool + 1
2840 // -> bool = (int)bool + 1
2841 // -> bool = ((int)bool + 1 != 0)
2842 // An interesting aspect of this is that increment is always true.
2843 // Decrement does not have this property.
2844 if (isInc && type->isBooleanType()) {
2845 value = Builder.getTrue();
2846
2847 // Most common case by far: integer increment.
2848 } else if (type->isIntegerType()) {
2849 llvm::Value *Base = value;
2850 if (type->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.getContext()))
2851 value = CGF.getCapabilityIntegerValue(Base);
2852 // Note that signed integer inc/dec with width less than int can't
2853 // overflow because of promotion rules; we're just eliding a few steps here.
2854 if (E->canOverflow() && type->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType()) {
2855 value = EmitIncDecConsiderOverflowBehavior(E, value, isInc);
2856 } else if (E->canOverflow() && type->isUnsignedIntegerType() &&
2857 CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow)) {
2858 value =
2859 EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(createBinOpInfoFromIncDec(E, value, isInc));
2860 } else {
2861 llvm::Value *amt = llvm::ConstantInt::get(value->getType(), amount, true);
2862 value = Builder.CreateAdd(value, amt, isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
2863 }
2864 if (type->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.getContext()))
2865 value = CGF.setCapabilityIntegerValue(Base, value);
2866 // Next most common: pointer increment.
2867 } else if (const PointerType *ptr = type->getAs<PointerType>()) {
2868 QualType type = ptr->getPointeeType();
2869
2870 // VLA types don't have constant size.
2871 if (const VariableArrayType *vla
2872 = CGF.getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(type)) {
2873 llvm::Value *numElts = CGF.getVLASize(vla).NumElts;
2874 if (!isInc) numElts = Builder.CreateNSWNeg(numElts, "vla.negsize");
2875 if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
2876 value = Builder.CreateGEP(value, numElts, "vla.inc");
2877 else
2878 value = CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(
2879 value, numElts, /*SignedIndices=*/false, isSubtraction,
2880 E->getExprLoc(), "vla.inc");
2881
2882 // Arithmetic on function pointers (!) is just +-1.
2883 } else if (type->isFunctionType()) {
2884 llvm::Value *amt = Builder.getInt32(amount);
2885
2886 value = CGF.EmitCastToVoidPtr(value);
2887 if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
2888 value = Builder.CreateGEP(value, amt, "incdec.funcptr");
2889 else
2890 value = CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(value, amt, /*SignedIndices=*/false,
2891 isSubtraction, E->getExprLoc(),
2892 "incdec.funcptr");
2893 value = Builder.CreateBitCast(value, input->getType());
2894
2895 // For everything else, we can just do a simple increment.
2896 } else {
2897 llvm::Value *amt = Builder.getInt32(amount);
2898 if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
2899 value = Builder.CreateGEP(value, amt, "incdec.ptr");
2900 else
2901 value = CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(value, amt, /*SignedIndices=*/false,
2902 isSubtraction, E->getExprLoc(),
2903 "incdec.ptr");
2904 }
2905
2906 // Vector increment/decrement.
2907 } else if (type->isVectorType()) {
2908 if (type->hasIntegerRepresentation()) {
2909 llvm::Value *amt = llvm::ConstantInt::get(value->getType(), amount);
2910
2911 value = Builder.CreateAdd(value, amt, isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
2912 } else {
2913 value = Builder.CreateFAdd(
2914 value,
2915 llvm::ConstantFP::get(value->getType(), amount),
2916 isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
2917 }
2918
2919 // Floating point.
2920 } else if (type->isRealFloatingType()) {
2921 // Add the inc/dec to the real part.
2922 llvm::Value *amt;
2923
2924 if (type->isHalfType() && !CGF.getContext().getLangOpts().NativeHalfType) {
2925 // Another special case: half FP increment should be done via float
2926 if (CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo().useFP16ConversionIntrinsics()) {
2927 value = Builder.CreateCall(
2928 CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::convert_from_fp16,
2929 CGF.CGM.FloatTy),
2930 input, "incdec.conv");
2931 } else {
2932 value = Builder.CreateFPExt(input, CGF.CGM.FloatTy, "incdec.conv");
2933 }
2934 }
2935
2936 if (value->getType()->isFloatTy())
2937 amt = llvm::ConstantFP::get(VMContext,
2938 llvm::APFloat(static_cast<float>(amount)));
2939 else if (value->getType()->isDoubleTy())
2940 amt = llvm::ConstantFP::get(VMContext,
2941 llvm::APFloat(static_cast<double>(amount)));
2942 else {
2943 // Remaining types are Half, LongDouble or __float128. Convert from float.
2944 llvm::APFloat F(static_cast<float>(amount));
2945 bool ignored;
2946 const llvm::fltSemantics *FS;
2947 // Don't use getFloatTypeSemantics because Half isn't
2948 // necessarily represented using the "half" LLVM type.
2949 if (value->getType()->isFP128Ty())
2950 FS = &CGF.getTarget().getFloat128Format();
2951 else if (value->getType()->isHalfTy())
2952 FS = &CGF.getTarget().getHalfFormat();
2953 else
2954 FS = &CGF.getTarget().getLongDoubleFormat();
2955 F.convert(*FS, llvm::APFloat::rmTowardZero, &ignored);
2956 amt = llvm::ConstantFP::get(VMContext, F);
2957 }
2958 value = Builder.CreateFAdd(value, amt, isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
2959
2960 if (type->isHalfType() && !CGF.getContext().getLangOpts().NativeHalfType) {
2961 if (CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo().useFP16ConversionIntrinsics()) {
2962 value = Builder.CreateCall(
2963 CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::convert_to_fp16,
2964 CGF.CGM.FloatTy),
2965 value, "incdec.conv");
2966 } else {
2967 value = Builder.CreateFPTrunc(value, input->getType(), "incdec.conv");
2968 }
2969 }
2970
2971 // Objective-C pointer types.
2972 } else {
2973 const ObjCObjectPointerType *OPT = type->castAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
2974 value = CGF.EmitCastToVoidPtr(value);
2975
2976 CharUnits size = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(OPT->getObjectType());
2977 if (!isInc) size = -size;
2978 llvm::Value *sizeValue =
2979 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.SizeTy, size.getQuantity());
2980
2981 if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
2982 value = Builder.CreateGEP(value, sizeValue, "incdec.objptr");
2983 else
2984 value = CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(value, sizeValue,
2985 /*SignedIndices=*/false, isSubtraction,
2986 E->getExprLoc(), "incdec.objptr");
2987 value = Builder.CreateBitCast(value, input->getType());
2988 }
2989
2990 if (atomicPHI) {
2991 llvm::BasicBlock *curBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
2992 llvm::BasicBlock *contBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_cont", CGF.CurFn);
2993 auto Pair = CGF.EmitAtomicCompareExchange(
2994 LV, RValue::get(atomicPHI), RValue::get(value), E->getExprLoc());
2995 llvm::Value *old = CGF.EmitToMemory(Pair.first.getScalarVal(), type);
2996 llvm::Value *success = Pair.second;
2997 atomicPHI->addIncoming(old, curBlock);
2998 Builder.CreateCondBr(success, contBB, atomicPHI->getParent());
2999 Builder.SetInsertPoint(contBB);
3000 return isPre ? value : input;
3001 }
3002
3003 // Store the updated result through the lvalue.
3004 if (LV.isBitField())
3005 CGF.EmitStoreThroughBitfieldLValue(RValue::get(value), LV, &value);
3006 else
3007 CGF.EmitStoreThroughLValue(RValue::get(value), LV);
3008
3009 // If this is a postinc, return the value read from memory, otherwise use the
3010 // updated value.
3011 return isPre ? value : input;
3012}

3016Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryMinus(const UnaryOperator *E) {
3017 TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
3018 // Emit unary minus with EmitSub so we handle overflow cases etc.
3019 BinOpInfo BinOp;
3020 BinOp.RHS = Visit(E->getSubExpr());
3021
3022 if (BinOp.RHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy())
3023 BinOp.LHS = llvm::ConstantFP::getZeroValueForNegation(BinOp.RHS->getType());
3024 else
3025 BinOp.LHS = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(BinOp.RHS->getType());
3026 Value *base = BinOp.LHS;
3027 BinOp.Ty = E->getType();
3028 BinOp.Opcode = BO_Sub;
3029 // FIXME: once UnaryOperator carries FPFeatures, copy it here.
3030 BinOp.E = E;
3031 BinOp.LHS = GetBinOpVal(BinOp, BinOp.LHS);
3032 BinOp.RHS = GetBinOpVal(BinOp, BinOp.RHS);
3033 Value *result = EmitSub(BinOp);
3034 return GetBinOpResult(BinOp, base, result);
3035}

3037Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryNot(const UnaryOperator *E) {
3038 TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
3039 Value *Op = Visit(E->getSubExpr());
3040 Value *Base = Op;
3041 bool IsIntCap = E->getType()->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.getContext());
3042 if (IsIntCap)
3043 Op = CGF.getCapabilityIntegerValue(Op);
3044 Op = Builder.CreateNot(Op, "neg");
3045 if (IsIntCap)
3046 Op = CGF.setCapabilityIntegerValue(Base, Op);
3047 return Op;
3048}
3049
3050Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryLNot(const UnaryOperator *E) {
3051 // Perform vector logical not on comparison with zero vector.
3052 if (E->getType()->isExtVectorType()) {
3053 Value *Oper = Visit(E->getSubExpr());
3054 Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Oper->getType());
3055 Value *Result;
3056 if (Oper->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy())
3057 Result = Builder.CreateFCmp(llvm::CmpInst::FCMP_OEQ, Oper, Zero, "cmp");
3058 else
3059 Result = Builder.CreateICmp(llvm::CmpInst::ICMP_EQ, Oper, Zero, "cmp");
3060 return Builder.CreateSExt(Result, ConvertType(E->getType()), "sext");
3061 }
3062
3063 // Compare operand to zero.
3064 Value *BoolVal = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(E->getSubExpr());
3065
3066 // Invert value.
3067 // TODO: Could dynamically modify easy computations here. For example, if
3068 // the operand is an icmp ne, turn into icmp eq.
3069 BoolVal = Builder.CreateNot(BoolVal, "lnot");
3070
3071 // ZExt result to the expr type.
3072 return Builder.CreateZExt(BoolVal, ConvertType(E->getType()), "lnot.ext");
3073}
3074
3075Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitOffsetOfExpr(OffsetOfExpr *E) {
3076 // Try folding the offsetof to a constant.
3077 Expr::EvalResult EVResult;
3078 if (E->EvaluateAsInt(EVResult, CGF.getContext())) {
3079 llvm::APSInt Value = EVResult.Val.getInt();
3080 return Builder.getInt(Value);
3081 }
3082
3083 // Loop over the components of the offsetof to compute the value.
3084 unsigned n = E->getNumComponents();
3085 llvm::Type* ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
3086 llvm::Value* Result = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ResultType);
3087 QualType CurrentType = E->getTypeSourceInfo()->getType();
3088 for (unsigned i = 0; i != n; ++i) {
3089 OffsetOfNode ON = E->getComponent(i);
3090 llvm::Value *Offset = nullptr;
3091 switch (ON.getKind()) {
3092 case OffsetOfNode::Array: {
3093 // Compute the index
3094 Expr *IdxExpr = E->getIndexExpr(ON.getArrayExprIndex());
3095 llvm::Value* Idx = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(IdxExpr);
3096 bool IdxSigned = IdxExpr->getType()->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
3097 Idx = Builder.CreateIntCast(Idx, ResultType, IdxSigned, "conv");
3098
3099 // Save the element type
3100 CurrentType =
3101 CGF.getContext().getAsArrayType(CurrentType)->getElementType();
3102
3103 // Compute the element size
3104 llvm::Value* ElemSize = llvm::ConstantInt::get(ResultType,
3105 CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(CurrentType).getQuantity());
3106
3107 // Multiply out to compute the result
3108 Offset = Builder.CreateMul(Idx, ElemSize);
3109 break;
3110 }
3111
3112 case OffsetOfNode::Field: {
3113 FieldDecl *MemberDecl = ON.getField();
3114 RecordDecl *RD = CurrentType->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
3115 const ASTRecordLayout &RL = CGF.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
3116
3117 // Compute the index of the field in its parent.
3118 unsigned i = 0;
3119 // FIXME: It would be nice if we didn't have to loop here!
3120 for (RecordDecl::field_iterator Field = RD->field_begin(),
3121 FieldEnd = RD->field_end();
3122 Field != FieldEnd; ++Field, ++i) {
3123 if (*Field == MemberDecl)
3124 break;
3125 }
3126 assert(i < RL.getFieldCount() && "offsetof field in wrong type");
3127
3128 // Compute the offset to the field
3129 int64_t OffsetInt = RL.getFieldOffset(i) /
3130 CGF.getContext().getCharWidth();
3131 Offset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(ResultType, OffsetInt);
3132
3133 // Save the element type.
3134 CurrentType = MemberDecl->getType();
3135 break;
3136 }
3137
3138 case OffsetOfNode::Identifier:
3139 llvm_unreachable("dependent __builtin_offsetof");
3140
3141 case OffsetOfNode::Base: {
3142 if (ON.getBase()->isVirtual()) {
3143 CGF.ErrorUnsupported(E, "virtual base in offsetof");
3144 continue;
3145 }
3146
3147 RecordDecl *RD = CurrentType->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
3148 const ASTRecordLayout &RL = CGF.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
3149
3150 // Save the element type.
3151 CurrentType = ON.getBase()->getType();
3152
3153 // Compute the offset to the base.
3154 const RecordType *BaseRT = CurrentType->getAs<RecordType>();
3155 CXXRecordDecl *BaseRD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(BaseRT->getDecl());
3156 CharUnits OffsetInt = RL.getBaseClassOffset(BaseRD);
3157 Offset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(ResultType, OffsetInt.getQuantity());
3158 break;
3159 }
3160 }
3161 Result = Builder.CreateAdd(Result, Offset);
3162 }
3163 return Result;
3164}

3166/// VisitUnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr - Return the size or alignment of the type of
3167/// argument of the sizeof expression as an integer.
3168Value *
3169ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr(
3170 const UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr *E) {
3171 QualType TypeToSize = E->getTypeOfArgument();
3172 if (E->getKind() == UETT_SizeOf) {
3173 if (const VariableArrayType *VAT =
3174 CGF.getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(TypeToSize)) {
3175 if (E->isArgumentType()) {
3176 // sizeof(type) - make sure to emit the VLA size.
3177 CGF.EmitVariablyModifiedType(TypeToSize);
3178 } else {
3179 // C99 6.5.3.4p2: If the argument is an expression of type
3180 // VLA, it is evaluated.
3181 CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E->getArgumentExpr());
3182 }
3183
3184 auto VlaSize = CGF.getVLASize(VAT);
3185 llvm::Value *size = VlaSize.NumElts;
3186
3187 // Scale the number of non-VLA elements by the non-VLA element size.
3188 CharUnits eltSize = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(VlaSize.Type);
3189 if (!eltSize.isOne())
3190 size = CGF.Builder.CreateNUWMul(CGF.CGM.getSize(eltSize), size);
3191
3192 return size;
3193 }
3194 } else if (E->getKind() == UETT_OpenMPRequiredSimdAlign) {
3195 auto Alignment =
3196 CGF.getContext()
3197 .toCharUnitsFromBits(CGF.getContext().getOpenMPDefaultSimdAlign(
3198 E->getTypeOfArgument()->getPointeeType()))
3199 .getQuantity();
3200 return llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.SizeTy, Alignment);
3201 }
3202
3203 // If this isn't sizeof(vla), the result must be constant; use the constant
3204 // folding logic so we don't have to duplicate it here.
3205 return Builder.getInt(E->EvaluateKnownConstInt(CGF.getContext()));
3206}
3207
3208Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryReal(const UnaryOperator *E) {
3209 Expr *Op = E->getSubExpr();
3210 if (Op->getType()->isAnyComplexType()) {
3211 // If it's an l-value, load through the appropriate subobject l-value.
3212 // Note that we have to ask E because Op might be an l-value that
3213 // this won't work for, e.g. an Obj-C property.
3214 if (E->isGLValue())
3215 return CGF.EmitLoadOfLValue(CGF.EmitLValue(E),
3216 E->getExprLoc()).getScalarVal();
3217
3218 // Otherwise, calculate and project.
3219 return CGF.EmitComplexExpr(Op, false, true).first;
3220 }
3221
3222 return Visit(Op);
3223}
3224
3225Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryImag(const UnaryOperator *E) {
3226 Expr *Op = E->getSubExpr();
3227 if (Op->getType()->isAnyComplexType()) {
3228 // If it's an l-value, load through the appropriate subobject l-value.
3229 // Note that we have to ask E because Op might be an l-value that
3230 // this won't work for, e.g. an Obj-C property.
3231 if (Op->isGLValue())
3232 return CGF.EmitLoadOfLValue(CGF.EmitLValue(E),
3233 E->getExprLoc()).getScalarVal();
3234
3235 // Otherwise, calculate and project.
3236 return CGF.EmitComplexExpr(Op, true, false).second;
3237 }
3238
3239 // __imag on a scalar returns zero. Emit the subexpr to ensure side
3240 // effects are evaluated, but not the actual value.
3241 if (Op->isGLValue())
3242 CGF.EmitLValue(Op);
3243 else
3244 CGF.EmitScalarExpr(Op, true);
3245 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ConvertType(E->getType()));
3246}
