3251
3252BinOpInfo ScalarExprEmitter::EmitBinOps(const BinaryOperator *E) {
3253 TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
3254 BinOpInfo Result;
3255 Result.LHS = Visit(E->getLHS());
3256#ifdef NOTYET
3257 auto RHSExpr = E->getRHS();
3258 bool PromoteRHSToPtrDiff = false;
3259 if (RHSExpr->getType()->isIntCapType()) {
3260 // For arithmetic on __intcap_t we ignore implicit promotions to intcap_t
3261 // on the RHS since we have to convert it back to an i64 anyway:
3262 if (auto CE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(RHSExpr->IgnoreParens())) {
3263 if (CE->getCastKind() == CK_IntegralCast &&
3264 !CE->getSubExpr()->getType()->isIntCapType()) {
3265 RHSExpr = CE->getSubExpr();
3266 PromoteRHSToPtrDiff = true;
3267 }
3268 }
3269 }
3270 Result.RHS = Visit(RHSExpr);
3271 if (PromoteRHSToPtrDiff) {
3272 // Ensure that the RHS is still promoted to the correct type:
3273 Result.RHS = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(Result.RHS, CGF.PtrDiffTy,
3274 E->getType()->isSignedIntegerType(),
3275 "promote");
3276 }
3277#else
3278 Result.RHS = Visit(E->getRHS());
3279#endif
3280 Result.Ty = E->getType();
3281 Result.Opcode = E->getOpcode();
3282 Result.FPFeatures = E->getFPFeatures();
3283 Result.E = E;
3284 return Result;
3285}
3286
3287LValue ScalarExprEmitter::EmitCompoundAssignLValue(
3288 const CompoundAssignOperator *E,
3289 Value *(ScalarExprEmitter::*Func)(const BinOpInfo &),
3290 Value *&Result) {
3291 QualType LHSTy = E->getLHS()->getType();
3292 BinOpInfo OpInfo;
3293
3294 if (E->getComputationResultType()->isAnyComplexType())
3295 return CGF.EmitScalarCompoundAssignWithComplex(E, Result);
3296
3297 // Emit the RHS first. __block variables need to have the rhs evaluated
3298 // first, plus this should improve codegen a little.
3299 OpInfo.RHS = Visit(E->getRHS());
3300 OpInfo.Ty = E->getComputationResultType();
3301 OpInfo.Opcode = E->getOpcode();
3302 OpInfo.FPFeatures = E->getFPFeatures();
3303 OpInfo.E = E;
3304 // Load/convert the LHS.
3305 LValue LHSLV = EmitCheckedLValue(E->getLHS(), CodeGenFunction::TCK_Store);
3306
3307 llvm::PHINode *atomicPHI = nullptr;
3308 if (const AtomicType *atomicTy = LHSTy->getAs<AtomicType>()) {
3309 QualType type = atomicTy->getValueType();
3310 if (!type->isBooleanType() && type->isIntegerType() &&
3311 !(type->isUnsignedIntegerType() &&
3312 CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow)) &&
3313 CGF.getLangOpts().getSignedOverflowBehavior() !=
3314 LangOptions::SOB_Trapping) {
3315 llvm::AtomicRMWInst::BinOp aop = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::BAD_BINOP;
3316 switch (OpInfo.Opcode) {
3317 // We don't have atomicrmw operands for *, %, /, <<, >>
3318 case BO_MulAssign: case BO_DivAssign:
3319 case BO_RemAssign:
3320 case BO_ShlAssign:
3321 case BO_ShrAssign:
3322 break;
3323 case BO_AddAssign:
3324 aop = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Add;
3325 break;
3326 case BO_SubAssign:
3327 aop = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Sub;
3328 break;
3329 case BO_AndAssign:
3330 aop = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::And;
3331 break;
3332 case BO_XorAssign:
3333 aop = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Xor;
3334 break;
3335 case BO_OrAssign:
3336 aop = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Or;
3337 break;
3338 default:
3339 llvm_unreachable("Invalid compound assignment type");
3340 }
3341 if (aop != llvm::AtomicRMWInst::BAD_BINOP) {
3342 llvm::Value *amt = CGF.EmitToMemory(
3343 EmitScalarConversion(OpInfo.RHS, E->getRHS()->getType(), LHSTy,
3344 E->getExprLoc()),
3345 LHSTy);
3346 Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(aop, LHSLV.getPointer(), amt,
3347 llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent);
3348 return LHSLV;
3349 }
3350 }
3351 // FIXME: For floating point types, we should be saving and restoring the
3352 // floating point environment in the loop.
3353 llvm::BasicBlock *startBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3354 llvm::BasicBlock *opBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_op", CGF.CurFn);
3355 OpInfo.LHS = EmitLoadOfLValue(LHSLV, E->getExprLoc());
3356 OpInfo.LHS = CGF.EmitToMemory(OpInfo.LHS, type);
3357 Builder.CreateBr(opBB);
3358 Builder.SetInsertPoint(opBB);
3359 atomicPHI = Builder.CreatePHI(OpInfo.LHS->getType(), 2);
3360 atomicPHI->addIncoming(OpInfo.LHS, startBB);
3361 OpInfo.LHS = atomicPHI;
3362 }
3363 else
3364 OpInfo.LHS = EmitLoadOfLValue(LHSLV, E->getExprLoc());
3365
3366 SourceLocation Loc = E->getExprLoc();
3367 OpInfo.LHS =
3368 EmitScalarConversion(OpInfo.LHS, LHSTy, E->getComputationLHSType(), Loc);
3369
3370 // Expand the binary operator.
3371 // We need special handling for add operations (pointer + integer)
3372 // FIXME: We should be able to emit a GEP for intcap_t add/sub operations,
3373 // but we can't because the logic checks lower down assumes that anything
3374 // that has an LLVM pointer type also has a C pointer type.
3375 if ((OpInfo.Opcode == BO_AddAssign || OpInfo.Opcode == BO_SubAssign) &&
3376 E->getType()->isPointerType())
3377 Result = (this->*Func)(OpInfo);
3378 else {
3379 Value *Base = OpInfo.LHS;
3380 OpInfo.LHS = GetBinOpVal(OpInfo, OpInfo.LHS, E->getComputationLHSType());
3381 OpInfo.RHS = GetBinOpVal(OpInfo, OpInfo.RHS, E->getComputationLHSType());
3382 Result = (this->*Func)(OpInfo);
3383 Result = GetBinOpResult(OpInfo, Base, Result, E->getComputationResultType());
3384 }
3385
3386 // Convert the result back to the LHS type,
3387 // potentially with Implicit Conversion sanitizer check.
3388 Result = EmitScalarConversion(Result, E->getComputationResultType(), LHSTy,
3389 Loc, ScalarConversionOpts(CGF.SanOpts));
3390
3391 if (atomicPHI) {
3392 llvm::BasicBlock *curBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3393 llvm::BasicBlock *contBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_cont", CGF.CurFn);
3394 auto Pair = CGF.EmitAtomicCompareExchange(
3395 LHSLV, RValue::get(atomicPHI), RValue::get(Result), E->getExprLoc());
3396 llvm::Value *old = CGF.EmitToMemory(Pair.first.getScalarVal(), LHSTy);
3397 llvm::Value *success = Pair.second;
3398 atomicPHI->addIncoming(old, curBlock);
3399 Builder.CreateCondBr(success, contBB, atomicPHI->getParent());
3400 Builder.SetInsertPoint(contBB);
3401 return LHSLV;
3402 }
3403
3404 // Store the result value into the LHS lvalue. Bit-fields are handled
3405 // specially because the result is altered by the store, i.e., [C99 6.5.16p1]
3406 // 'An assignment expression has the value of the left operand after the
3407 // assignment...'.
3408 if (LHSLV.isBitField())
3409 CGF.EmitStoreThroughBitfieldLValue(RValue::get(Result), LHSLV, &Result);
3410 else
3411 CGF.EmitStoreThroughLValue(RValue::get(Result), LHSLV);
3412
3413 return LHSLV;
3414}
3415
3416Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitCompoundAssign(const CompoundAssignOperator *E,
3417 Value *(ScalarExprEmitter::*Func)(const BinOpInfo &)) {
3418 bool Ignore = TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
3419 Value *RHS = nullptr;
3420 LValue LHS = EmitCompoundAssignLValue(E, Func, RHS);
3421
3422 // If the result is clearly ignored, return now.
3423 if (Ignore)
3424 return nullptr;
3425
3426 // The result of an assignment in C is the assigned r-value.
3427 if (!CGF.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
3428 return RHS;
3429
3430 // If the lvalue is non-volatile, return the computed value of the assignment.
3431 if (!LHS.isVolatileQualified())
3432 return RHS;
3433
3434 // Otherwise, reload the value.
3435 return EmitLoadOfLValue(LHS, E->getExprLoc());
3436}
3437
3438void ScalarExprEmitter::EmitUndefinedBehaviorIntegerDivAndRemCheck(
3439 const BinOpInfo &Ops, llvm::Value *Zero, bool isDiv) {
3440 SmallVector<std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>, 2> Checks;
3441
3442 if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::IntegerDivideByZero)) {
3443 Checks.push_back(std::make_pair(Builder.CreateICmpNE(Ops.RHS, Zero),
3444 SanitizerKind::IntegerDivideByZero));
3445 }
3446
3447 const auto *BO = cast<BinaryOperator>(Ops.E);
3448 if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow) &&
3449 Ops.Ty->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation() &&
3450 !IsWidenedIntegerOp(CGF.getContext(), BO->getLHS()) &&
3451 Ops.mayHaveIntegerOverflow()) {
3452 llvm::IntegerType *Ty = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(Zero->getType());
3453
3454 llvm::Value *IntMin =
3455 Builder.getInt(llvm::APInt::getSignedMinValue(Ty->getBitWidth()));
3456 llvm::Value *NegOne = llvm::ConstantInt::get(Ty, -1ULL);
3457
3458 llvm::Value *LHSCmp = Builder.CreateICmpNE(Ops.LHS, IntMin);
3459 llvm::Value *RHSCmp = Builder.CreateICmpNE(Ops.RHS, NegOne);
3460 llvm::Value *NotOverflow = Builder.CreateOr(LHSCmp, RHSCmp, "or");
3461 Checks.push_back(
3462 std::make_pair(NotOverflow, SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow));
3463 }
3464
3465 if (Checks.size() > 0)
3466 EmitBinOpCheck(Checks, Ops);
3467}
3468
3469Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitDiv(const BinOpInfo &Ops) {
3470 {
3471 CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
3472 if ((CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::IntegerDivideByZero) ||
3473 CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow)) &&
3474 Ops.Ty->isIntegerType() &&
3475 (Ops.mayHaveIntegerDivisionByZero() || Ops.mayHaveIntegerOverflow())) {
3476 llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ConvertType(Ops.Ty));
3477 EmitUndefinedBehaviorIntegerDivAndRemCheck(Ops, Zero, true);
3478 } else if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::FloatDivideByZero) &&
3479 Ops.Ty->isRealFloatingType() &&
3480 Ops.mayHaveFloatDivisionByZero()) {
3481 llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ConvertType(Ops.Ty));
3482 llvm::Value *NonZero = Builder.CreateFCmpUNE(Ops.RHS, Zero);
3483 EmitBinOpCheck(std::make_pair(NonZero, SanitizerKind::FloatDivideByZero),
3484 Ops);
3485 }
3486 }
3487
3488 if (Ops.LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
3489 llvm::Value *Val = Builder.CreateFDiv(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "div");
3490 if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenCL &&
3491 !CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().CorrectlyRoundedDivSqrt) {
3492 // OpenCL v1.1 s7.4: minimum accuracy of single precision / is 2.5ulp
3493 // OpenCL v1.2 s5.6.4.2: The -cl-fp32-correctly-rounded-divide-sqrt
3494 // build option allows an application to specify that single precision
3495 // floating-point divide (x/y and 1/x) and sqrt used in the program
3496 // source are correctly rounded.
3497 llvm::Type *ValTy = Val->getType();
3498 if (ValTy->isFloatTy() ||
3499 (isa<llvm::VectorType>(ValTy) &&
3500 cast<llvm::VectorType>(ValTy)->getElementType()->isFloatTy()))
3501 CGF.SetFPAccuracy(Val, 2.5);
3502 }
3503 return Val;
3504 }
3505 else if (Ops.Ty->hasUnsignedIntegerRepresentation())
3506 return Builder.CreateUDiv(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "div");
3507 else
3508 return Builder.CreateSDiv(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "div");
3509}
3510
3511Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitRem(const BinOpInfo &Ops) {
3512 // Rem in C can't be a floating point type: C99 6.5.5p2.
3513 if ((CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::IntegerDivideByZero) ||
3514 CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow)) &&
3515 Ops.Ty->isIntegerType() &&
3516 (Ops.mayHaveIntegerDivisionByZero() || Ops.mayHaveIntegerOverflow())) {
3517 CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
3518 llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ConvertType(Ops.Ty));
3519 EmitUndefinedBehaviorIntegerDivAndRemCheck(Ops, Zero, false);
3520 }
3521
3522 if (Ops.Ty->hasUnsignedIntegerRepresentation())
3523 return Builder.CreateURem(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "rem");
3524 else
3525 return Builder.CreateSRem(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "rem");
3526}
3527
3528Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(const BinOpInfo &Ops) {
3529 unsigned IID;
3530 unsigned OpID = 0;
3531
3532 bool isSigned = Ops.Ty->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
3533 switch (Ops.Opcode) {
3534 case BO_Add:
3535 case BO_AddAssign:
3536 OpID = 1;
3537 IID = isSigned ? llvm::Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow :
3538 llvm::Intrinsic::uadd_with_overflow;
3539 break;
3540 case BO_Sub:
3541 case BO_SubAssign:
3542 OpID = 2;
3543 IID = isSigned ? llvm::Intrinsic::ssub_with_overflow :
3544 llvm::Intrinsic::usub_with_overflow;
3545 break;
3546 case BO_Mul:
3547 case BO_MulAssign:
3548 OpID = 3;
3549 IID = isSigned ? llvm::Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow :
3550 llvm::Intrinsic::umul_with_overflow;
3551 break;
3552 default:
3553 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported operation for overflow detection");
3554 }
3555 OpID <<= 1;
3556 if (isSigned)
3557 OpID |= 1;
3558
3559 CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
3560 llvm::Type *opTy = CGF.CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(Ops.Ty);
3561
3562 llvm::Function *intrinsic = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(IID, opTy);
3563
3564 Value *resultAndOverflow = Builder.CreateCall(intrinsic, {Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS});
3565 Value *result = Builder.CreateExtractValue(resultAndOverflow, 0);
3566 Value *overflow = Builder.CreateExtractValue(resultAndOverflow, 1);
3567
3568 // Handle overflow with llvm.trap if no custom handler has been specified.
3569 const std::string *handlerName =
3570 &CGF.getLangOpts().OverflowHandler;
3571 if (handlerName->empty()) {
3572 // If the signed-integer-overflow sanitizer is enabled, emit a call to its
3573 // runtime. Otherwise, this is a -ftrapv check, so just emit a trap.
3574 if (!isSigned || CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow)) {
3575 llvm::Value *NotOverflow = Builder.CreateNot(overflow);
3576 SanitizerMask Kind = isSigned ? SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow
3577 : SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow;
3578 EmitBinOpCheck(std::make_pair(NotOverflow, Kind), Ops);
3579 } else
3580 CGF.EmitTrapCheck(Builder.CreateNot(overflow));
3581 return result;
3582 }
3583
3584 // Branch in case of overflow.
3585 llvm::BasicBlock *initialBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3586 llvm::BasicBlock *continueBB =
3587 CGF.createBasicBlock("nooverflow", CGF.CurFn, initialBB->getNextNode());
3588 llvm::BasicBlock *overflowBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("overflow", CGF.CurFn);
3589
3590 Builder.CreateCondBr(overflow, overflowBB, continueBB);
3591
3592 // If an overflow handler is set, then we want to call it and then use its
3593 // result, if it returns.
3594 Builder.SetInsertPoint(overflowBB);
3595
3596 // Get the overflow handler.
3597 llvm::Type *Int8Ty = CGF.Int8Ty;
3598 llvm::Type *argTypes[] = { CGF.Int64Ty, CGF.Int64Ty, Int8Ty, Int8Ty };
3599 llvm::FunctionType *handlerTy =
3600 llvm::FunctionType::get(CGF.Int64Ty, argTypes, true);
3601 llvm::FunctionCallee handler =
3602 CGF.CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(handlerTy, *handlerName);
3603
3604 // Sign extend the args to 64-bit, so that we can use the same handler for
3605 // all types of overflow.
3606 llvm::Value *lhs = Builder.CreateSExt(Ops.LHS, CGF.Int64Ty);
3607 llvm::Value *rhs = Builder.CreateSExt(Ops.RHS, CGF.Int64Ty);
3608
3609 // Call the handler with the two arguments, the operation, and the size of
3610 // the result.
3611 llvm::Value *handlerArgs[] = {
3612 lhs,
3613 rhs,
3614 Builder.getInt8(OpID),
3615 Builder.getInt8(cast<llvm::IntegerType>(opTy)->getBitWidth())
3616 };
3617 llvm::Value *handlerResult =
3618 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(handler, handlerArgs);
3619
3620 // Truncate the result back to the desired size.
3621 handlerResult = Builder.CreateTrunc(handlerResult, opTy);
3622 Builder.CreateBr(continueBB);
3623
3624 Builder.SetInsertPoint(continueBB);
3625 llvm::PHINode *phi = Builder.CreatePHI(opTy, 2);
3626 phi->addIncoming(result, initialBB);
3627 phi->addIncoming(handlerResult, overflowBB);
3628
3629 return phi;
3630}
3631
3632/// Emit pointer + index arithmetic.
3633static Value *emitPointerArithmetic(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3634 const BinOpInfo &op,
3635 bool isSubtraction) {
3636 // FIXME: subobject-bounds
3637
3638 // Must have binary (not unary) expr here. Unary pointer
3639 // increment/decrement doesn't use this path.
3640 const BinaryOperator *expr = cast<BinaryOperator>(op.E);
3641
3642 Value *pointer = op.LHS;
3643 Expr *pointerOperand = expr->getLHS();
3644 Value *index = op.RHS;
3645 Expr *indexOperand = expr->getRHS();
3646
3647 // In a subtraction, the LHS is always the pointer.
3648 if (!isSubtraction && !pointerOperand->getType()->isAnyPointerType()) {
3649 std::swap(pointer, index);
3650 std::swap(pointerOperand, indexOperand);
3651 }
3652
3653 if (index->getType()->isPointerTy())
3654 index = CGF.getCapabilityIntegerValue(index);
3655
3656 bool isSigned = indexOperand->getType()->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
3657
3658 unsigned width = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(index->getType())->getBitWidth();
3659 auto &DL = CGF.CGM.getDataLayout();
3660 auto PtrTy = cast<llvm::PointerType>(pointer->getType());
3661
3662 // Some versions of glibc and gcc use idioms (particularly in their malloc
3663 // routines) that add a pointer-sized integer (known to be a pointer value)
3664 // to a null pointer in order to cast the value back to an integer or as
3665 // part of a pointer alignment algorithm. This is undefined behavior, but
3666 // we'd like to be able to compile programs that use it.
3667 //
3668 // Normally, we'd generate a GEP with a null-pointer base here in response
3669 // to that code, but it's also UB to dereference a pointer created that
3670 // way. Instead (as an acknowledged hack to tolerate the idiom) we will
3671 // generate a direct cast of the integer value to a pointer.
3672 //
3673 // The idiom (p = nullptr + N) is not met if any of the following are true:
3674 //
3675 // The operation is subtraction.
3676 // The index is not pointer-sized.
3677 // The pointer type is not byte-sized.
3678 //
3679 if (BinaryOperator::isNullPointerArithmeticExtension(CGF.getContext(),
3680 op.Opcode,
3681 expr->getLHS(),
3682 expr->getRHS()))
3683 return CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(index, pointer->getType());
3684
3685 if (width != DL.getTypeSizeInBits(PtrTy)) {
3686 // Zero-extend or sign-extend the pointer value according to
3687 // whether the index is signed or not.
3688 index = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(index, DL.getIntPtrType(PtrTy), isSigned,
3689 "idx.ext");
3690 }
3691
3692 // If this is subtraction, negate the index.
3693 if (isSubtraction)
3694 index = CGF.Builder.CreateNeg(index, "idx.neg");
3695
3696 if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds))
3697 CGF.EmitBoundsCheck(op.E, pointerOperand, index, indexOperand->getType(),
3698 /*Accessed*/ false);
3699
3700 const PointerType *pointerType
3701 = pointerOperand->getType()->getAs<PointerType>();
3702 if (!pointerType && !pointerOperand->getType()->isIntCapType()) {
3703 QualType objectType = pointerOperand->getType()
3704 ->castAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()
3705 ->getPointeeType();
3706 llvm::Value *objectSize
3707 = CGF.CGM.getSize(CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(objectType));
3708
3709 index = CGF.Builder.CreateMul(index, objectSize);
3710
3711 Value *result = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(pointer, CGF.VoidPtrTy);
3712 result = CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(result, index, "add.ptr");
3713 return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(result, pointer->getType());
3714 }
3715
3716 QualType elementType = pointerType->getPointeeType();
3717 if (const VariableArrayType *vla
3718 = CGF.getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(elementType)) {
3719 // The element count here is the total number of non-VLA elements.
3720 llvm::Value *numElements = CGF.getVLASize(vla).NumElts;
3721
3722 // Effectively, the multiply by the VLA size is part of the GEP.
3723 // GEP indexes are signed, and scaling an index isn't permitted to
3724 // signed-overflow, so we use the same semantics for our explicit
3725 // multiply. We suppress this if overflow is not undefined behavior.
3726 if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined()) {
3727 index = CGF.Builder.CreateMul(index, numElements, "vla.index");
3728 pointer = CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(pointer, index, "add.ptr");
3729 } else {
3730 index = CGF.Builder.CreateNSWMul(index, numElements, "vla.index");
3731 pointer =
3732 CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(pointer, index, isSigned, isSubtraction,
3733 op.E->getExprLoc(), "add.ptr");
3734 }
3735 return pointer;
3736 }
3737
3738 // Explicitly handle GNU void* and function pointer arithmetic extensions. The
3739 // GNU void* casts amount to no-ops since our void* type is i8*, but this is
3740 // future proof.
3741 if (elementType->isVoidType() || elementType->isFunctionType()) {
3742 Value *result = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(pointer,
3743 llvm::Type::getInt8PtrTy(CGF.getLLVMContext(),
3744 pointer->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace()));
3745 result = CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(result, index, "add.ptr");
3746 return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(result, pointer->getType());
3747 }
3748
3749 if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
3750 return CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(pointer, index, "add.ptr");
3751
3752 return CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(pointer, index, isSigned, isSubtraction,
3753 op.E->getExprLoc(), "add.ptr");
3754}
3755
3756// Construct an fmuladd intrinsic to represent a fused mul-add of MulOp and
3757// Addend. Use negMul and negAdd to negate the first operand of the Mul or
3758// the add operand respectively. This allows fmuladd to represent a*b-c, or
3759// c-a*b. Patterns in LLVM should catch the negated forms and translate them to
3760// efficient operations.
3761static Value* buildFMulAdd(llvm::BinaryOperator *MulOp, Value *Addend,
3762 const CodeGenFunction &CGF, CGBuilderTy &Builder,
3763 bool negMul, bool negAdd) {
3764 assert(!(negMul && negAdd) && "Only one of negMul and negAdd should be set.");
3765
3766 Value *MulOp0 = MulOp->getOperand(0);
3767 Value *MulOp1 = MulOp->getOperand(1);
3768 if (negMul) {
3769 MulOp0 =
3770 Builder.CreateFSub(
3771 llvm::ConstantFP::getZeroValueForNegation(MulOp0->getType()), MulOp0,
3772 "neg");
3773 } else if (negAdd) {
3774 Addend =
3775 Builder.CreateFSub(
3776 llvm::ConstantFP::getZeroValueForNegation(Addend->getType()), Addend,
3777 "neg");
3778 }
3779
3780 Value *FMulAdd = Builder.CreateCall(
3781 CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::fmuladd, Addend->getType()),
3782 {MulOp0, MulOp1, Addend});
3783 MulOp->eraseFromParent();
3784
3785 return FMulAdd;
3786}
3787
3788// Check whether it would be legal to emit an fmuladd intrinsic call to
3789// represent op and if so, build the fmuladd.
3790//
3791// Checks that (a) the operation is fusable, and (b) -ffp-contract=on.
3792// Does NOT check the type of the operation - it's assumed that this function
3793// will be called from contexts where it's known that the type is contractable.
3794static Value* tryEmitFMulAdd(const BinOpInfo &op,
3795 const CodeGenFunction &CGF, CGBuilderTy &Builder,
3796 bool isSub=false) {
3797
3798 assert((op.Opcode == BO_Add || op.Opcode == BO_AddAssign ||
3799 op.Opcode == BO_Sub || op.Opcode == BO_SubAssign) &&
3800 "Only fadd/fsub can be the root of an fmuladd.");
3801
3802 // Check whether this op is marked as fusable.
3803 if (!op.FPFeatures.allowFPContractWithinStatement())
3804 return nullptr;
3805
3806 // We have a potentially fusable op. Look for a mul on one of the operands.
3807 // Also, make sure that the mul result isn't used directly. In that case,
3808 // there's no point creating a muladd operation.
3809 if (auto *LHSBinOp = dyn_cast<llvm::BinaryOperator>(op.LHS)) {
3810 if (LHSBinOp->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::FMul &&
3811 LHSBinOp->use_empty())
3812 return buildFMulAdd(LHSBinOp, op.RHS, CGF, Builder, false, isSub);
3813 }
3814 if (auto *RHSBinOp = dyn_cast<llvm::BinaryOperator>(op.RHS)) {
3815 if (RHSBinOp->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::FMul &&
3816 RHSBinOp->use_empty())
3817 return buildFMulAdd(RHSBinOp, op.LHS, CGF, Builder, isSub, false);
3818 }
3819
3820 return nullptr;
3821}
3822
3823Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitAdd(const BinOpInfo &op) {
3824 const BinaryOperator *expr = cast<BinaryOperator>(op.E);
3825 if (expr->getLHS()->getType()->isAnyPointerType() ||
3826 expr->getRHS()->getType()->isAnyPointerType())
3827 return emitPointerArithmetic(CGF, op, CodeGenFunction::NotSubtraction);
3828
3829 if (op.Ty->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType()) {
3830 switch (CGF.getLangOpts().getSignedOverflowBehavior()) {
3831 case LangOptions::SOB_Defined:
3832 return Builder.CreateAdd(op.LHS, op.RHS, "add");
3833 case LangOptions::SOB_Undefined:
3834 if (!CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow))
3835 return Builder.CreateNSWAdd(op.LHS, op.RHS, "add");
3836 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
3837 case LangOptions::SOB_Trapping:
3838 if (CanElideOverflowCheck(CGF.getContext(), op))
3839 return Builder.CreateNSWAdd(op.LHS, op.RHS, "add");
3840 return EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(op);
3841 }
3842 }
3843
3844 if (op.Ty->isUnsignedIntegerType() &&
3845 CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow) &&
3846 !CanElideOverflowCheck(CGF.getContext(), op))
3847 return EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(op);
3848
3849 if (op.LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
3850 // Try to form an fmuladd.
3851 if (Value *FMulAdd = tryEmitFMulAdd(op, CGF, Builder))
3852 return FMulAdd;
3853
3854 Value *V = Builder.CreateFAdd(op.LHS, op.RHS, "add");
3855 return propagateFMFlags(V, op);
3856 }
3857
3858 if (op.isFixedPointBinOp())
3859 return EmitFixedPointBinOp(op);
3860
3861 return Builder.CreateAdd(op.LHS, op.RHS, "add");
3862}
3863
3864/// The resulting value must be calculated with exact precision, so the operands
3865/// may not be the same type.
3866Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitFixedPointBinOp(const BinOpInfo &op) {
3867 using llvm::APSInt;
3868 using llvm::ConstantInt;
3869
3870 const auto *BinOp = cast<BinaryOperator>(op.E);
3871
3872 // The result is a fixed point type and at least one of the operands is fixed
3873 // point while the other is either fixed point or an int. This resulting type
3874 // should be determined by Sema::handleFixedPointConversions().
3875 QualType ResultTy = op.Ty;
3876 QualType LHSTy = BinOp->getLHS()->getType();
3877 QualType RHSTy = BinOp->getRHS()->getType();
3878 ASTContext &Ctx = CGF.getContext();
3879 Value *LHS = op.LHS;
3880 Value *RHS = op.RHS;
3881
3882 auto LHSFixedSema = Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(LHSTy);
3883 auto RHSFixedSema = Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(RHSTy);
3884 auto ResultFixedSema = Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(ResultTy);
3885 auto CommonFixedSema = LHSFixedSema.getCommonSemantics(RHSFixedSema);
3886
3887 // Convert the operands to the full precision type.
3888 Value *FullLHS = EmitFixedPointConversion(LHS, LHSFixedSema, CommonFixedSema,
3889 BinOp->getExprLoc());
3890 Value *FullRHS = EmitFixedPointConversion(RHS, RHSFixedSema, CommonFixedSema,
3891 BinOp->getExprLoc());
3892
3893 // Perform the actual addition.
3894 Value *Result;
3895 switch (BinOp->getOpcode()) {
3896 case BO_Add: {
3897 if (ResultFixedSema.isSaturated()) {
3898 llvm::Intrinsic::ID IID = ResultFixedSema.isSigned()
3899 ? llvm::Intrinsic::sadd_sat
3900 : llvm::Intrinsic::uadd_sat;
3901 Result = Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(IID, FullLHS, FullRHS);
3902 } else {
3903 Result = Builder.CreateAdd(FullLHS, FullRHS);
3904 }
3905 break;
3906 }
3907 case BO_Sub: {
3908 if (ResultFixedSema.isSaturated()) {
3909 llvm::Intrinsic::ID IID = ResultFixedSema.isSigned()
3910 ? llvm::Intrinsic::ssub_sat
3911 : llvm::Intrinsic::usub_sat;
3912 Result = Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(IID, FullLHS, FullRHS);
3913 } else {
3914 Result = Builder.CreateSub(FullLHS, FullRHS);
3915 }
3916 break;
3917 }
3918 case BO_LT:
3919 return CommonFixedSema.isSigned() ? Builder.CreateICmpSLT(FullLHS, FullRHS)
3920 : Builder.CreateICmpULT(FullLHS, FullRHS);
3921 case BO_GT:
3922 return CommonFixedSema.isSigned() ? Builder.CreateICmpSGT(FullLHS, FullRHS)
3923 : Builder.CreateICmpUGT(FullLHS, FullRHS);
3924 case BO_LE:
3925 return CommonFixedSema.isSigned() ? Builder.CreateICmpSLE(FullLHS, FullRHS)
3926 : Builder.CreateICmpULE(FullLHS, FullRHS);
3927 case BO_GE:
3928 return CommonFixedSema.isSigned() ? Builder.CreateICmpSGE(FullLHS, FullRHS)
3929 : Builder.CreateICmpUGE(FullLHS, FullRHS);
3930 case BO_EQ:
3931 // For equality operations, we assume any padding bits on unsigned types are
3932 // zero'd out. They could be overwritten through non-saturating operations
3933 // that cause overflow, but this leads to undefined behavior.
3934 return Builder.CreateICmpEQ(FullLHS, FullRHS);
3935 case BO_NE:
3936 return Builder.CreateICmpNE(FullLHS, FullRHS);
3937 case BO_Mul:
3938 case BO_Div:
3939 case BO_Shl:
3940 case BO_Shr:
3941 case BO_Cmp:
3942 case BO_LAnd:
3943 case BO_LOr:
3944 case BO_MulAssign:
3945 case BO_DivAssign:
3946 case BO_AddAssign:
3947 case BO_SubAssign:
3948 case BO_ShlAssign:
3949 case BO_ShrAssign:
3950 llvm_unreachable("Found unimplemented fixed point binary operation");
3951 case BO_PtrMemD:
3952 case BO_PtrMemI:
3953 case BO_Rem:
3954 case BO_Xor:
3955 case BO_And:
3956 case BO_Or:
3957 case BO_Assign:
3958 case BO_RemAssign:
3959 case BO_AndAssign:
3960 case BO_XorAssign:
3961 case BO_OrAssign:
3962 case BO_Comma:
3963 llvm_unreachable("Found unsupported binary operation for fixed point types.");
3964 }
3965
3966 // Convert to the result type.
3967 return EmitFixedPointConversion(Result, CommonFixedSema, ResultFixedSema,
3968 BinOp->getExprLoc());
3969}
3970
3971Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitSub(const BinOpInfo &op) {
3972 auto RHSExpr = isa<BinaryOperator>(op.E)
3973 ? cast<BinaryOperator>(op.E)->getRHS()
3974 : nullptr;
3975 if (RHSExpr && RHSExpr->getType()->isIntCapType()) {
3976 const bool IsAddrMode = CGF.CGM.getLangOpts().cheriUIntCapUsesAddr();
3977 // Subtraction of __intcap_t is ambiguous: could be pointer
3978 // increment/decrement or pointer difference
3979 auto LHSExpr = cast<BinaryOperator>(op.E)->getLHS();
3980 // However, we can avoid emitting this warning in address interpretation
3981 // if the LHS is an non-capability integer that was promoted to __intcap_t
3982 // since it will always yield an untagged capability with the correct value
3983 // TODO: should avoid the getaddr/setaddr calls in codegen for this case
3984 QualType LhsRealType = LHSExpr->IgnoreImplicit()->getType();
3985 bool ShouldWarn =
3986 op.Ty->isIntCapType() && (!IsAddrMode || LhsRealType->isIntCapType());
3987 QualType RhsRealType = RHSExpr->IgnoreImplicit()->getType();
3988 if (ShouldWarn && RhsRealType->isIntCapType()) {
3989 CGF.CGM.getDiags().Report(op.E->getExprLoc(),
3990 diag::warn_uintcap_add_subtract)
3991 << /* subtraction */ 1 << RhsRealType << LhsRealType << IsAddrMode
3992 << op.E->getSourceRange();
3993 CGF.CGM.getDiags().Report(RHSExpr->getExprLoc(),
3994 diag::note_uintcap_subtract);
3995 }
3996 // In offset interpretation subtracting an __intcap_t from a pointer may
3997 // also yield the wrong result since only the offset is subtracted.
3998 if (!IsAddrMode && op.Ty->isPointerType() && RhsRealType->isIntCapType()) {
3999 CGF.CGM.getDiags().Report(op.E->getExprLoc(),
4000 diag::warn_ptr_uintcap_subtract_offset_mode)
4001 << /* subtraction */ 1 << RhsRealType << op.Ty
4002 << op.E->getSourceRange();
4003 }
4004 // TODO: warn about inefficient code generation?
4005 }
4006
4007 // The LHS is always a pointer if either side is.
4008 if (!op.LHS->getType()->isPointerTy()) {
4009 if (op.Ty->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType()) {
4010 switch (CGF.getLangOpts().getSignedOverflowBehavior()) {
4011 case LangOptions::SOB_Defined:
4012 return Builder.CreateSub(op.LHS, op.RHS, "sub");
4013 case LangOptions::SOB_Undefined:
4014 if (!CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow))
4015 return Builder.CreateNSWSub(op.LHS, op.RHS, "sub");
4016 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4017 case LangOptions::SOB_Trapping:
4018 if (CanElideOverflowCheck(CGF.getContext(), op))
4019 return Builder.CreateNSWSub(op.LHS, op.RHS, "sub");
4020 return EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(op);
4021 }
4022 }
4023
4024 if (op.Ty->isUnsignedIntegerType() &&
4025 CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow) &&
4026 !CanElideOverflowCheck(CGF.getContext(), op))
4027 return EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(op);
4028
4029 if (op.LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
4030 // Try to form an fmuladd.
4031 if (Value *FMulAdd = tryEmitFMulAdd(op, CGF, Builder, true))
4032 return FMulAdd;
4033 Value *V = Builder.CreateFSub(op.LHS, op.RHS, "sub");
4034 return propagateFMFlags(V, op);
4035 }
4036
4037 if (op.isFixedPointBinOp())
4038 return EmitFixedPointBinOp(op);
4039
4040 return Builder.CreateSub(op.LHS, op.RHS, "sub");
4041 }
4042
4043 // If the RHS is not a pointer, then we have normal pointer
4044 // arithmetic.
4045 if (!cast<BinaryOperator>(op.E)->getRHS()->getType()->isPointerType())
4046 return emitPointerArithmetic(CGF, op, CodeGenFunction::IsSubtraction);
4047
4048 // Otherwise, this is a pointer subtraction.
4049
4050 const BinaryOperator *expr = cast<BinaryOperator>(op.E);
4051 // Do the raw subtraction part.
4052 llvm::Value *LHS = op.LHS;
4053 llvm::Value *RHS = op.RHS;
4054 Value *diffInChars;
4055 if (expr->getLHS()->getType()->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.getContext())) {
4056 llvm::Function *CapPtrDiff =
4057 CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_cap_diff, CGF.PtrDiffTy);
4058 llvm::Type *CapTy = CapPtrDiff->getFunctionType()->getParamType(0);
4059 LHS = Builder.CreateBitCast(LHS, CapTy);
4060 RHS = Builder.CreateBitCast(RHS, CapTy);
4061 diffInChars = Builder.CreateCall(CapPtrDiff, { LHS, RHS});
4062 } else {
4063 LHS = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(op.LHS, CGF.PtrDiffTy, "sub.ptr.lhs.cast");
4064 RHS = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(op.RHS, CGF.PtrDiffTy, "sub.ptr.rhs.cast");
4065 diffInChars = Builder.CreateSub(LHS, RHS, "sub.ptr.sub");
4066 }
4067
4068 // Okay, figure out the element size.
4069 QualType elementType = expr->getLHS()->getType()->getPointeeType();
4070
4071 llvm::Value *divisor = nullptr;
4072
4073 // For a variable-length array, this is going to be non-constant.
4074 if (const VariableArrayType *vla
4075 = CGF.getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(elementType)) {
4076 auto VlaSize = CGF.getVLASize(vla);
4077 elementType = VlaSize.Type;
4078 divisor = VlaSize.NumElts;
4079
4080 // Scale the number of non-VLA elements by the non-VLA element size.
4081 CharUnits eltSize = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(elementType);
4082 if (!eltSize.isOne())
4083 divisor = CGF.Builder.CreateNUWMul(CGF.CGM.getSize(eltSize), divisor);
4084
4085 // For everything elese, we can just compute it, safe in the
4086 // assumption that Sema won't let anything through that we can't
4087 // safely compute the size of.
4088 } else {
4089 CharUnits elementSize;
4090 // Handle GCC extension for pointer arithmetic on void* and
4091 // function pointer types.
4092 if (elementType->isVoidType() || elementType->isFunctionType())
4093 elementSize = CharUnits::One();
4094 else
4095 elementSize = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(elementType);
4096
4097 // Don't even emit the divide for element size of 1.
4098 if (elementSize.isOne())
4099 return diffInChars;
4100
4101 divisor = CGF.CGM.getSize(elementSize);
4102 }
4103
4104 // Otherwise, do a full sdiv. This uses the "exact" form of sdiv, since
4105 // pointer difference in C is only defined in the case where both operands
4106 // are pointing to elements of an array.
4107 return Builder.CreateExactSDiv(diffInChars, divisor, "sub.ptr.div");
4108}
4109
4110Value *ScalarExprEmitter::GetWidthMinusOneValue(Value* LHS,Value* RHS) {
4111 llvm::IntegerType *Ty;
4112 if (llvm::VectorType *VT = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(LHS->getType()))
4113 Ty = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(VT->getElementType());
4114 else
4115 Ty = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(LHS->getType());
4116 return llvm::ConstantInt::get(RHS->getType(), Ty->getBitWidth() - 1);
4117}
4118
4119Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitShl(const BinOpInfo &Ops) {
4120 // LLVM requires the LHS and RHS to be the same type: promote or truncate the
4121 // RHS to the same size as the LHS.
4122 Value *RHS = Ops.RHS;
4123 if (RHS->getType()->isPointerTy())
4124 RHS = CGF.getCapabilityIntegerValue(RHS);
4125 if (Ops.LHS->getType() != RHS->getType())
4126 RHS = Builder.CreateIntCast(RHS, Ops.LHS->getType(), false, "sh_prom");
4127
4128 bool SanitizeBase = CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ShiftBase) &&
4129 Ops.Ty->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation() &&
4130 !CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined();
4131 bool SanitizeExponent = CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ShiftExponent);
4132 // OpenCL 6.3j: shift values are effectively % word size of LHS.
4133 if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenCL)
4134 RHS =
4135 Builder.CreateAnd(RHS, GetWidthMinusOneValue(Ops.LHS, RHS), "shl.mask");
4136 else if ((SanitizeBase || SanitizeExponent) &&
4137 isa<llvm::IntegerType>(Ops.LHS->getType())) {
4138 CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
4139 SmallVector<std::pair<Value *, SanitizerMask>, 2> Checks;
4140 llvm::Value *WidthMinusOne = GetWidthMinusOneValue(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS);
4141 llvm::Value *ValidExponent = Builder.CreateICmpULE(Ops.RHS, WidthMinusOne);
4142
4143 if (SanitizeExponent) {
4144 Checks.push_back(
4145 std::make_pair(ValidExponent, SanitizerKind::ShiftExponent));
4146 }
4147
4148 if (SanitizeBase) {
4149 // Check whether we are shifting any non-zero bits off the top of the
4150 // integer. We only emit this check if exponent is valid - otherwise
4151 // instructions below will have undefined behavior themselves.
4152 llvm::BasicBlock *Orig = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
4153 llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = CGF.createBasicBlock("cont");
4154 llvm::BasicBlock *CheckShiftBase = CGF.createBasicBlock("check");
4155 Builder.CreateCondBr(ValidExponent, CheckShiftBase, Cont);
4156 llvm::Value *PromotedWidthMinusOne =
4157 (RHS == Ops.RHS) ? WidthMinusOne
4158 : GetWidthMinusOneValue(Ops.LHS, RHS);
4159 CGF.EmitBlock(CheckShiftBase);
4160 llvm::Value *BitsShiftedOff = Builder.CreateLShr(
4161 Ops.LHS, Builder.CreateSub(PromotedWidthMinusOne, RHS, "shl.zeros",
4162 /*NUW*/ true, /*NSW*/ true),
4163 "shl.check");
4164 if (CGF.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
4165 // In C99, we are not permitted to shift a 1 bit into the sign bit.
4166 // Under C++11's rules, shifting a 1 bit into the sign bit is
4167 // OK, but shifting a 1 bit out of it is not. (C89 and C++03 don't
4168 // define signed left shifts, so we use the C99 and C++11 rules there).
4169 llvm::Value *One = llvm::ConstantInt::get(BitsShiftedOff->getType(), 1);
4170 BitsShiftedOff = Builder.CreateLShr(BitsShiftedOff, One);
4171 }
4172 llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::ConstantInt::get(BitsShiftedOff->getType(), 0);
4173 llvm::Value *ValidBase = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(BitsShiftedOff, Zero);
4174 CGF.EmitBlock(Cont);
4175 llvm::PHINode *BaseCheck = Builder.CreatePHI(ValidBase->getType(), 2);
4176 BaseCheck->addIncoming(Builder.getTrue(), Orig);
4177 BaseCheck->addIncoming(ValidBase, CheckShiftBase);
4178 Checks.push_back(std::make_pair(BaseCheck, SanitizerKind::ShiftBase));
4179 }
4180
4181 assert(!Checks.empty());
4182 EmitBinOpCheck(Checks, Ops);
4183 }
4184
4185 return Builder.CreateShl(Ops.LHS, RHS, "shl");
4186}
4187
4188Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitShr(const BinOpInfo &Ops) {
4189 // LLVM requires the LHS and RHS to be the same type: promote or truncate the
4190 // RHS to the same size as the LHS.
4191 Value *RHS = Ops.RHS;
4192 if (RHS->getType()->isPointerTy())
4193 RHS = CGF.getCapabilityIntegerValue(RHS);
4194 if (Ops.LHS->getType() != RHS->getType())
4195 RHS = Builder.CreateIntCast(RHS, Ops.LHS->getType(), false, "sh_prom");
4196
4197 // OpenCL 6.3j: shift values are effectively % word size of LHS.
4198 if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenCL)
4199 RHS =
4200 Builder.CreateAnd(RHS, GetWidthMinusOneValue(Ops.LHS, RHS), "shr.mask");
4201 else if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ShiftExponent) &&
4202 isa<llvm::IntegerType>(Ops.LHS->getType())) {
4203 CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
4204 llvm::Value *Valid =
4205 Builder.CreateICmpULE(RHS, GetWidthMinusOneValue(Ops.LHS, RHS));
4206 EmitBinOpCheck(std::make_pair(Valid, SanitizerKind::ShiftExponent), Ops);
4207 }
4208
4209 if (Ops.Ty->hasUnsignedIntegerRepresentation())
4210 return Builder.CreateLShr(Ops.LHS, RHS, "shr");
4211 return Builder.CreateAShr(Ops.LHS, RHS, "shr");
4212}
4213
4214enum IntrinsicType { VCMPEQ, VCMPGT };
4215// return corresponding comparison intrinsic for given vector type
4216static llvm::Intrinsic::ID GetIntrinsic(IntrinsicType IT,
4217 BuiltinType::Kind ElemKind) {
4218 switch (ElemKind) {
4219 default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected element type");
4220 case BuiltinType::Char_U:
4221 case BuiltinType::UChar:
4222 return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequb_p :
4223 llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtub_p;
4224 case BuiltinType::Char_S:
4225 case BuiltinType::SChar:
4226 return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequb_p :
4227 llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtsb_p;
4228 case BuiltinType::UShort:
4229 return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequh_p :
4230 llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtuh_p;
4231 case BuiltinType::Short:
4232 return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequh_p :
4233 llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtsh_p;
4234 case BuiltinType::UInt:
4235 return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequw_p :
4236 llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtuw_p;
4237 case BuiltinType::Int:
4238 return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequw_p :
4239 llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtsw_p;
4240 case BuiltinType::ULong:
4241 case BuiltinType::ULongLong:
4242 return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequd_p :
4243 llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtud_p;
4244 case BuiltinType::Long:
4245 case BuiltinType::LongLong:
4246 return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequd_p :
4247 llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtsd_p;
4248 case BuiltinType::Float:
4249 return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpeqfp_p :
4250 llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtfp_p;
4251 case BuiltinType::Double:
4252 return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_xvcmpeqdp_p :
4253 llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_xvcmpgtdp_p;
4254 }
4255}
4256
4257Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitCompare(const BinaryOperator *E,
4258 llvm::CmpInst::Predicate UICmpOpc,
4259 llvm::CmpInst::Predicate SICmpOpc,
4260 llvm::CmpInst::Predicate FCmpOpc) {
4261 TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
4262 Value *Result;
4263 QualType LHSTy = E->getLHS()->getType();
4264 QualType RHSTy = E->getRHS()->getType();
4265 if (const MemberPointerType *MPT = LHSTy->getAs<MemberPointerType>()) {
4266 assert(E->getOpcode() == BO_EQ ||
4267 E->getOpcode() == BO_NE);
4268 Value *LHS = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getLHS());
4269 Value *RHS = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getRHS());
4270 Result = CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberPointerComparison(
4271 CGF, LHS, RHS, MPT, E->getOpcode() == BO_NE);
4272 } else if (!LHSTy->isAnyComplexType() && !RHSTy->isAnyComplexType()) {
4273 BinOpInfo BOInfo = EmitBinOps(E);
4274 Value *LHS = BOInfo.LHS;
4275 Value *RHS = BOInfo.RHS;
4276
4277 // If AltiVec, the comparison results in a numeric type, so we use
4278 // intrinsics comparing vectors and giving 0 or 1 as a result
4279 if (LHSTy->isVectorType() && !E->getType()->isVectorType()) {
4280 // constants for mapping CR6 register bits to predicate result
4281 enum { CR6_EQ=0, CR6_EQ_REV, CR6_LT, CR6_LT_REV } CR6;
4282
4283 llvm::Intrinsic::ID ID = llvm::Intrinsic::not_intrinsic;
4284
4285 // in several cases vector arguments order will be reversed
4286 Value *FirstVecArg = LHS,
4287 *SecondVecArg = RHS;
4288
4289 QualType ElTy = LHSTy->getAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
4290 const BuiltinType *BTy = ElTy->getAs<BuiltinType>();
4291 BuiltinType::Kind ElementKind = BTy->getKind();
4292
4293 switch(E->getOpcode()) {
4294 default: llvm_unreachable("is not a comparison operation");
4295 case BO_EQ:
4296 CR6 = CR6_LT;
4297 ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPEQ, ElementKind);
4298 break;
4299 case BO_NE:
4300 CR6 = CR6_EQ;
4301 ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPEQ, ElementKind);
4302 break;
4303 case BO_LT:
4304 CR6 = CR6_LT;
4305 ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPGT, ElementKind);
4306 std::swap(FirstVecArg, SecondVecArg);
4307 break;
4308 case BO_GT:
4309 CR6 = CR6_LT;
4310 ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPGT, ElementKind);
4311 break;
4312 case BO_LE:
4313 if (ElementKind == BuiltinType::Float) {
4314 CR6 = CR6_LT;
4315 ID = llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgefp_p;
4316 std::swap(FirstVecArg, SecondVecArg);
4317 }
4318 else {
4319 CR6 = CR6_EQ;
4320 ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPGT, ElementKind);
4321 }
4322 break;
4323 case BO_GE:
4324 if (ElementKind == BuiltinType::Float) {
4325 CR6 = CR6_LT;
4326 ID = llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgefp_p;
4327 }
4328 else {
4329 CR6 = CR6_EQ;
4330 ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPGT, ElementKind);
4331 std::swap(FirstVecArg, SecondVecArg);
4332 }
4333 break;
4334 }
4335
4336 Value *CR6Param = Builder.getInt32(CR6);
4337 llvm::Function *F = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(ID);
4338 Result = Builder.CreateCall(F, {CR6Param, FirstVecArg, SecondVecArg});
4339
4340 // The result type of intrinsic may not be same as E->getType().
4341 // If E->getType() is not BoolTy, EmitScalarConversion will do the
4342 // conversion work. If E->getType() is BoolTy, EmitScalarConversion will
4343 // do nothing, if ResultTy is not i1 at the same time, it will cause
4344 // crash later.
4345 llvm::IntegerType *ResultTy = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(Result->getType());
4346 if (ResultTy->getBitWidth() > 1 &&
4347 E->getType() == CGF.getContext().BoolTy)
4348 Result = Builder.CreateTrunc(Result, Builder.getInt1Ty());
4349 return EmitScalarConversion(Result, CGF.getContext().BoolTy, E->getType(),
4350 E->getExprLoc());
4351 }
4352
4353 if (BOInfo.isFixedPointBinOp()) {
4354 Result = EmitFixedPointBinOp(BOInfo);
4355 } else if (LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
4356 Result = Builder.CreateFCmp(FCmpOpc, LHS, RHS, "cmp");
4357 } else if (LHSTy->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation()) {
4358 Result = Builder.CreateICmp(SICmpOpc, LHS, RHS, "cmp");
4359 } else {
4360 // Unsigned integers and pointers.
4361
4362 if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers &&
4363 !isa<llvm::ConstantPointerNull>(LHS) &&
4364 !isa<llvm::ConstantPointerNull>(RHS)) {
4365
4366 // Dynamic information is required to be stripped for comparisons,
4367 // because it could leak the dynamic information. Based on comparisons
4368 // of pointers to dynamic objects, the optimizer can replace one pointer
4369 // with another, which might be incorrect in presence of invariant
4370 // groups. Comparison with null is safe because null does not carry any
4371 // dynamic information.
4372 if (LHSTy.mayBeDynamicClass())
4373 LHS = Builder.CreateStripInvariantGroup(LHS);
4374 if (RHSTy.mayBeDynamicClass())
4375 RHS = Builder.CreateStripInvariantGroup(RHS);
4376 }
4377
4378 Result = Builder.CreateICmp(UICmpOpc, LHS, RHS, "cmp");
4379 }
4380
4381 // If this is a vector comparison, sign extend the result to the appropriate
4382 // vector integer type and return it (don't convert to bool).
4383 if (LHSTy->isVectorType())
4384 return Builder.CreateSExt(Result, ConvertType(E->getType()), "sext");
4385
4386 } else {
4387 // Complex Comparison: can only be an equality comparison.
4388 CodeGenFunction::ComplexPairTy LHS, RHS;
4389 QualType CETy;
4390 if (auto *CTy = LHSTy->getAs<ComplexType>()) {
4391 LHS = CGF.EmitComplexExpr(E->getLHS());
4392 CETy = CTy->getElementType();
4393 } else {
4394 LHS.first = Visit(E->getLHS());
4395 LHS.second = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(LHS.first->getType());
4396 CETy = LHSTy;
4397 }
4398 if (auto *CTy = RHSTy->getAs<ComplexType>()) {
4399 RHS = CGF.EmitComplexExpr(E->getRHS());
4400 assert(CGF.getContext().hasSameUnqualifiedType(CETy,
4401 CTy->getElementType()) &&
4402 "The element types must always match.");
4403 (void)CTy;
4404 } else {
4405 RHS.first = Visit(E->getRHS());
4406 RHS.second = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(RHS.first->getType());
4407 assert(CGF.getContext().hasSameUnqualifiedType(CETy, RHSTy) &&
4408 "The element types must always match.");
4409 }
4410
4411 Value *ResultR, *ResultI;
4412 if (CETy->isRealFloatingType()) {
4413 ResultR = Builder.CreateFCmp(FCmpOpc, LHS.first, RHS.first, "cmp.r");
4414 ResultI = Builder.CreateFCmp(FCmpOpc, LHS.second, RHS.second, "cmp.i");
4415 } else {
4416 // Complex comparisons can only be equality comparisons. As such, signed
4417 // and unsigned opcodes are the same.
4418 ResultR = Builder.CreateICmp(UICmpOpc, LHS.first, RHS.first, "cmp.r");
4419 ResultI = Builder.CreateICmp(UICmpOpc, LHS.second, RHS.second, "cmp.i");
4420 }
4421
4422 if (E->getOpcode() == BO_EQ) {
4423 Result = Builder.CreateAnd(ResultR, ResultI, "and.ri");
4424 } else {
4425 assert(E->getOpcode() == BO_NE &&
4426 "Complex comparison other than == or != ?");
4427 Result = Builder.CreateOr(ResultR, ResultI, "or.ri");
4428 }
4429 }
4430
4431 return EmitScalarConversion(Result, CGF.getContext().BoolTy, E->getType(),
4432 E->getExprLoc());
4433}
4434
4435Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitBinAssign(const BinaryOperator *E) {
4436 bool Ignore = TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
4437
4438 Value *RHS;
4439 LValue LHS;
4440
4441 switch (E->getLHS()->getType().getObjCLifetime()) {
4442 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
4443 std::tie(LHS, RHS) = CGF.EmitARCStoreStrong(E, Ignore);
4444 break;
4445
4446 case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
4447 std::tie(LHS, RHS) = CGF.EmitARCStoreAutoreleasing(E);
4448 break;
4449
4450 case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
4451 std::tie(LHS, RHS) = CGF.EmitARCStoreUnsafeUnretained(E, Ignore);
4452 break;
4453
4454 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
4455 RHS = Visit(E->getRHS());
4456 LHS = EmitCheckedLValue(E->getLHS(), CodeGenFunction::TCK_Store);
4457 RHS = CGF.EmitARCStoreWeak(LHS.getAddress(), RHS, Ignore);
4458 break;
4459
4460 case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
4461 // __block variables need to have the rhs evaluated first, plus
4462 // this should improve codegen just a little.
4463 RHS = Visit(E->getRHS());
4464 LHS = EmitCheckedLValue(E->getLHS(), CodeGenFunction::TCK_Store);
4465
4466 // Store the value into the LHS. Bit-fields are handled specially
4467 // because the result is altered by the store, i.e., [C99 6.5.16p1]
4468 // 'An assignment expression has the value of the left operand after
4469 // the assignment...'.
4470 if (LHS.isBitField()) {
4471 CGF.EmitStoreThroughBitfieldLValue(RValue::get(RHS), LHS, &RHS);
4472 } else {
4473 CGF.EmitNullabilityCheck(LHS, RHS, E->getExprLoc());
4474 CGF.EmitStoreThroughLValue(RValue::get(RHS), LHS);
4475 }
4476 }
4477
4478 // If the result is clearly ignored, return now.
4479 if (Ignore)
4480 return nullptr;
4481
4482 // The result of an assignment in C is the assigned r-value.
4483 if (!CGF.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
4484 return RHS;
4485
4486 // If the lvalue is non-volatile, return the computed value of the assignment.
4487 if (!LHS.isVolatileQualified())
4488 return RHS;
4489
4490 // Otherwise, reload the value.
4491 return EmitLoadOfLValue(LHS, E->getExprLoc());
4492}
4493
4494Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitBinLAnd(const BinaryOperator *E) {
4495 // Perform vector logical and on comparisons with zero vectors.
4496 if (E->getType()->isVectorType()) {
4497 CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4498
4499 Value *LHS = Visit(E->getLHS());
4500 Value *RHS = Visit(E->getRHS());
4501 Value *Zero = llvm::ConstantAggregateZero::get(LHS->getType());
4502 if (LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
4503 LHS = Builder.CreateFCmp(llvm::CmpInst::FCMP_UNE, LHS, Zero, "cmp");
4504 RHS = Builder.CreateFCmp(llvm::CmpInst::FCMP_UNE, RHS, Zero, "cmp");
4505 } else {
4506 LHS = Builder.CreateICmp(llvm::CmpInst::ICMP_NE, LHS, Zero, "cmp");
4507 RHS = Builder.CreateICmp(llvm::CmpInst::ICMP_NE, RHS, Zero, "cmp");
4508 }
4509 Value *And = Builder.CreateAnd(LHS, RHS);
4510 return Builder.CreateSExt(And, ConvertType(E->getType()), "sext");
4511 }
4512
4513 llvm::Type *ResTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
4514
4515 // If we have 0 && RHS, see if we can elide RHS, if so, just return 0.
4516 // If we have 1 && X, just emit X without inserting the control flow.
4517 bool LHSCondVal;
4518 if (CGF.ConstantFoldsToSimpleInteger(E->getLHS(), LHSCondVal)) {
4519 if (LHSCondVal) { // If we have 1 && X, just emit X.
4520 CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4521
4522 Value *RHSCond = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(E->getRHS());
4523 // ZExt result to int or bool.
4524 return Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(RHSCond, ResTy, "land.ext");
4525 }
4526
4527 // 0 && RHS: If it is safe, just elide the RHS, and return 0/false.
4528 if (!CGF.ContainsLabel(E->getRHS()))
4529 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ResTy);
4530 }
4531
4532 llvm::BasicBlock *ContBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("land.end");
4533 llvm::BasicBlock *RHSBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("land.rhs");
4534
4535 CodeGenFunction::ConditionalEvaluation eval(CGF);
4536
4537 // Branch on the LHS first. If it is false, go to the failure (cont) block.
4538 CGF.EmitBranchOnBoolExpr(E->getLHS(), RHSBlock, ContBlock,
4539 CGF.getProfileCount(E->getRHS()));
4540
4541 // Any edges into the ContBlock are now from an (indeterminate number of)
4542 // edges from this first condition. All of these values will be false. Start
4543 // setting up the PHI node in the Cont Block for this.
4544 llvm::PHINode *PN = llvm::PHINode::Create(llvm::Type::getInt1Ty(VMContext), 2,
4545 "", ContBlock);
4546 for (llvm::pred_iterator PI = pred_begin(ContBlock), PE = pred_end(ContBlock);
4547 PI != PE; ++PI)
4548 PN->addIncoming(llvm::ConstantInt::getFalse(VMContext), *PI);
4549
4550 eval.begin(CGF);
4551 CGF.EmitBlock(RHSBlock);
4552 CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4553 Value *RHSCond = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(E->getRHS());
4554 eval.end(CGF);
4555
4556 // Reaquire the RHS block, as there may be subblocks inserted.
4557 RHSBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
4558
4559 // Emit an unconditional branch from this block to ContBlock.
4560 {
4561 // There is no need to emit line number for unconditional branch.
4562 auto NL = ApplyDebugLocation::CreateEmpty(CGF);
4563 CGF.EmitBlock(ContBlock);
4564 }
4565 // Insert an entry into the phi node for the edge with the value of RHSCond.
4566 PN->addIncoming(RHSCond, RHSBlock);
4567
4568 // Artificial location to preserve the scope information
4569 {
4570 auto NL = ApplyDebugLocation::CreateArtificial(CGF);
4571 PN->setDebugLoc(Builder.getCurrentDebugLocation());
4572 }
4573
4574 // ZExt result to int.
4575 return Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(PN, ResTy, "land.ext");
4576}
4577
4578Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitBinLOr(const BinaryOperator *E) {
4579 // Perform vector logical or on comparisons with zero vectors.
4580 if (E->getType()->isVectorType()) {
4581 CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4582
4583 Value *LHS = Visit(E->getLHS());
4584 Value *RHS = Visit(E->getRHS());
4585 Value *Zero = llvm::ConstantAggregateZero::get(LHS->getType());
4586 if (LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
4587 LHS = Builder.CreateFCmp(llvm::CmpInst::FCMP_UNE, LHS, Zero, "cmp");
4588 RHS = Builder.CreateFCmp(llvm::CmpInst::FCMP_UNE, RHS, Zero, "cmp");
4589 } else {
4590 LHS = Builder.CreateICmp(llvm::CmpInst::ICMP_NE, LHS, Zero, "cmp");
4591 RHS = Builder.CreateICmp(llvm::CmpInst::ICMP_NE, RHS, Zero, "cmp");
4592 }
4593 Value *Or = Builder.CreateOr(LHS, RHS);
4594 return Builder.CreateSExt(Or, ConvertType(E->getType()), "sext");
4595 }
4596
4597 llvm::Type *ResTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
4598
4599 // If we have 1 || RHS, see if we can elide RHS, if so, just return 1.
4600 // If we have 0 || X, just emit X without inserting the control flow.
4601 bool LHSCondVal;
4602 if (CGF.ConstantFoldsToSimpleInteger(E->getLHS(), LHSCondVal)) {
4603 if (!LHSCondVal) { // If we have 0 || X, just emit X.
4604 CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4605
4606 Value *RHSCond = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(E->getRHS());
4607 // ZExt result to int or bool.
4608 return Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(RHSCond, ResTy, "lor.ext");
4609 }
4610
4611 // 1 || RHS: If it is safe, just elide the RHS, and return 1/true.
4612 if (!CGF.ContainsLabel(E->getRHS()))
4613 return llvm::ConstantInt::get(ResTy, 1);
4614 }
4615
4616 llvm::BasicBlock *ContBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("lor.end");
4617 llvm::BasicBlock *RHSBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("lor.rhs");
4618
4619 CodeGenFunction::ConditionalEvaluation eval(CGF);
4620
4621 // Branch on the LHS first. If it is true, go to the success (cont) block.
4622 CGF.EmitBranchOnBoolExpr(E->getLHS(), ContBlock, RHSBlock,
4623 CGF.getCurrentProfileCount() -
4624 CGF.getProfileCount(E->getRHS()));
4625
4626 // Any edges into the ContBlock are now from an (indeterminate number of)
4627 // edges from this first condition. All of these values will be true. Start
4628 // setting up the PHI node in the Cont Block for this.
4629 llvm::PHINode *PN = llvm::PHINode::Create(llvm::Type::getInt1Ty(VMContext), 2,
4630 "", ContBlock);
4631 for (llvm::pred_iterator PI = pred_begin(ContBlock), PE = pred_end(ContBlock);
4632 PI != PE; ++PI)
4633 PN->addIncoming(llvm::ConstantInt::getTrue(VMContext), *PI);
4634
4635 eval.begin(CGF);
4636
4637 // Emit the RHS condition as a bool value.
4638 CGF.EmitBlock(RHSBlock);
4639 CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4640 Value *RHSCond = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(E->getRHS());
4641
4642 eval.end(CGF);
4643
4644 // Reaquire the RHS block, as there may be subblocks inserted.
4645 RHSBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
4646
4647 // Emit an unconditional branch from this block to ContBlock. Insert an entry
4648 // into the phi node for the edge with the value of RHSCond.
4649 CGF.EmitBlock(ContBlock);
4650 PN->addIncoming(RHSCond, RHSBlock);
4651
4652 // ZExt result to int.
4653 return Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(PN, ResTy, "lor.ext");
4654}

4656Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitBinComma(const BinaryOperator *E) {
4657 CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E->getLHS());
4658 CGF.EnsureInsertPoint();
4659 return Visit(E->getRHS());
4660}

4666/// isCheapEnoughToEvaluateUnconditionally - Return true if the specified
4667/// expression is cheap enough and side-effect-free enough to evaluate
4668/// unconditionally instead of conditionally. This is used to convert control
4669/// flow into selects in some cases.
4670static bool isCheapEnoughToEvaluateUnconditionally(const Expr *E,
4671 CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
4672 // Anything that is an integer or floating point constant is fine.
4673 return E->IgnoreParens()->isEvaluatable(CGF.getContext());
4674
4675 // Even non-volatile automatic variables can't be evaluated unconditionally.
4676 // Referencing a thread_local may cause non-trivial initialization work to
4677 // occur. If we're inside a lambda and one of the variables is from the scope
4678 // outside the lambda, that function may have returned already. Reading its
4679 // locals is a bad idea. Also, these reads may introduce races there didn't
4680 // exist in the source-level program.
4681}
4682
4683
4684Value *ScalarExprEmitter::
4685VisitAbstractConditionalOperator(const AbstractConditionalOperator *E) {
4686 TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
4687
4688 // Bind the common expression if necessary.
4689 CodeGenFunction::OpaqueValueMapping binding(CGF, E);
4690
4691 Expr *condExpr = E->getCond();
4692 Expr *lhsExpr = E->getTrueExpr();
4693 Expr *rhsExpr = E->getFalseExpr();
4694
4695 // If the condition constant folds and can be elided, try to avoid emitting
4696 // the condition and the dead arm.
4697 bool CondExprBool;
4698 if (CGF.ConstantFoldsToSimpleInteger(condExpr, CondExprBool)) {
4699 Expr *live = lhsExpr, *dead = rhsExpr;
4700 if (!CondExprBool) std::swap(live, dead);
4701
4702 // If the dead side doesn't have labels we need, just emit the Live part.
4703 if (!CGF.ContainsLabel(dead)) {
4704 if (CondExprBool)
4705 CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4706 Value *Result = Visit(live);
4707
4708 // If the live part is a throw expression, it acts like it has a void
4709 // type, so evaluating it returns a null Value*. However, a conditional
4710 // with non-void type must return a non-null Value*.
4711 if (!Result && !E->getType()->isVoidType())
4712 Result = llvm::UndefValue::get(CGF.ConvertType(E->getType()));
4713
4714 return Result;
4715 }
4716 }
4717
4718 // OpenCL: If the condition is a vector, we can treat this condition like
4719 // the select function.
4720 if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenCL
4721 && condExpr->getType()->isVectorType()) {
4722 CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4723
4724 llvm::Value *CondV = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(condExpr);
4725 llvm::Value *LHS = Visit(lhsExpr);
4726 llvm::Value *RHS = Visit(rhsExpr);
4727
4728 llvm::Type *condType = ConvertType(condExpr->getType());
4729 llvm::VectorType *vecTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(condType);
4730
4731 unsigned numElem = vecTy->getNumElements();
4732 llvm::Type *elemType = vecTy->getElementType();
4733
4734 llvm::Value *zeroVec = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(vecTy);
4735 llvm::Value *TestMSB = Builder.CreateICmpSLT(CondV, zeroVec);
4736 llvm::Value *tmp = Builder.CreateSExt(TestMSB,
4737 llvm::VectorType::get(elemType,
4738 numElem),
4739 "sext");
4740 llvm::Value *tmp2 = Builder.CreateNot(tmp);
4741
4742 // Cast float to int to perform ANDs if necessary.
4743 llvm::Value *RHSTmp = RHS;
4744 llvm::Value *LHSTmp = LHS;
4745 bool wasCast = false;
4746 llvm::VectorType *rhsVTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(RHS->getType());
4747 if (rhsVTy->getElementType()->isFloatingPointTy()) {
4748 RHSTmp = Builder.CreateBitCast(RHS, tmp2->getType());
4749 LHSTmp = Builder.CreateBitCast(LHS, tmp->getType());
4750 wasCast = true;
4751 }
4752
4753 llvm::Value *tmp3 = Builder.CreateAnd(RHSTmp, tmp2);
4754 llvm::Value *tmp4 = Builder.CreateAnd(LHSTmp, tmp);
4755 llvm::Value *tmp5 = Builder.CreateOr(tmp3, tmp4, "cond");
4756 if (wasCast)
4757 tmp5 = Builder.CreateBitCast(tmp5, RHS->getType());
4758
4759 return tmp5;
4760 }
4761
4762 // If this is a really simple expression (like x ? 4 : 5), emit this as a
4763 // select instead of as control flow. We can only do this if it is cheap and
4764 // safe to evaluate the LHS and RHS unconditionally.
4765 if (isCheapEnoughToEvaluateUnconditionally(lhsExpr, CGF) &&
4766 isCheapEnoughToEvaluateUnconditionally(rhsExpr, CGF)) {
4767 llvm::Value *CondV = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(condExpr);
4768 llvm::Value *StepV = Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(CondV, CGF.Int64Ty);
4769
4770 CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E, StepV);
4771
4772 llvm::Value *LHS = Visit(lhsExpr);
4773 llvm::Value *RHS = Visit(rhsExpr);
4774 if (!LHS) {
4775 // If the conditional has void type, make sure we return a null Value*.
4776 assert(!RHS && "LHS and RHS types must match");
4777 return nullptr;
4778 }
4779 return Builder.CreateSelect(CondV, LHS, RHS, "cond");
4780 }
4781
4782 llvm::BasicBlock *LHSBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("cond.true");
4783 llvm::BasicBlock *RHSBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("cond.false");
4784 llvm::BasicBlock *ContBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("cond.end");
4785
4786 CodeGenFunction::ConditionalEvaluation eval(CGF);
4787 CGF.EmitBranchOnBoolExpr(condExpr, LHSBlock, RHSBlock,
4788 CGF.getProfileCount(lhsExpr));
4789
4790 CGF.EmitBlock(LHSBlock);
4791 CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4792 eval.begin(CGF);
4793 Value *LHS = Visit(lhsExpr);
4794 eval.end(CGF);
4795
4796 LHSBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
4797 Builder.CreateBr(ContBlock);
4798
4799 CGF.EmitBlock(RHSBlock);
4800 eval.begin(CGF);
4801 Value *RHS = Visit(rhsExpr);
4802 eval.end(CGF);
4803
4804 RHSBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
4805 CGF.EmitBlock(ContBlock);
4806
4807 // If the LHS or RHS is a throw expression, it will be legitimately null.
4808 if (!LHS)
4809 return RHS;
4810 if (!RHS)
4811 return LHS;
4812
4813 // Create a PHI node for the real part.
4814 llvm::PHINode *PN = Builder.CreatePHI(LHS->getType(), 2, "cond");
4815 PN->addIncoming(LHS, LHSBlock);
4816 PN->addIncoming(RHS, RHSBlock);
4817 return PN;
4818}

4824Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitVAArgExpr(VAArgExpr *VE) {
4825 QualType Ty = VE->getType();
4826
4827 if (Ty->isVariablyModifiedType())
4828 CGF.EmitVariablyModifiedType(Ty);
4829
4830 Address ArgValue = Address::invalid();
4831 Address ArgPtr = CGF.EmitVAArg(VE, ArgValue);
4832
4833 llvm::Type *ArgTy = ConvertType(VE->getType());
4834
4835 // If EmitVAArg fails, emit an error.
4836 if (!ArgPtr.isValid()) {
4837 CGF.ErrorUnsupported(VE, "va_arg expression");

4842 llvm::Value *Val = Builder.CreateLoad(ArgPtr);
4843
4844 // If EmitVAArg promoted the type, we must truncate it.
4845 if (ArgTy != Val->getType()) {
4846 if (ArgTy->isPointerTy() && !Val->getType()->isPointerTy())
4847 Val = Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Val, ArgTy);
4848 else
4849 Val = Builder.CreateTrunc(Val, ArgTy);
4850 }
4851
4852 return Val;
4853}

4859// Convert a vec3 to vec4, or vice versa.
4860static Value *ConvertVec3AndVec4(CGBuilderTy &Builder, CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4861 Value *Src, unsigned NumElementsDst) {
4862 llvm::Value *UnV = llvm::UndefValue::get(Src->getType());
4863 SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 4> Args;
4864 Args.push_back(Builder.getInt32(0));
4865 Args.push_back(Builder.getInt32(1));
4866 Args.push_back(Builder.getInt32(2));
4867 if (NumElementsDst == 4)
4868 Args.push_back(llvm::UndefValue::get(CGF.Int32Ty));
4869 llvm::Constant *Mask = llvm::ConstantVector::get(Args);
4870 return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Src, UnV, Mask);
4871}
4872
4873// Create cast instructions for converting LLVM value \p Src to LLVM type \p
4874// DstTy. \p Src has the same size as \p DstTy. Both are single value types
4875// but could be scalar or vectors of different lengths, and either can be
4876// pointer.
4877// There are 4 cases:
4878// 1. non-pointer -> non-pointer : needs 1 bitcast
4879// 2. pointer -> pointer : needs 1 bitcast or addrspacecast
4880// 3. pointer -> non-pointer
4881// a) pointer -> intptr_t : needs 1 ptrtoint
4882// b) pointer -> non-intptr_t : needs 1 ptrtoint then 1 bitcast
4883// 4. non-pointer -> pointer
4884// a) intptr_t -> pointer : needs 1 inttoptr
4885// b) non-intptr_t -> pointer : needs 1 bitcast then 1 inttoptr
4886// Note: for cases 3b and 4b two casts are required since LLVM casts do not
4887// allow casting directly between pointer types and non-integer non-pointer
4888// types.
4889static Value *createCastsForTypeOfSameSize(CGBuilderTy &Builder,
4890 const llvm::DataLayout &DL,
4891 Value *Src, llvm::Type *DstTy,
4892 StringRef Name = "") {
4893 auto SrcTy = Src->getType();
4894
4895 // Case 1.
4896 if (!SrcTy->isPointerTy() && !DstTy->isPointerTy())
4897 return Builder.CreateBitCast(Src, DstTy, Name);
4898
4899 // Case 2.
4900 if (SrcTy->isPointerTy() && DstTy->isPointerTy())
4901 return Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(Src, DstTy, Name);
4902
4903 // Case 3.
4904 if (SrcTy->isPointerTy() && !DstTy->isPointerTy()) {
4905 // Case 3b.
4906 if (!DstTy->isIntegerTy())
4907 Src = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Src, DL.getIntPtrType(SrcTy));
4908 // Cases 3a and 3b.
4909 return Builder.CreateBitOrPointerCast(Src, DstTy, Name);
4910 }
4911
4912 // Case 4b.
4913 if (!SrcTy->isIntegerTy())
4914 Src = Builder.CreateBitCast(Src, DL.getIntPtrType(DstTy));
4915 // Cases 4a and 4b.
4916 return Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Src, DstTy, Name);
4917}
4918
4919Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitAsTypeExpr(AsTypeExpr *E) {
4920 Value *Src = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getSrcExpr());
4921 llvm::Type *DstTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
4922
4923 llvm::Type *SrcTy = Src->getType();
4924 unsigned NumElementsSrc = isa<llvm::VectorType>(SrcTy) ?
4925 cast<llvm::VectorType>(SrcTy)->getNumElements() : 0;
4926 unsigned NumElementsDst = isa<llvm::VectorType>(DstTy) ?
4927 cast<llvm::VectorType>(DstTy)->getNumElements() : 0;
4928
4929 // Going from vec3 to non-vec3 is a special case and requires a shuffle
4930 // vector to get a vec4, then a bitcast if the target type is different.
4931 if (NumElementsSrc == 3 && NumElementsDst != 3) {
4932 Src = ConvertVec3AndVec4(Builder, CGF, Src, 4);
4933
4934 if (!CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().PreserveVec3Type) {
4935 Src = createCastsForTypeOfSameSize(Builder, CGF.CGM.getDataLayout(), Src,
4936 DstTy);
4937 }
4938
4939 Src->setName("astype");
4940 return Src;
4941 }
4942
4943 // Going from non-vec3 to vec3 is a special case and requires a bitcast
4944 // to vec4 if the original type is not vec4, then a shuffle vector to
4945 // get a vec3.
4946 if (NumElementsSrc != 3 && NumElementsDst == 3) {
4947 if (!CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().PreserveVec3Type) {
4948 auto Vec4Ty = llvm::VectorType::get(DstTy->getVectorElementType(), 4);
4949 Src = createCastsForTypeOfSameSize(Builder, CGF.CGM.getDataLayout(), Src,
4950 Vec4Ty);
4951 }
4952
4953 Src = ConvertVec3AndVec4(Builder, CGF, Src, 3);
4954 Src->setName("astype");
4955 return Src;
4956 }
4957
4958 return Src = createCastsForTypeOfSameSize(Builder, CGF.CGM.getDataLayout(),
4959 Src, DstTy, "astype");
4960}

5009LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitObjCIsaExpr(const ObjCIsaExpr *E) {
5010 // object->isa or (*object).isa
5011 // Generate code as for: *(Class*)object
5012
5013 Expr *BaseExpr = E->getBase();
5014 Address Addr = Address::invalid();
5015 if (BaseExpr->isRValue()) {
5016 Addr = Address(EmitScalarExpr(BaseExpr), getPointerAlign());
5017 } else {
5018 Addr = EmitLValue(BaseExpr).getAddress();
5019 }
5020
5021 // Cast the address to Class*.
5022 Addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, ConvertType(E->getType()));
5023 return MakeAddrLValue(Addr, E->getType());
5024}

5027LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCompoundAssignmentLValue(
5028 const CompoundAssignOperator *E) {
5029 ScalarExprEmitter Scalar(*this);
5030 Value *Result = nullptr;
5031 switch (E->getOpcode()) {
5032#define COMPOUND_OP(Op) \
5033 case BO_##Op##Assign: \
5034 return Scalar.EmitCompoundAssignLValue(E, &ScalarExprEmitter::Emit##Op, \
5035 Result)
5036 COMPOUND_OP(Mul);
5037 COMPOUND_OP(Div);
5038 COMPOUND_OP(Rem);
5039 COMPOUND_OP(Add);
5040 COMPOUND_OP(Sub);
5041 COMPOUND_OP(Shl);
5042 COMPOUND_OP(Shr);
5043 COMPOUND_OP(And);
5044 COMPOUND_OP(Xor);
5045 COMPOUND_OP(Or);
5046#undef COMPOUND_OP
5047
5048 case BO_PtrMemD:
5049 case BO_PtrMemI:
5050 case BO_Mul:
5051 case BO_Div:
5052 case BO_Rem:
5053 case BO_Add:
5054 case BO_Sub:
5055 case BO_Shl:
5056 case BO_Shr:
5057 case BO_LT:
5058 case BO_GT:
5059 case BO_LE:
5060 case BO_GE:
5061 case BO_EQ:
5062 case BO_NE:
5063 case BO_Cmp:
5064 case BO_And:
5065 case BO_Xor:
5066 case BO_Or:
5067 case BO_LAnd:
5068 case BO_LOr:
5069 case BO_Assign:
5070 case BO_Comma:
5071 llvm_unreachable("Not valid compound assignment operators");
5072 }
5073
5074 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled compound assignment operator");
5075}
5076
5077Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(Value *Ptr,
5078 ArrayRef<Value *> IdxList,
5079 bool SignedIndices,
5080 bool IsSubtraction,
5081 SourceLocation Loc,
5082 const Twine &Name) {
5083 Value *GEPVal = Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(Ptr, IdxList, Name);
5084
5085 // If the pointer overflow sanitizer isn't enabled, do nothing.
5086 if (!SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::PointerOverflow))
5087 return GEPVal;
5088
5089 // If the GEP has already been reduced to a constant, leave it be.
5090 if (isa<llvm::Constant>(GEPVal))
5091 return GEPVal;
5092
5093 // Only check for overflows in the default address space.
5094 if (GEPVal->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace())
5095 return GEPVal;
5096
5097 auto *GEP = cast<llvm::GEPOperator>(GEPVal);
5098 assert(GEP->isInBounds() && "Expected inbounds GEP");
5099
5100 SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
5101 auto &VMContext = getLLVMContext();
5102 const auto &DL = CGM.getDataLayout();
5103 auto *IntPtrTy = DL.getIntPtrType(GEP->getPointerOperandType());
5104
5105 // Grab references to the signed add/mul overflow intrinsics for intptr_t.
5106 auto *Zero = llvm::ConstantInt::getNullValue(IntPtrTy);
5107 auto *SAddIntrinsic =
5108 CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow, IntPtrTy);
5109 auto *SMulIntrinsic =
5110 CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow, IntPtrTy);
5111
5112 // The total (signed) byte offset for the GEP.
5113 llvm::Value *TotalOffset = nullptr;
5114 // The offset overflow flag - true if the total offset overflows.
5115 llvm::Value *OffsetOverflows = Builder.getFalse();
5116
5117 /// Return the result of the given binary operation.
5118 auto eval = [&](BinaryOperator::Opcode Opcode, llvm::Value *LHS,
5119 llvm::Value *RHS) -> llvm::Value * {
5120 assert((Opcode == BO_Add || Opcode == BO_Mul) && "Can't eval binop");
5121
5122 // If the operands are constants, return a constant result.
5123 if (auto *LHSCI = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(LHS)) {
5124 if (auto *RHSCI = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(RHS)) {
5125 llvm::APInt N;
5126 bool HasOverflow = mayHaveIntegerOverflow(LHSCI, RHSCI, Opcode,
5127 /*Signed=*/true, N);
5128 if (HasOverflow)
5129 OffsetOverflows = Builder.getTrue();
5130 return llvm::ConstantInt::get(VMContext, N);
5131 }
5132 }
5133
5134 // Otherwise, compute the result with checked arithmetic.
5135 auto *ResultAndOverflow = Builder.CreateCall(
5136 (Opcode == BO_Add) ? SAddIntrinsic : SMulIntrinsic, {LHS, RHS});
5137 OffsetOverflows = Builder.CreateOr(
5138 Builder.CreateExtractValue(ResultAndOverflow, 1), OffsetOverflows);
5139 return Builder.CreateExtractValue(ResultAndOverflow, 0);
5140 };
5141
5142 // Determine the total byte offset by looking at each GEP operand.
5143 for (auto GTI = llvm::gep_type_begin(GEP), GTE = llvm::gep_type_end(GEP);
5144 GTI != GTE; ++GTI) {
5145 llvm::Value *LocalOffset;
5146 auto *Index = GTI.getOperand();
5147 // Compute the local offset contributed by this indexing step:
5148 if (auto *STy = GTI.getStructTypeOrNull()) {
5149 // For struct indexing, the local offset is the byte position of the
5150 // specified field.
5151 unsigned FieldNo = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Index)->getZExtValue();
5152 LocalOffset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(
5153 IntPtrTy, DL.getStructLayout(STy)->getElementOffset(FieldNo));
5154 } else {
5155 // Otherwise this is array-like indexing. The local offset is the index
5156 // multiplied by the element size.
5157 auto *ElementSize = llvm::ConstantInt::get(
5158 IntPtrTy, DL.getTypeAllocSize(GTI.getIndexedType()));
5159 auto *IndexS = Builder.CreateIntCast(Index, IntPtrTy, /*isSigned=*/true);
5160 LocalOffset = eval(BO_Mul, ElementSize, IndexS);
5161 }
5162
5163 // If this is the first offset, set it as the total offset. Otherwise, add
5164 // the local offset into the running total.
5165 if (!TotalOffset || TotalOffset == Zero)
5166 TotalOffset = LocalOffset;
5167 else
5168 TotalOffset = eval(BO_Add, TotalOffset, LocalOffset);
5169 }
5170
5171 // Common case: if the total offset is zero, don't emit a check.
5172 if (TotalOffset == Zero)
5173 return GEPVal;
5174
5175 // Now that we've computed the total offset, add it to the base pointer (with
5176 // wrapping semantics).
5177 auto *IntPtr = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(GEP->getPointerOperand(), IntPtrTy);
5178 auto *ComputedGEP = Builder.CreateAdd(IntPtr, TotalOffset);
5179
5180 // The GEP is valid if:
5181 // 1) The total offset doesn't overflow, and
5182 // 2) The sign of the difference between the computed address and the base
5183 // pointer matches the sign of the total offset.
5184 llvm::Value *ValidGEP;
5185 auto *NoOffsetOverflow = Builder.CreateNot(OffsetOverflows);
5186 if (SignedIndices) {
5187 auto *PosOrZeroValid = Builder.CreateICmpUGE(ComputedGEP, IntPtr);
5188 auto *PosOrZeroOffset = Builder.CreateICmpSGE(TotalOffset, Zero);
5189 llvm::Value *NegValid = Builder.CreateICmpULT(ComputedGEP, IntPtr);
5190 ValidGEP = Builder.CreateAnd(
5191 Builder.CreateSelect(PosOrZeroOffset, PosOrZeroValid, NegValid),
5192 NoOffsetOverflow);
5193 } else if (!SignedIndices && !IsSubtraction) {
5194 auto *PosOrZeroValid = Builder.CreateICmpUGE(ComputedGEP, IntPtr);
5195 ValidGEP = Builder.CreateAnd(PosOrZeroValid, NoOffsetOverflow);
5196 } else {
5197 auto *NegOrZeroValid = Builder.CreateICmpULE(ComputedGEP, IntPtr);
5198 ValidGEP = Builder.CreateAnd(NegOrZeroValid, NoOffsetOverflow);
5199 }
5200
5201 llvm::Constant *StaticArgs[] = {EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc)};
5202 // Pass the computed GEP to the runtime to avoid emitting poisoned arguments.
5203 llvm::Value *DynamicArgs[] = {IntPtr, ComputedGEP};
5204 EmitCheck(std::make_pair(ValidGEP, SanitizerKind::PointerOverflow),
5205 SanitizerHandler::PointerOverflow, StaticArgs, DynamicArgs);
5206
5207 return GEPVal;
5208}
